title: punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: texas chili
directions: Saute onions, garlic and meat until brown.
Add all ingredients except beans.
Cook on very low heat for 4 hours.
Add beans and cook for about 30 minutes more.

title: quick steak bake
directions: Mix soups together.
Place steak in baking dish.
Pour soup over steak.
Cook 2 hours at 300°.

title: ham and cheese pockets
directions: Combine ham and cheese in small bowl; mix well.
Roll biscuits into 4 1/2-inch circles on floured surface.
Spread center of each circle generously with mustard.
Top with 2 scant tablespoons ham mixture.
Fold over biscuits to enclose filling; seal edges with fork.
Place on baking sheet.
Brush with mixture of egg and 1 tablespoon water.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, or until puffed and golden.
Serve hot or cold.

title: chocolate sauce(for homemade ice cream)
directions: Heat milk, sugar, cocoa, cornstarch, salt and butter until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Add vanilla.
Cool and serve.

title: light and easy lemon broccoli chicken
directions: In skillet in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Drain fat.
Combine soup and milk.
Stir in lemon juice and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Reduce heat to low. Cover; simmer 5 minutes or until fork-tender stirring occasionally.
Garnish with lemon slices.
Makes 4 servings. Preparation time: 5 minutes, cooking time :15 minutes.

title: meat balls and spaghetti
directions: Separately food process celery, onions, bell peppers and mushrooms.
In a large saucepot, add cooking oil.
When hot, add celery, bell pepper, onions, mushroom, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Add two tomato sauce cans of water and 1 1/2 tomato paste cans of water.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Mix all ingredients together and bake for 25 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Serves 12.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cover potatoes with salted water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook about 30 minutes, or until tender.
Drain and cool slightly.
Peel and coarsely shred potatoes; set aside.

title: mint-chocolate cookie ice cream
directions: Combine ingredients in freezer cylinder.
Layer ice and salt in freezer bucket to edge of cylinder lid.
Cover with plain ice. Churn until motor of freezer slows or follow your freezer's instructions.

title: mrs. hollon's chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except oats, nuts and chocolate chips.
Blend well with mixer.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls using teaspoon for each.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: meat-zi-pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a pie plate with a fork.
Spread evenly on bottom and sides of plate.
Press firmly in place. Spread catsup on meat, then mushrooms, Cheddar cheese and 2 tablespoons grated cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine cottage cheese, honey, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, baking soda, egg and softened yeast.
Add enough flour to form a medium dough, beating well after each addition of flour.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Rinse and drain again.
Combine beans with celery, eggs, pickles and seasonings.
Add mayonnaise or Italian dressing to your taste.
Serves 4. (Miracle Whip may be used instead of mayonnaise.)

title: chicken rolls
directions: Roll dough out and stretch it to cover one heaping tablespoonful of chicken mixture.
Seal edges.
Roll all 16 rolls out, filling as above.
Place rolls on greased cookie sheet and bake 12 to 18 minutes at 350°.
Serve with cream gravy.

title: holiday hot chocolate(mix)
directions: All ingredients are dry.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Cook ground beef in a skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain meat.
Stir in flour, onion and pepper. Stir in mushroom soup.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add sour cream and heat thoroughly.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: creamy tuna-macaroni toss
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain and return to pan to keep warm.
In a 2-quart saucepan, over medium heat, melt butter.
Add onion; cook until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour until blended; cook for 1 minute.
Gradually stir in milk, bouillon cube, salt and pepper.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in tuna and pimento.
Heat through.
Toss with macaroni; garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion, salt and pepper together.
Drain well. Melt oleo; mix with dressing mix.
Put half of dressing mix on bottom of baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour over dressing mix.
Sprinkle with remaining dressing mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta and chicken salad
directions: Prepare rotini; drain.
Combine with next 7 ingredients. Combine dressing, mayo and pepper.
Add to salad mixture.
Toss. Add chicken.
Cover and chill.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pirate's house deviled crab
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake in greased pan or individual dishes at 400° for 17 to 20 minutes.

title: english muffin loaf
directions: In a small saucepan, heat water and oil until very warm (120° to 130°).
In a large bowl, blend warm liquid, 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt, yeast and eggs at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in enough remaining flour to make a stiff batter.
Cover; let rise in warm place until light and double in size (45 to 60 minutes). Grease (not oil) and sprinkle with cornmeal two 8 x 4-inch loaf pans or 3 one pound coffee cans.
Stir down dough (beat vigorously 30 seconds); spoon into prepared pans.
Cover, let rise in warm place until double in size 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit delight
directions: Combine fruit and sour cream.
Chill for several hours.
Spoon individual servings on lettuce leaves.

title: banana punch
directions: Make orange juice according to directions.
Place bananas in blender with lemon juice and process.
Heat water and sugar in saucepan until just boiling.
Add bananas and juices.
Freeze at least 24 hours.
Remove from freezer 3 to 4 hours before serving. At serving time, mix with ginger ale to form a slush.

title: paprika sticks
directions: Slice cucumbers and cover with boiling water; leave overnight. Prepare syrup with vinegar, sugar, salt, celery seed, turmeric and mustard seed.
Pack cukes in jars.
Pour syrup over cukes and seal.
Cook in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Stir Jell-O into hot water 2 minutes.
Add cottage cheese; stir well.
Add pineapple or fruit cocktail, then add Cool Whip. Put in refrigerator until set well and serve.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix in
large
mixing
bowl,
brown
sugar, flour, salt, pumpkin pie
spice or cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger and cloves.
Add and stir
pumpkin,
evaporated milk and egg.
Pour mixture into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apple slices in greased pie plate.
In a bowl, mix sugar, oats and flour.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Pour over top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the ingredients in the order in which they are listed.
Mix the ingredients well with a spoon. Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes.
Allow the cake to cool completely before frosting it.
Frost with a cream cheese frosting.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Mix milk, pudding and Cool Whip.
Spray pan with Pam.
Line pan with graham crackers, then add mixture.
Layer with graham crackers until pudding mixture is used up, then put on topping.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake for 40 minutes in a 375° oven. Serve chilled.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cook sausage until brown and crumbly. In mixing bowl, toss together cheese and Bisquick. Add warm, undrained, sausage.
Roll into 1 inch balls. Place on cookie sheet. Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: christmas nut and date roll
directions: Combine cream and marshmallows in large bowl.
Let set 1 hour; stir occasionally.
Crush graham crackers; divide in half.
At the end of 1 hour, add chopped dates, nuts and 1/2 graham cracker mix to marshmallow cream mix.
Stir well.
Make into a roll.
Put 1/2 graham cracker crumbs on large sheet waxed paper.
Roll date mixture into crumbs; wrap in wax paper and refrigerate.
Chill several days.
Slice thin to serve.

title: buttermilk blueberry muffin
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients. Gently fold in blueberries. Combine yogurt and buttermilk. Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened. Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes. Yield: 1 dozen.

title: chicken and wine casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Pull apart or cut into bite size pieces when cool.
Place in bottom of square or oblong casserole dish. Drain mushrooms and place on top of chicken pieces.
Layer the Swiss cheese over the chicken and mushrooms.
Next, mix the mushroom soup and white wine together.
Pour over top of Swiss cheese.
Melt butter and add approximately 1 cup bread crumbs; sprinkle parsley and Parmesan cheese over top of dish and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Saute onions, bell peppers and celery in margarine.
Add crawfish tails.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes or until crawfish tails are cooked.
Add Tony's seasoning.
Add mushroom soup.
Pour in unbaked shell and top with another pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together 3/4 cup sugar and margarine.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans as directed on package; drain.
Combine with all ingredients, except onion rings.
Pour into medium size casserole. Break onion rings over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and margarine together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch glass or aluminum pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix raisins, apricots, prunes, nuts and orange juice in a bowl.
Cover and let stand several hours, stirring once or twice. Grease one large 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or 2 small 2 x 3-inch pans. Line with foil.
Drain the fruits, reserving the liquid; add water if necessary to make 1 cup.
In a large bowl, mix together bread mix, egg and the cup of liquid.
Stir until all dry ingredients are completely mixed; add fruits.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour and 40 minutes for large pan; 1 hour and 20 minutes for small pans.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; take off foil and cool completely.
May be stored in refrigerator 2 to 3 weeks in plastic wrap or foil.

title: casserole bread
directions: If using self-rising flour, omit salt.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine the ingredients in the order given. Mix well and pour into a greased 2 to 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes. This recipe doubles nicely. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add milk, oil and vanilla.
Mix well until batter is smooth.
Blend in nuts.
Spread batter into a greased, floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle one cup packed brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa over batter.
Pour 1 3/4 cups hot water over that.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Brownie-like cake comes to the top with a chocolate pudding on the bottom.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cook stew beef and short ribs slowly for 1 hour. Add frozen vegetables. Continue cooking, slowly, for approximately 30 minutes. Add tomatoes, sauce and other seasonings to taste. Cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.

title: carol's corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large casserole dish.
Mix together onion, corn, cornbread mix and egg.
Pour into dish.
Stir in 3/4 package grated cheese and save remaining for top.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 35 minutes or until casserole resembles cornbread.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.

title: creamy stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until tender.
Cut in halves lengthwise.
Scoop out insides and place in bowl, reserving shells.
Mix insides, salad dressing, cheese, chives, onions, butter and salt together; blend well.
Spoon potato mixture back into shells.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: french-apple-cake
directions: Mix well-beaten eggs, oil, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and flour with a mixer; mix well.
Then add vanilla; mix well.
Mix in apple and nuts last with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan or in Bundt pan for 45 to 60 minutes until tester comes clean.

title: corned beef rolls
directions: Separate slices of corned beef, using 2 slices at a time. Place slices (2 stacked together) on cutting board; spread top slice with cream cheese only down the center.
Slice pickle spear in half (or thirds, if large); position on slice of cream cheese. Roll up, and place seam down on tray.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef; add all the ingredients except cabbage, green beans and macaroni into large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add cabbage, green beans and macaroni; simmer until everything is tender.
Sprinkle with shredded Velveeta before serving.

title: hot macadamia dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk, blending until smooth.
Stir in shredded dried beef, onion, green pepper, garlic, pepper and ginger.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour beef mixture into a shallow glass baking dish.
Saute nuts in butter until thoroughly glazed. Sprinkle nuts over beef mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.
Serve hot with crackers.
Garnish as desired.

title: pecan cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs and fold in all ingredients. Bake in tube pan at 300° for 2 hours.

title: banana bread(makes 3 loaves or 4 small loaves)
directions: Melt butter and let cool.
Mash bananas in mixer; add one egg at a time and beat after each egg.
Add cooled butter to banana-egg mixture.
Add sugar; beat well.
On lowest setting, blend in dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cool completely before slicing.
Freezes well.

title: greek onions(6 servings)
directions: Slice onions into 1/2-inch slices.
Layer in bottom of 10-inch pie plate that has been prepared with nonstick vegetable spray. Thaw, drain and squeeze all water from spinach.
Mix the next 7 ingredients together.
Pour over onions.
Top with grated Swiss or Parmesan cheese and bacon.
Microwave, uncovered, at High power for 10 to 15 minutes, turning dish 1/4 turn every 3 to 4 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: sky valley blackberry cobbler
directions: Wash and drain berries.
Put them into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix together sugar, flour and egg.
Mixture will be dry and lumpy.
Pour over berries.
Melt butter and pour it over top. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: brownies
directions: Melt
chocolate
and
oleo in microwave.
Add sugar and eggs; beat
well.
Add flour, salt, vanilla and pecans.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.

title: moist bread stuffing
directions: Combine ingredients.
Stuff into bird cavity, or bake in loaf pan at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until golden brown and crispy.

title: quick egg souffle
directions: Heat milk and butter in upper part of double boiler. Add seasonings to eggs and beat until very light. Add eggs to hot milk and blend well. Cook over gently simmering water for 30 minutes. Serve on warm platter. Garnish with a sprig of parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry pleasure
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft and stir in milk.
Mix in lemon juice and spread into pie crust.
Dissolve Jell-O with boiling water.
Stir in strawberries and pour over cream cheese mixture. Chill until firm.
Serve topped with Cool Whip if desired.

title: apple cider
directions: Mix all together in large coffeepot.
Heat and serve.

title: kaezmarak cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 9-inch pie plate at 325° for 1 hour.
Let cool completely before frosting with whipped cream.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.
Very easy, moist and good!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large pan; add onion and saute. Add broccoli and stir. Add soup; stir and simmer. Next, stir in Cheez Whiz and cooked rice. Place into a large casserole dish. Top with buttered crumbs or sliced almonds. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: cowboy saucey
directions: In a 2-cup glass measuring cup, combine butter, vinegar, sugar, mustard, black pepper, Worcestershire sauce and cayenne pepper.
Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes, stirring to blend. Serve at room temperature as a dipping sauce or use as a basting sauce, during grilling.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling water with salt.
Drain and rinse. Mix the remaining ingredients with the spaghetti.
Let chill several hours before serving.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and onion.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, crush enough chips to make crust.
In large bowl mix cream soups, milk, Ro-Tel and garlic powder.
Pour evenly over chips and meat. Top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven.
Pie is done when bubbling in center.
serve with remaining chips and salad.

title: chicken-n-rice casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, mix soups, water and rice.
Lay washed chicken pieces over top.
Sprinkle with spices and dot with margarine.
Bake, covered, at 275° for 3 hours or at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
During last 30 minutes, uncover and turn heat up to 350°.

title: lemon marinade chicken barbecue
directions: Split chicken, halves or quarters.
Place in shallow baking pans.
Combine other ingredients in a jar and shake or whip in a bowl.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Cover tightly and marinade in refrigerator 6 to 8 hours or overnight (up to 24 hours).

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix together and dip with chips.

title: ravishing rocky road
directions: Place chocolate in 2-quart glass bowl. Microwave on High 2 1/2 minutes. Stir well until evenly melted. Fold in marshmallows and nuts. Coat evenly. Turn into buttered 8-inch square dish. Chill until set. Cut in squares. Makes 2 pounds.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion, garlic and mushrooms in butter until tender. Dredge meat in flour and lightly fry in separate pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place meat in pan with onion, garlic and mushrooms.
Simmer for about 45 minutes.
Uncover and continue cooking for 15 minutes.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Serve over pasta.

title: peach cake
directions: Place peaches in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix dry jello and sugar together and sprinkle over peaches.
Sprinkle cake mix over this. Pour margarine and water over all.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: salmon stew
directions: Cook potatoes and onions.
Bring milk to boil; add butter, potatoes, onion and salmon.
Cook on low heat for approximately 20 minutes.

title: taco tater skins
directions: Combine all and let set 1 hour. Drain well.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and 1/4 cup melted margarine; line an 8-inch pie pan.
Saute onions in 2 tablespoons margarine until tender, but not brown.
Put in pie shell.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over onions.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Combine ingredients (will be soft).
Refrigerate 2 hours. Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll to 1/4-inch on lightly floured surface.
Cut out and place on cookie sheet 3-inches apart. Decorate.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are brown.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, blend together all ingredients.
Turn mixture into pie shell.
Bake in 375° oven until sharp knife inserted near center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: cheese dip
directions: Simmer Ro-Tel, ground cumin, pepper, garlic powder and water for 20 minutes.
Grate American cheese.
Alternating cheese and Ro-Tel mixture, mix in blender until well blended.
Refrigerate. Best served cold.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute the celery and onion in skillet in 2 or 3 tablespoons butter.
Mix all other ingredients in casserole dish and add celery and onion mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Serve hot.

title: toasted and salted pumpkin seeds(very easy and fun.  kids love it.)
directions: Melt butter on a cookie sheet in a preheated 425° oven.
Stir the pumpkin seeds around until well coated.
Toast for about 20 minutes or until lightly brown, stirring occasionally.
Season with salt and store in a covered jar.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix soda into buttermilk. Cut shortening into remaining dry ingredients. Add milk gradually to form a soft dough. Knead 30 seconds on a lightly floured surface. Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with floured biscuit cutter. Place on a greased baking sheet. Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: oatmeal biscuits
directions: Place oats in electric blender; process until oats are ground. Combine first 6 ingredients; mix.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk; stir well. Sprinkle 2 teaspoons flour over work surface.
Dump dough and knead 10 to 12 times.
Roll out to 1/2 inch thick.
Cut into rounds with 2-inch cutter.
Put on cookie sheet coated with Mazola.
Bake at 400° until brown (10 minutes).
Makes 4 biscuits, 111 calories each.

title: meringue
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add sugar slowly.
Add cream of tartar and vanilla.
Beat until stiff.
Pour over baked pudding.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cut up candied pineapple and cherries in a large bowl. Add raisins.
Pour the orange juice over this and let sit while mixing other ingredients.
In a dish, melt your margarine. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Chip nuts up real fine in a bowl.
Put flour on the chopped nuts and work in well.
Mix this in with your eggs and margarine.
Mix in flour and fruits.
Mix real good.
Put in 2 tube pans and cook at 250° until done.
Test by toothpick.
(Grease and flour tube pans.)
This makes 2 cakes.

title: cottage cheese cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix all the rest of the ingredients together in electric mixer.
Butter and flour a spring-form pan.
Fold in egg whites and pour into pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° (first 10 minutes at 400°).
Cool in oven. Refrigerate.

title: whipped salad
directions: Soak gelatine in cold water.
Mix lemon juice, sugar and pineapple; bring to a boil.
Add this mixture to the gelatine and cool.
Beat when nearly cool enough to set, then add remaining ingredients in order and mold or leave in covered dish.
Can decorate with maraschino cherry halves.

title: steak or crock-pot soup
directions: Saute beef.
Add 2 cups water and rest of ingredients.
Bring to boil and serve.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Brown chicken breasts. Place all ingredients in crock-pot. Cook on low setting for 6 hours. It's good on rice.

title: golden fudge
directions: Combine sugar, condensed milk, evaporated milk and margarine in pan over medium heat until a bit dropped in cold water forms a hard ball.
Remove from heat and add nuts and Marshmallow Fluff. Spread in buttered pan.
Cool in refrigerator before cutting.

title: maw-maw's chocolate pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, cocoa, sugar and salt.
Add milk and cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook 2 minutes and remove from heat.
Add small amount to egg yolks and stir well.
Add egg mixture into hot pudding, stirring constantly.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: easy beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Slice potatoes.
In a casserole dish, place in layers, meat, potatoes and onions.
Pour soup over and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake until it melts.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: decadent chocolate brownies
directions: Spray an 8-inch square pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cocoa, flour and baking powder; set aside.
Combine oil and sugars well.
Lightly beat egg whites.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add cocoa mixture and mix well.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 20 minutes. Cool before cutting.

title: bits 'o brickle cookies
directions: Blend sugars, margarine and oil until well mixed.
Add almond extract and eggs; mix well.
Mix dry ingredients together. Gradually blend in at low speed.
Stir in brickle chips and almonds.
Shape large tablespoonfuls of dough into balls; roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. With fork dipped in sugar, flatten in crisscross pattern.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until light golden brown around edges.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Boil potatoes. Combine soup, sour cream, water and dill weed. Blend well. Alternate layers of potato and soup in lightly greased casserole dish.

title: meatza pie
directions: Combine hamburger, milk, bread crumbs and garlic salt; form this into a 9-inch or larger pie plate to make a pie shell.
Add to this one at a time, tomato sauce, mushrooms, Cheddar cheese and oregano.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let set 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and sugar with fork to fine crumbs. Spread over cold pie shell.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix this up and store in container.
Will keep for months. When you use, mix 1/2 cup of mix with 1/2 cup of water.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter, and mix well.
Add cooled melted butter and beat well.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: kahlua trifle
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan, then cut into squares and cool cake.
Make pudding according to package.
Pour Kahlua over cooled cake squares and refrigerate overnight or several hours.

title: pork shish kabob
directions: Marinate 24 hours before cooking all ingredients.
Before cooking on barbecue grill, arrange ingredients on bamboo skewer (1 cube of pork, 1 green pepper slice and 1 slice of onion and repeat).
Cook shish kabobs on barbecue grill 25 to 30 minutes. Serve with fried rice and sweet and sour sauce.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix the sugar and oil well.
Add the eggs, buttermilk and soda; mix.
Add the flour; mix until well blended.
Add the jam, preserves, cinnamon, cloves, allspice and chopped nuts (if desired).
Bake in tube pan for 30 minutes at 350°, or until done.

title: easter baskets
directions: Place coconut in small container, add a few drops of green food coloring.
Cover container and shake until coconut is green. Set aside.

title: cole slaw
directions: Chop or grind cabbage and onion with green pepper.
Sprinkle on salt.
Pour boiling water over chopped vegetables.
Set 1 hour. Drain.
Combine sugar, vinegar, pimentos, celery seed and mustard seed.
Pour over vegetables.
Set 24 hours.
Store tightly covered in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: reuben meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly mix 1/4 cup soup, meat, bread crumbs, eggs, parsley and garlic.
On foil or wax paper, shape into a 10 x 15-inch rectangle.
Combine sauerkraut, shredded cheese and caraway; spread over meat.
Roll into loaf.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, or until done.
Combine rest of soup and horseradish; pour over loaf. Place cheese triangles on top.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: cherries on snow
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter.
Press into bottom of 8-inch spring-form pan.
Line sides with wax paper.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar; let boil.
Add Jell-O and cream cheese.
Stir until dissolved.
Add ice water and cool until it begins to thicken.
Add Cool Whip and pecans.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour into deep dish unbaked pie shell. Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook ground beef, onions and seasonings until done.
Put in a 2-quart baking dish and cover with mashed potatoes and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese has melted and lightly browned.

title: monkey bread
directions: Pour boiling water over the Crisco and sugar and cool. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Mix Crisco mixture with eggs and add flour until dough is a stiff batter.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Knead and dip rolls in melted margarine.
Tear into small balls and jam together in bread pan.
Let stand 3 hours. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, then 15 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken; pick off bone and set aside (save broth). Add 3 to 4 cans mixed vegetables to broth and chicken. Bring to a boil; thicken with cornstarch. Pour into a long pan; top with biscuits. Bake until biscuits are brown.

title: easy crock-pot stroganoff
directions: You can add 3 tablespoons cornstarch, mixed in 1/4 cup cold water, to thicken.
Blend until smooth and heat through.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: enchiladas(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; drain.
Add soup and enchilada sauce; simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Use a pat of butter and quick-fry shells.
Line 11 x 13-inch pan by filling shells with mixture, then sprinkle some cheese on top; roll.
Repeat until all shells are used.
Pour remaining mixture over top, covering shells.
Cover with cheese.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: basil-tomato cream sauce
directions: Saute onion, pepper, garlic and basil in oil.
Add tomatoes. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add cream, salt and pepper.
(You can thicken with flour, if desired.)
Serve over pasta, scallops, etc.

title: my aunt's coated pecans
directions: Into beaten egg white, add brown sugar, flour and vanilla. Mix well.
Add pecan halves; stir gently with fork until each half is well coated.
Place each half separately on greased baking sheet and bake at 300° until light brown.

title: apple cake with nuts
directions: Mix apples and sugar.
Add oil, nuts, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Add 2 mixture together; blend well.
Fold into a well-greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake shrinks from sides of pan.
Serve with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: oreo cookie pie
directions: Crush Oreo cookies; set 1/2 cup aside.
Mix remaining crumbs with butter or margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine in pan on medium-high.
(Don't overcook.)
After warm, place in dish and serve.
Sprinkle pepper and salt to taste.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and 1 1/2 sticks margarine to make crust. Mix sugar, 2 sticks margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Whip for 10 minutes for filling.

title: fruit cocktail pudding
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add 1 beaten egg and drained fruit cocktail.
Pour into buttered baking dish and sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in an 8-inch square baking dish.

title: southwest iowa's sweet 'n sour sauerkraut
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add onions and apples, saute until softened, 3 to 5 minutes.
Combine onion and apples with sauerkraut in large mixing bowl.
Stir in tomatoes, brown sugar and wine.
Season with caraway seed and pepper.
Place mixture in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 1 1/4 hours.
Uncover and bake another 1/2 hour.
Serve as a side dish to roast turkey. Serves 12 people.

title: biscuits
directions: Measure dry ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Cut in butter with pastry blender or two knives until mixture is coarse crumbs. Add sour cream, stirring until mixture is moistened.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead 10 times to form a soft, smooth dough.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° about 10 minutes.

title: maple marshmallow frosting
directions: Put maple sugar and boiling water in saucepan, stirring occasionally, until sugar is dissolved, then boil without stirring until syrup will thread when dropped from tip of spoon. Add marshmallow cream and pour gradually on beaten white of egg, beating constantly. Place over hot water and fold over and over for 3 minutes; remove from fire and continue folding until the right consistency to spread.

title: crispy chicken tenders -- with dip
directions: Preheat oven to 400° and grease a shallow baking pan. Combine 2/3 cup mayonnaise or salad dressing, onion flakes and dry mustard in mixing bowl and mix well. Combine cracker crumbs and sesame seeds. Cut chicken breasts in strips; dip into mayonnaise mixture, then coat with cracker crumbs. Arrange in baking pan. Bake about 15 minutes.

title: warm fruity rice pudding
directions: Combine milk, fruit cocktail juice, vanilla pudding mix, ginger and rice in a saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens. Remove from heat, add drained fruit and let stand for 15 minutes before serving.

title: cox hot sauce
directions: Cook all of this about 20 to 30 minutes on a low heat; after it boils, mix in 1 or 2 teaspoons cornstarch in a little water and stir into boiling sauce. Cook until it thickens. Measurements are approximate; adjust to your own taste.

title: open-faced tacos
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add the can of chili.
Mix together the Cheddar cheese soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Heat beef mixture and soup mixture.
On the serving plate, place chips on the bottom. Next, place meat mixture, then cooked rice and top with soup mixture.

title: exotic chicken salad
directions: Thaw and drain peas.
Mix all ingredients.
Serve on lettuce. Top with Chinese noodles.

title: taco soup
directions: Simmer all ingredients (except Fritos and cheese) until flavors blend.
Serve over Fritos with grated cheese on top.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 or 9-inch ovenproof skillet or layer pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Arrange fruit in skillet.
Cream 1/3 cup margarine and granulated sugar until light and fluffy. Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Carefully pour batter over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Immediately invert onto serving platter.

title: ranch style baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: swiss chicken cutlets
directions: Cut each cheese slice in half; place one half on top of each cutlet.
Starting with a short end, tightly roll up cutlets, jelly-roll style.
Tie securely with string.
On waxed paper, combine flour and pepper.
Mix well.
Add cutlets; toss gently to coat.
In large nonstick skillet, melt butter and add cutlets. Cook about 3 minutes or until golden; turn frequently.
Add broth, wine and oregano.
Cook until chicken is cooked through and sauce is slightly thickened, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove string and serve.

title: pennsylvania dutch mayonnaise
directions: Combine hard-cooked egg yolks, mashed and worked smooth, uncooked egg yolk, salt, paprika and mustard in a bowl.
Work smooth.
Add the oil by tablespoonfuls, beating vigorously after each addition, until half of the oil has been used.
Then beat in small amounts of the remaining oil alternately with the lemon juice and vinegar.
Makes 1 cup dressing.

title: easy peas salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let set overnight in the refrigerator.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine soy sauce, sugar, ginger root and sesame seed in a bowl.
Place chicken in a baking dish and pour sauce over it.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes, basting as chicken bakes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil, skin and mash potatoes. Add other ingredients.
Put in casserole dish. Top with topping mixture.

title: creamy cheese soup
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients until vegetables are tender. Stir in cream cheese; add milk, butter and flour until blended. Cook until mixture bubbles and thickens.

title: cooked whipped frosting
directions: Cook and stir constantly until thick and creamy the milk and flour.
Cool completely.
Beat 4 minutes on high speed the butter and shortening.
Add sugar.
Beat 4 minutes on high speed.
Add flour and milk mixture.
Beat 4 minutes more.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Drain fruit and save juice to make 2 cups.
Combine 2 cups of juice, cornstarch, sugar, sherry and butter and cook over medium heat until thickened.
Arrange fruits attractively in shallow casserole dish.
Pour thickened sauce over all and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: divinity roll
directions: Cook together sugar, syrup and water until hard ball forms. Fold in egg whites.
Beat egg whites with syrup mixture.
Bring to boil over medium heat, then beat to very hard and stiff stage, about 7 minutes.
Make a roll of this mixture.
Spread caramels, water and pecans over roll.

title: banana split cake
directions: Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: molasses whole wheat bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix the molasses/syrup, milk, shortening, salt, proofed yeast and the egg.
Add the wheat flour, 1 c. at a time, and mix well.
Add 2 c. white flour and mix very well by hand, adding more white flour if needed for desired consistency. Pour out onto a floured surface and knead 8-10 minutes until dough is stiff but not sticky.
Put in a greased bowl and let rise 1-1/2 hours or until doubled in bulk.
Halve and put into 2 greased loaf pans and let rise again until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour. Bake at 375°, 45 minutes to an hour.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together, then add egg and mix well.
Melt margarine and add to sugar mixture until blended.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Put 1 cup nuts into pie crust.
Pour half of mixture into each crust.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until you can shake pie and it seems solid.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with beater.
Place in pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
Place on jelly roll pan of water.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Remove yolks and place in small bowl.
Mash egg yolks and blend with mustard and mayonnaise.
Stuff egg whites with mixture.
Garnish with paprika.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef, onions and green chiles. Season with salt, pepper and garlic salt. Dip 3 tortillas in enchilada sauce and place in bottom of greased pan or casserole (9 x 13-inch).
Spread with 1/4 of the meat mixture, 1/4 of the soup and 1/4 of the cheese. Repeat layers. Bake at 450° for 1/2 hour or until bubbly.

title: broiled pork chops with orange glaze
directions: Slash edges of chops to prevent curling.
Season with salt and pepper.
Broil 4 inches from heat, brushing often with mixture of juice and remaining ingredients, about 15 minutes.
Turn and broil, basting often until thoroughly cooked and well browned.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place in 2-quart casserole dish in layers in the order listed. Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered and 1/2 hour uncovered.

title: party pork balls(appetizer)
directions: Combine pork, water chestnuts, onions, ginger, salt, soy sauce, egg, and bread crumbs in a large bowl; mix well.
Shape into 36 balls.
Roll in cornstarch to coat lightly, shaking off excess.
Brown in oil in a large skillet.
Remove balls as they brown to a roasting pan; cover loosely with foil.
Bake in a moderate oven 350° for 20 minutes, or until thoroughly cooked. Combine with sweet and sour sauce.

title: cajun potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in crab boil until tender.
Cool.
Slice potatoes thin and layer in casserole dish.
Melt butter and add sour cream.
Salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle grated cheese and green onions and crumble over top.
Bake at 450° for 35 minutes.

title: jello delights
directions: Mix strawberry jello and icing sugar; set aside.
Combine remaining jello, coconut, milk and vanilla.
Mix and roll in small balls.
Roll in jello and sugar mixture.
(When making double recipe, use 1 can of condensed milk.)

title: five hour beef stew
directions: Don't brown the beef cubes.
Cut the vegetables into chunks; dice the onion.
Mix all ingredients well and put into a Dutch oven or a roaster.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours. Don't peek; don't stir.
Serve with hot biscuits.
Vegetable can be varied.
Can be put into a crock-pot on low for 8 hours.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, water and oil together.
Pour over cucumbers, pepper, tomato and onion.
Mix well.

title: raina's favorite brown cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put margarine, sugar and eggs in mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer on medium until smooth.
Add flour, baking soda and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts (if desired).
Dough will be very stiff.
Spoon dough onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes for soft cookies; for 10 to 12 minutes for crisp cookies.

title: southern corn muffins
directions: Mix corn meal in a 2-quart bowl.
(Omit salt and baking powder when using self-rising meal.)
Add milk gradually until mixture is firm.
Add egg and melted shortening.
Stir 1 minute, until smooth.
Pour into warm greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 servings.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Combine meal, milk, eggs, salt, soda, bacon drippings and corn. Mix well. Brown beef and drain on paper towel. Saute onion and drain on paper towel. Pour half of batter into well-greased iron skillet. Sprinkle cheese over batter. Sprinkle cooled meat over cheese. Sprinkle chopped onion over meat. Place peppers over onion. Top with remaining batter. Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or browned.

title: meringue surprise
directions: Combine egg whites, vanilla and salt; beat until stiff.
Beat in sugar gradually until stiff and satiny.
At Christmas, divide mixture into 2 parts and add red and green food coloring.
Fold half of chocolate chips into each mixture.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, oil, salt, pepper and water.
Bring to a boil.
Set aside to cool.
Mix all the vegetables.
Pour vinegar mixture over vegetables and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours or overnight. Yield:
15 servings.

title: cabbage and sausage soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter until onion is translucent. Add the chicken broth, sausage, and potatoes.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat until potatoes are fork tender.
Add cabbage.
Just before serving, add the vinegar and ketchup.
Serve with a crusty bread.
Serves 4.

title: little pig souffle
directions: In 9x13-inch casserole dish, layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese.
Beat eggs well, add milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over casserole and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken cacciatore(microwave)
directions: In a 3-quart microproof casserole, mix onion, green pepper and butter.
Cook covered on High (max power) 4 to 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and flour; stir until smooth.
Stir in all ingredients except chicken.
Cover and cook on High (max power) 5 minutes. Add chicken pieces, immersing them in sauce.
Cook, covered, on High (max power) 20 to 25 minutes until chicken is tender.
Stir once during cooking.
Allow to stand 5 minutes covered after cooking.
Remove bay leaf and serve with rice.
Delicious!

title: salmon balls
directions: Mash salmon; add flour, cornmeal, soda, eggs and buttermilk. Shape into balls, using 1 teaspoon for each ball.
Fry in 2-inches hot fat until brown.
Drain and serve hot.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugars. Add eggs, vanilla and salt. Then add dry ingredients, flour and soda slowly and cream together last oatmeal, raisins and pecans.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugars, oleo and oil.
Add vanilla and eggs; mix well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Roll in small balls. Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar or a cinnamon and sugar mix.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: savory pastry
directions: Combine flour, celery seed, salt and paprika; cut in shortening.
Sprinkle with 2 to 3 tablespoons water, mixing with fork until all flour is moistened and dough clings together.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick on floured surface.
Cut to fit top of casserole.
Put on top and cut slits near center.
Bake at 425° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in 2 layers.
Split layers in half when cooled.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut (reserve a small amount of plain coconut to put on finished cake).
Chill mixture.
Reserve 1 cup for frosting.
Spread remainder between layers and on top of cake.

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat oil in a Dutch oven and saute the onion until soft.
Add the meat, garlic, chili powder and cumin.
Cook until the meat is browned.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Simmer about 2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: texas triple dip
directions: Layer equal amounts of each ingredient in a clear glass bowl. Serve with tortilla chips or corn chips.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Boil pepperoni for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Cook and drain spaghetti.
Add margarine and generous amount of Parmesan cheese to spaghetti.
Cook onion and ground beef; drain fat.
Add sauce and simmer about 15 minutes.
Add mushrooms.

title: pretzel appetizer
directions: Break pretzels into small pieces. Combine all ingredients and coat pretzels. Spread in a single layer on cookie sheet and bake at 200° for 1 hour. Cool and enjoy.

title: chiffon cake
directions: Whip egg whites and cream of tartar until very stiff peaks are formed.
Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder into large bowl. Make a well in center of flour.
Add oil, egg yolks, water and vanilla.
Beat with wooden spoon until smooth.
Gradually pour egg yolk mixture over beaten egg whites.
Fold gently.
Put in tube pan and bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: bits 'o brickle cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Roll in small balls (size of walnuts).
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with sugar dipped glass bottom.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Melt butter and add next 4 ingredients together.
Make into small balls.
Dip in chocolate and paraffin.
May use chocolate almond bark instead of paraffin mixture.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Mix thoroughly and roll very thin.
Cut in strips and bake on ungreased baking sheet in a 450° oven for 15 minutes.

title: fried morel mushrooms
directions: Immediately upon your return from finding mushrooms in the woods, or being gifted with "morels", rinse and slice the morel mushrooms in half, down the middle.
Place in a bowl of salt water, cover and soak overnight in the refrigerator.
This is done to eliminate any small bugs or insects.
When ready to cook, drain, rinse and carefully pat the morel mushrooms dry with paper towels.

title: holiday loaf
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients and add eggs, milk and oil.
Blend.
Stir in coconut, cherries, carrots, pecans and raisins.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured loaf pans, each 7 x 3 x 2-inches.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Turn out and cool.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.

Heat cottage cheese to lukewarm. Combine all ingredients except flour; mix well and add flour to form a stiff dough, beating well after each addition of flour. Cover and let rise until doubled in size.
Stir down the dough. Place in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart greased casserole or shape into the form you desire and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Let dough rise again (30 to 40 minutes) and bake at 350° until brown.
Brush top with butter and sprinkle with salt.
Enjoy!

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix lemon juice, milk and vanilla; add sliced bananas.
Mix Cool Whip; add pineapple and add to lemon juice mixture.
Sprinkle with coconut, nuts and cherries after pouring into graham cracker crust.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place in layers as follows:
sauerkraut, onion, brown sugar and pork chops; top with cream of chicken soup.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour in regular oven or 22 to 28 minutes in microwave.

title: pigs -n- blanket
directions: Flatten out biscuits.
Roll around wiener.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.

title: lane cake
directions: Cream butter until smooth; add sugar gradually and beat until light and fluffy. Add vanilla. Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating until smooth. Fold into beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into 4 round 9-inch cake pans, greased and floured. Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes. Let cool.
Spread Lane Frosting between layers and on top and sides.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Bake cake mix in 13
x 9-inch pan.
Cool the cake.
Mix together cream cheese,
vanilla
pudding and milk until thick, then pour over cake.
Cook the pineapple and cornstarch.
When it's cool, spread on
top
of pudding.
Top with Dream Whip or Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts or coconut if desired.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.
Serve on crisp lettuce.

title: chocolate and oat bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and butter.
Mix well; reserving 1/2 cup of mixture.
Press remaining oat mixture on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 10 minutes. Pour condensed milk evenly over crust.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.
Top with remaining oat mixture.
Press down and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Brown beef and sausage.
Add tomato sauce, mushrooms and onion.
Cook until onion is tender.
Scoop zucchini out so it looks like shells, then spoon meat mixture evenly in each zucchini.
Top with Mozzarella.
Cook until golden brown and bubbly, approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour, at 350°.
May take longer, depending on the size of the zucchini.
You can raise the heat just before taking it out to brown the top.

title: lace cookie cups with ice cream
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
In medium saucepan, bring corn syrup to a full boil over medium heat, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add butter; reduce heat to low.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until butter melts, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in flour, sugar and nuts. Drop tablespoons of dough 4 inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Put only 2 on a sheet.
Bake for 11 to 13 minutes, or until cookies are golden brown and bubbly.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Layer into large bowl.
1st Layer: Tear angel food cake into bite-size pieces.
2nd Layer: Mix instant pudding and milk and pour over cake.
3rd Layer:
Slice berries, mix with glaze and pour over pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: herbal muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in well oiled muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes about 1 dozen.

title: *cucumber dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a glass bowl. Chill for several hours or overnight. Can be used as dip or side dish.

title: red onion and fennel salad
directions: Wash and slice thin fennel bulb and onion.
Add remaining ingredients; toss.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours and serve with side dishes.

title: bierocks
directions: Fix hot roll mix as directed on box.
Let stand for 45 minutes.
Brown ground beef; add salt.
Drain ground beef.
Add sliced cabbage, longwise.
Add pepper and simmer until cabbage is done.

title: i love you cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand with wooden spoon.
Do not use a beater while mixing.	Bake in a 10 x 6 loaf pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Let squash, onions, sweet peppers, hot peppers and salt set overnight.
Next day, rinse in cold water and drain.
Mix sugar, vinegar, dry mustard, turmeric, celery seed and black pepper. Bring to a boil after adding red sweet peppers.

title: swedish cucumbers
directions: Sprinkle the sugar and salt over the sliced cucumbers.
Mix the water and vinegar and pour over.
Sprinkle with dill. Marinate for a few hours before serving.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except nuts.
After mixing well, roll in chopped nuts.
Chill well.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken breasts in water (with about 4 chicken bouillon cubes) until tender. (I use boneless or split breasts with skin removed.) Take chicken out of broth and cool enough to take off bone and cut into bite-sized pieces (don't add to broth yet). Add the chicken broth. Cut small the celery, carrots and onion. Add to broth and cook until tender. Add parsley flakes. Add the noodles to boiling broth and cook until tender (about 20 minutes). Add the chicken soup and cut up chicken.*
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Add milk to pudding mix; beat until turning.
Add Cool Whip. Place graham crackers in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour half of pudding mix over.
Place graham crackers on top to form another layer.
Pour remaining pudding.
Top with graham crackers.
Seal with icing.
Refrigerate for 6 hours.

title: lemon cream sauce
directions: Cook in double boiler until thickened.
When cooled, add cream, if used.
Use over fruit.
Good with bananas, apples, pineapple, grapes, kiwi and nuts.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Crush Oreos.
Melt margarine.
Combine and cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch rectangular pan.
Press softened ice cream into pan. Cover with Cool Whip.
Drizzle with chocolate topping and sprinkle with nuts.
Freeze.
Set out 3 to 5 minutes before serving.
Cut in squares.

title: japanese pie
directions: Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable ball
directions: Chop all vegetables very small and mix together.
Make 1 large or 2 small Vegetable Balls.
Roll in crushed pecans.

title: dinner butter rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; cool milk and add it with egg, salt and sugar, then add flour.
Mix and knead; let rise until double in size.
Roll out in circles.
Brush with melted oleo.
Cut in pre-shaped wedges.
Roll to desired shapes.
Brush with oleo; let rise.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt
butter in pan.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together. Pour in pan over melted butter; do not mix together.
Lay fruit on
top.
Bake
at
350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown. During
the
cooking
process,
the
fruit goes to the bottom and crust rises to the top.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Melt bark in oven at 200° or in a double boiler.
Stir in peanut butter, Rice Krispies and marshmallows.
Drop on wax paper until dry.

title: creamy potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine potatoes, soup mix and cream cheese.
Add eggs.
Turn into buttered 1
1/2-quart baking dish.
Dot with 1 tablespoon of margarine.
Bake 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 8.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cube bread and put in bottom of greased 9 x 14-inch casserole dish.
Break up sausage; fry, drain and crumble over bread.
Beat eggs and add other ingredients; pour into dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next morning for quick breakfast, bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: steak soup
directions: Brown ground beef in Dutch oven over medium heat.
Add onions, carrots, celery and garlic; cook 10 to 12 minutes until vegetables are softened.
Add chicken broth, tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, red pepper sauce and pepper; bring to boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt butter or margarine in small saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring until deep brown.
Whisk into soup; cover and simmer 15 minutes more.
Makes 11 cups.

title: honey orange sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until almost tender.
Peel.
Cut into halves lengthwise and arrange in well-greased shallow baking pan. Melt butter or margarine in saucepan.
Blend in cornstarch and salt.
Add orange juice, a little at a time, stirring constantly. Add honey.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour sauce over potatoes and bake in a moderate oven at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: natalie's famous cookie-pops
directions: You will need 20 to 25 wooden sticks (round edges).

title: tuna potato bake casserole
directions: Prepare potatoes as directed except use 2-quart casserole. Stir in peas and carrots and tuna.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Stir.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese and butter.
Sprinkle over casserole and return to oven.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes longer until tender.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: rice consomme(or baked rice)
directions: Melt oleo in skillet, add chopped onion.
Saute until tender, not browned.
Pour into a 2-quart flat casserole.
Stir in the rice, mushrooms and consomme, mixing well.
Cover tightly with foil, airtight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in margarine.
Add sugar, salt and tomato sauce.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes.
Mix 3 ounces of cream cheese and 1 cup sour cream together.

title: chicken tarragon
directions: Season chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
Brown pieces in butter in frying pan.
Place chicken pieces in microwave casserole. Brown onion rings in frypan used for chicken.
Place onion slices on top of chicken; add mushrooms and juice.
Sprinkle tarragon over chicken.
Cook on High for 10 minutes.
Let rest for 2 minutes. Turn dish.
Cook 5 minutes more on High.
Turn dish again; cook for 5 minutes on High.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix butter and eggs thoroughly.
Add buttermilk and sifted dry ingredients.
Stir until smooth.
Roll out on a lightly floured board to 1/2-inch thickness.
Let set for 20 minutes.
Cut with a floured 2 1/2-inch doughnut cutter.
Drop into a kettle of hot oil.
Turn when they rise to surface, then turn again when they brown.
Drain on an absorbent cloth or paper towels.
Cool.
Dust with either powdered sugar or cinnamon/sugar.

title: peppy pot roast
directions: Brown meat in large heavy pan; pour off fat.
Add soup mix and 1/2 cup water.
Cover; cook over low heat for 3 hours or until tender.
Stir occasionally.
Remove meat from pan.
Gradually blend remaining water into flour; slowly stir into gravy.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Chop first 4 ingredients fine.
Add bacon bits to taste.
Pour 1/4 bottle Viva Italian salad dressing over this or to taste.

title: glazed cheese cake puffs
directions: In a large bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Line muffin pan with paper liners.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in each liner. Fill 3/4 full with mixture. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes (will not be brown).
Cool.
Cover with cherry or blueberry filling.
Chill.
Remove paper liners before serving. Makes 2 dozen.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook lima beans moderately (do not overcook).
Drain and add 1 stick of margarine while beans are still hot.
Add remaining ingredients; top with crushed Ritz crackers and dabs of butter. Bake for about 20 minutes, but do not overcook.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice the apples and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and beaten eggs with a fork. Spread mixture over the apples.
Drizzle the melted oleo over all. Sprinkle with the cinnamon and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Delicious with ice cream or whipped cream on top.

title: cruiser's slaw
directions: Place cabbage in bottom of bowl.
Layer 3-bean salad on cabbage.
Top with chopped vegetables.
Add seasonings as desired (salt, pepper, celery seed).
Pour reserved liquid marinade over all.
Add additional vinaigrette if necessary.
Refrigerate for 2-4 hours.

title: kaye's refrigerator pickles
directions: Take cucumbers, onions and salt; put in a large bowl in water. Let stand for 2 hours.
In gallon jar, mix sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Shake well together, then pack cucumber mixture in jar.

title: farm cookies
directions: Cream the sugars, shortening and eggs.
Sift flour with next 3 ingredients. Add to creamed ingredients, mixing well. Fold in oatmeal, corn flakes, nuts and vanilla.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 minutes at 425°.
Makes 4 dozen large cookies.

title: swiss woods souffle
directions: Distribute bread pieces evenly over bottom of baking dish.
Mix eggs with 1 1/2 cup milk and spices; pour over bread and let stand. Meanwhile brown and drain sausage.
Spread meat over bread. Combine soup, 1/2 cup milk and cheese; spread over sausage.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until brown.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: crystals garden
directions: Place 6 pieces of sponge in shallow bowl.
Place a few pieces of clay pot in bowl.
Put a drop of food coloring on various pieces.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken into beaten egg and water, then dredge through bread crumbs.
Let sit to set the coating.

title: lemon pie plus
directions: Blend all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Chill and serve.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Thaw bread dough (can be put in refrigerator overnight) and place in greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Spread dough in pan.
Spread pie filling over dough.
In a bowl, mix butter, flour and sugar until crumbly.
Sprinkle over filling.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yield: 24 servings.

title: dilly onion rings
directions: Cut onion into slices and put into mixture of sugar, water, vinegar, salt and dried dill seed.
Let set at least 5 hours before serving.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix to stiff batter with sweet milk.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot, deep fat and fry.
Serve with fish.

title: topsy turvy pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a square pan, 8 x 8 x 2. Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in milk, nuts and dates. Spread evenly in prepared pan. Mix water, orange juice, brown sugar and butter in a saucepan. Bring to boil, stirring to blend. Pour over batter in pan. Do not stir. Bake 50 to 55 minutes. Delicious served warm with sauce side up and topped with Cool Whip.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Open can of salmon.
Take bones out of salmon. Add eggs, cracker and onion; mix well.
Make salmon into patties.
Fry in skillet with small amount of oil.
Fry until patties are golden brown.
Makes 6 to 8 patties.

title: philly cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: halibut royale
directions: Lightly brown onion rings.
Place fillets in greased baking pan, on top of onion rings and butter.
Mix lemon juice and eggs together; pour over fish.
Sprinkle with salt and paprika.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in a 400° oven.
Do not turn over; eat and enjoy!

title: pineapple-orange jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Mix fruit with dry jello.
Add mixture to cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix well. Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: In large bowl combine, blend at low speed until crumbly; reserve 1 cup.

title: unbelievable pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend 2 minutes at low speed.
Use 9-inch pie plate and grease with margarine and sprinkle with flour.
Pour batter into pie plate.
Make sure oven rack is in middle slot.
This pie makes its own crust and the coconut comes to the top and browns.
Serve hot with whipped cream or cold.
Turn off heat and cool in oven 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, margarine and flavoring.
Mix sugar and flour together, then add to mixture and blend well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured pie pans.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients and let stand for 20 to 30 minutes.
Beat eggs slightly; beat in oil and vanilla.
Add apple mixture and dry ingredients alternately.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° (preheated) for 30 to 40 minutes.
For bars, bake in larger pan.
When cooled, top with following frosting.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar and egg.
Blend in flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cover and chill.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 3-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
With fork, dipped in flour, flatten in crisscross pattern to 2-inches.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set, but not hard.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies, if using self-rising flour, omit soda, baking powder and salt.

title: turtle cake
directions: Pour half the cake batter into prepared 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: avery butter sauce(for meat, poultry, vegetables or fish)
directions: Melt the butter or margarine; stir in salt, mustard, paprika, water, juice and Tabasco sauce.
Makes about 1/3 cup.

title: great tortilla filling or stew
directions: Place all
ingredients in crock-pot; cook until meat is very tender.
Serve inside flour tortilla, or eat as stew.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Season with salt, pepper and garlic salt. Serve with favorite crackers.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their skins until tender.
Drain well, peel and break up into small chunks with a wooden spoon.
In a skillet, saute onions
and
bacon
until browned.
Remove from heat and stir
in
the
remaining ingredients.
Pour over warm potatoes. Mix well and serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread dough over your lightly greased pizza pan and bake until light brown according to directions on package.
While dough is baking, prepare glaze.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Mix and spread over cooled cookie dough.
Now get your favorite fruit mixtures such as sliced kiwi, strawberry, peaches, fruit cocktail, bananas or any fruit your family likes and arrange on top of the cream cheese.
Put glaze over top of fruit and refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: fettuccini
directions: Melt butter; add garlic and saute.
Beat egg with whipping cream and add.
Whisk until well mixed.
Add the rest of the ingredients, sour cream last.
Do not boil.
Can add cooked shrimp, scallops, etc.
Cook fettuccini and pour sauce over.

title: italian sloppy joes
directions: Brown the hamburger.
Drain the grease, then put the Italian tomato soup and brown sugar and chili powder.
Cook until hot. Taste to see if you need more seasoning.
Then turn the heat down to low and put the cheese on top.
Cover and let the cheese melt. Then put on the buns.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan the lettuce, cucumber, onion, sliced boiled eggs, green pepper and slightly cooked peas.
Mix together mayonnaise, sour cream and original Hidden Valley Ranch dressing and put over other layers.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: kiss cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and vinegar, beating until stiff.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonful onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until tops are firm and very lightly browned.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: old fashioned chicken pie
directions: Lay deboned chicken on the bottom of a casserole dish.
Dice eggs and put on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix soup mix and chicken broth and pour on top of chicken and eggs.
Mix flour, milk and butter and pour on top.
Bake, uncovered, for about an hour.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Work flour, sugar and margarine together into coarse crumbs. Reserve 1 1/2 cups of crumbs.
Mix molasses, boiling water and soda; combine with remaining crumbs.
Mix well.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Sprinkle the 1 1/2 cups of reserved crumbs over the top of the cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Chop onions very fine.
Combine eggs, oil and salt; beat and then add other ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: phyl's sweet potato muffins
directions: Cook and mash sweet potatoes.
Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon together.
Stir well.
Add oil and eggs; stir in sweet potatoes, raisins, chopped nuts and vanilla.	Lightly grease muffin pans, filling about 1/2 full.
Bake approximately 30 minutes for regular size muffins or 12 to 15 minutes for mini-muffin pans at 375°.
Do not overbake.

title: tuna tetrazzini
directions: Break spaghetti into pieces and cook in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Put tuna, pimento, green pepper and chopped onion in casserole.
Mix water and soup and add to tuna mixture.
Add 3/4 cup cheese, the spaghetti and season to taste.
Toss lightly until well mixed and coated with sauces.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for about 45 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Place apricots, pineapple, lemon juice and sugar in blender; blend and put in pan.
Bring to boil.
Add jello.
Put aside and cool.
When cool, add cheese.
Place in refrigerator until liverly.
Take out and whip.
Add Cool Whip and pecans.

title: coach ball's party salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and sweetened milk in large bowl. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well and refrigerate overnight.
Do not attempt to mold.

title: dad's special
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in soup, milk and seasonings.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer half of the noodles, meat and cheese.
Repeat layers of noodles and meat.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese. Continue baking until melted.

title: french toast
directions: Combine egg and vanilla.
Add bread.
Allow to absorb as much egg as possible.
Place in heated nonstick skillet that has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Cook until brown.

title: tom's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together; knead a little like bread.
Put into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer, if necessary.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine cake mix, melted margarine and 1/3 cup milk.
Press half of mixture in pan and bake 6 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Melt 1/3 cup milk and caramels over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and 1 cup nuts over cake.
Spread caramels over chips and nuts.
Drop remainder of cake mixture on caramels.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: coconut-squash bread
directions: Beat oil, eggs and squash together.
Sift next 6 ingredients together; stir in pudding mixture and add nuts.
Add to pumpkin mixture; mix until well moistened.
Place batter in well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until bread tests done.

title: oatmeal-apricot-hazelnut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat with mixer at medium speed until well blended.
Combine 1 1/2 cups flour with baking soda and salt. Stir into creamed mixture with a spoon.
Stir in oats and hazelnuts.
Toss apricots with remaining 1 tablespoon flour.
Stir into dough.
Stir in vanilla milk chips.

title: peppery hot wings
directions: Heat oil (2-3 inches) in deep fryer.
Fry wings, 4-6 at a time, turning occasionally, until golden brown and done, 8-10 minutes.
Drain.
Keep warm in 275°F oven while frying remaining wings.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Prepare jello according to package directions except substitute buttermilk for cold water.
Stir in remaining ingredients and chill in refrigerator until firm.

title: diane's chocolate pie
directions: Mix together to make crust.
Bake at 300° to 325° for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: hot fruit casserole(a lot, keeps well)
directions: Drain all the fruit.
Cut pineapple slices in halves, also peaches if they are extra large.
Arrange fruit in alternate layers in large, medium-deep casserole dish.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry hamburger well and drain.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Bake another 30 minutes.
Makes large casserole.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients in a large saucepan until onions become transparent.
Add next 6 ingredients and heat to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Add cilantro and simmer 5 minutes.
To serve, place 2 tablespoons crumbled chips in individual bowls.
Ladle in soup and top with a heaping tablespoon Monterey Jack cheese.

title: fairy gingerbread
directions: Cream sugar and butter in a bowl.
Beat eggs, then add eggs, milk and molasses.
Sift flour, soda and ginger into mixture and beat well.
Bake in shallow greased pan in moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes.

title: deluxe cornbread *
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend in sour cream, oil and corn.
Blend cornmeal, salt and baking powder.
Add to first mixture.
Blend well and pour into oiled 8-inch square pan.
Bake in 375° oven 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit punch bars
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light at high speed.
Add fruit cocktail and juice, flour, salt, soda and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed.
Spread on large cookie sheet.
Batter will be thin. Sprinkle with nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Cut pancetta or bacon into 1/4-inch strips.
Lightly crush garlic.
In a saucepan, cook garlic in oil and margarine until garlic turns deep gold.
(Discard garlic.)
Add bacon and cook until it begins to crisp.
Add wine and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
In large serving bowl, lightly beat eggs.
Stir in grated cheeses, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and parsley.
Cook spaghetti in boiling water with 2 or 3 tablespoons salt until just done (firm to the bite).
Drain.
Add to serving bowl and toss well. Reheat bacon quickly over high heat and pour entire contents of pan over the spaghetti.
Toss again and serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: tomato relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan, then cook for 1 hour, stirring often.
Put in jars and seal.

title: mango ice cream
directions: Heat sugar, 1/3 cup water and cream of tartar in small saucepan to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Cool to lukewarm. Pare mango. Remove pit. Place mango in blender and puree until smooth. Place in medium size bowl. Stir in sugar syrup, lime juice and peel into pureed mango. Fold in whipped cream. Freeze ice cream in ice cream maker according to manufacturer's directions. Makes about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add taco seasoning and mix well.
Add beans, tomato sauce and 1 can water.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.

title: a bushel of christmas cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat liquids and mix together.
Chill 1 hour, then roll out.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except for the cheese and sour cream. After this is well blended, add sour cream.
Pour into Pyrex dish and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Spread cheese on top and bake 10 more minutes.

title: peach fuzz
directions: Put ingredients into blender.
Fill container with ice cubes and blend well.

title: banana-peanut butter bread
directions: Puree bananas in blender; combine bananas, egg whites, brown sugar and peanut butter in a bowl and beat until well blended. Combine flour, oats, baking powder, baking soda and salt, then add to banana mixture.
Mix just until moistened and pour into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan which has been coated with cooking spray.
Let stand for 15 minutes, then bake at 350° for 40 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Turn out on rack and cool completely before slicing.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions in skillet; drain.
Add soups and sour cream.
Mix well.
Place in casserole dish.
Cut the 10 biscuits in halves and place on top of meat mixture.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are brown.

title: butterscotch rolls (pull aparts)
directions: Spray Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans with Pam.
Put rolls in pan in layers.
May add raisins, if desired.
Bring to boil the butter, brown sugar and pudding mix.
Pour over rolls.
Let set overnight in refrigerator to rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: avocado dip
directions: Peel core and mash avocado, add mix according to package, add tomatoes. Cool for 2 hours serve and enjoy.

title: grilled honey mustard chicken
directions: Mix ingredients, brush top of chicken with 1/2 of the salad dressing mixture. Place chicken on grill.
Grill for 15 to 20 minutes, brush with remaining mixture and turn.
Continue grilling 15 to 20 minutes more or until chicken is done.

title: dad's new york cheese cake
directions: You will need a table-top Mixmaster and a 10-inch spring-form pan.

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine jello, sugar and water in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve.
Remove from heat and stir in fruit and baby food.
Set aside to cool.
Beat milk and cream cheese until smooth.
Then beat in jello mixture.
Fold in pecans.
Pour in mold and refrigerate until firm.

title: peppered pork roast
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine vinegar, margarine and pepper in a small pan.
Heat until margarine melts.
Brush sauce over the roast.
Roast 1 hour, basting every 15 minutes with additional sauce.
Reduce heat to 250° and continue roasting until meat reaches an interior temperature of 160°.
Let sit 20 minutes before carving.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: In a large kettle, brown the beef.
Add all the remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
This can be frozen.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: chicken and celery salad
directions: Peel and core the apples. Dice the apples and drop pieces into cold water acidulated with 1 tablespoon lemon juice. Combine the cooked chicken and celery. Drain and add apples. Add the minced onion, chopped fresh dill and tarragon or sweet basil. Add pecans. Combine the cream (whipped), Miracle Whip, pepper, salt and lemon juice. Pour over the salad and toss lightly. Correct seasoning with salt to taste. Chill until ready to serve.

title: miracle cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter and sugar; mix well.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Roll dough in 3/4-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a floured fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Allow to cool.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Add garlic salt, soup, water and chili powder.
Let simmer.
