Grease a baking dish and break uncooked spaghetti into smaller pieces and spread evenly in dish. Pour hamburger mixture over spaghetti.
Stir to blend; cover with foil and bake 30 minutes at 350° without stirring.
Remove foil and add cheese (leave a little for the top).
Stir and put rest on top.
Heat another few minutes to melt cheese.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Mix all together; let rise 2 times before rolling out.
Make as you like for sweet rolls with butter, brown sugar, nuts, etc. Let rise a little while.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: ann's stuffed pizza
directions: Brown hamburg, onion, Romano cheese, garlic, salt, pepper and olive oil.
While browning, defrost spinach in microwave.
Squeeze out water.
Add to ingredients in browning skillet.
Saute until well mixed.
Place Boboli on cookie sheet.
Put all ingredients on top.
Add second Boboli and bake for 25 minutes until crispy to touch.
Good as main dish or appetizer.

title: oven vegetable dish
directions: Combine first 7
ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Layer green beans on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Add fresh tomatoes on top and bake 1/2 hour more.

title: fried lumpia with sesame seed
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients together.
Wrap in lumpia wrapper. Grease steamer and steam for 10 minutes.
Rub with egg whites and sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Cool.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: corned beef sandwich
directions: Tear corned beef apart with a fork.
Add all ingredients. Beat until smooth with mixer and spread on bread.
Good toasted in oven and served with pickle strips.

title: sour cream coconut
directions: Bake cake as directed on package.
Makes 2 layers and split. Mix sugar and sour cream.
Add Cool Whip; spread icing between layers and on top.
Cover with coconut.
You may mix coconut in icing.

title: cashew chicken casserole
directions: Roll chicken in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in margarine for 15 minutes.
Add soup and milk.
Add 1/3 can of chow mein noodles and 1/2 cup of cashews.
Pour into baking dish and top with rest of noodles and cashews.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over rice, if desired.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into baking dish.

title: venison jerky
directions: Mix ingredients and marinate meat in it for 12 hours.
Put meat on a rack in a shallow baking dish.
Heat oven to 150° and bake meat for 10 to 12 hours, until dry.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Home is where you can be silent and still be heard...

title: puppy chow
directions: In microwave, melt butter, chips and peanut butter; stir.
Add cereal.
Pour into large Ziploc bag containing sugar; shake.

title: ranch style bean casserole
directions: Saute onion and ground beef until brown.
Add 1 can diced Ro-Tel tomatoes; add 1 can cream of chicken soup and 1 can Ranch Style beans (not drained).
Butter casserole dish and line with torn up flour tortillas.
Cover with meat sauce.
Make layers and top with shredded sharp Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: no-bake choco-crunch cookies
directions: Melt chocolate, honey and salt in a saucepan over very low heat.
Stir in vanilla, cereal and apple.
Drop mixture by heaping tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper-lined baking sheet.
Firm in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage and cheese together; add Bisquick along and knead well.
Bake at 375° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Beat eggs well in a separate bowl.
Add sugar and then Wesson oil.
Add flour mixture and flavoring.
Last, fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in a large, greased pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. Drain pinto beans. Crush 1/2 of Doritos. Mix all ingredients together, except lettuce and 1/2 of Doritos. Mix well, then add 1/2 head lettuce in bite size pieces. Mix again, then garnish with remaining Doritos.

title: party dill pickle slices
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and onion and spread on one side of bread.
Put pickle on bread and roll up.
Wrap each roll in foil and chill 2 or 3 hours.
Once chilled, unwrap and slice.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put sugar, milk and salt in saucepan.
Cook 10 minutes; take from heat.
Add peanut butter, butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Beat until thick and shiny.
Add vanilla; beat well.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Remove from stove and add flour and nuts.
Spread in a 10 x 13-inch Pyrex.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
(Baking time may vary.)
Cream the cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix chocolate pudding mix, milk, vanilla and brown sugar with mixer until pudding stage (not too thick).
Spread on cream cheese mixture.
Cover with an 8 ounce container Cool Whip.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions; put into bowl.
Cover with brine made from 5 cups water and 1/3 cup salt; soak for 24 hours. Drain.
Combine cucumbers and onions with remaining ingredients. Bring to rolling boil.
Pack into warm jars; seal or keep in the refrigerator.

title: hot rolls
directions: To hot milk, add sugar, shortening, salt, potatoes and eggs. When mixture is lukewarm, add yeast and flour.
Knead well.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.

title: fried cheese
directions: Dip cheese slices into egg yolk mixture, then into flour, coating each side evenly.
Shake off excess flour.
In a 10-inch skillet, heat a 1/4-inch layer of olive oil.
When the oil begins to smoke, add the cheese.
Fry first on one side, then the other. Remove from skillet; squeeze lemon juice on each slice.
Serve immediately.
Allow 2 slices for each person.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix ground beef, rice, milk, onion and salt. Shape into 12 balls. Place in 8 X 8 baking dish. Pour tomato and water mixture over top of meatballs. Cover. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until rice shows plainly on the outside.

title: santa's whiskers(cookies)
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add milk, vanilla and flour.
Stir in pecans, cherries and the 3/4 cup coconut by hand.

title: masters wings
directions: Place wings in large rectangular pan.
Mix rest of items and pour over wings to cover.
Bake 2 hours at 350° or until ends of wings start to darken.
Do not double up; make one pan at a time. These wings are a hit for company so prepare plenty.

title: angel squares
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add
whole
egg
and yolk. Beat thoroughly and add
teaspoon
vanilla
and
the
dry ingredients:
flour, salt, nuts and baking powder.
Spread the mixture 1/4-inch thick in a greased pan.
Beat egg white until stiff.
Add brown sugar
gradually and add 1/4 teaspoon vanilla. Spread over mixture and
bake
minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: honeyed chicken (yola)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in shallow 3-quart baking dish over low heat.
Stir in honey, mustard, salt and curry powder. Roll chicken pieces in mixture and arrange in single layer.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: avocado dip
directions: Peel the avocado; remove seed.
Puree the avocado in a blender.
Add cream cheese and sour cream; mix well.
Add garlic powder, salt, pepper and celery salt.
Process until well mixed. Spoon into a serving dish.
Top with onion, green pepper, tomato, olives and cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips..

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place potatoes in a greased 9 X13 pan, season with salt and pepper.
In a bowl, combine onions, soup and sour cream.
Pour over top of hash browns.
Sprinkle with cheese and pour melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini crescent pie
directions: In skillet, cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender. Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In large bowl, blend eggs and cheese.
Stir in vegetable mixture.
Separate crescent rolls into triangles.
Place in ungreased 10-inch pie plate; press over bottom and sides to form crust.
Spread crust with mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture into crust and bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk and fold in Cool Whip.
Then, layer in pan with crackers, bananas and pudding.
Top with extra Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Squeeze juice from crab meat.
Mix 1/4 can of crab meat with cream cheese.
Add a little grated onion/onion flakes or garlic salt.
Add rest of crab meat to cocktail sauce and mix.
Pour over cheese ball.

title: buttermilk chicken dinner(microwave)
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, combine water, bouillon granules, thyme, rosemary and bay leaves.
Rinse chicken.
Pat dry.
Place chicken, breast side down, in casserole.
Cook, covered, on 100% power (High) for 10 minutes.
Turn chicken over.
If using new potatoes, peel a strip around the centers.
Arrange potatoes, onions and carrots around chicken.
Cook, covered, on 50% power (Medium) for 30 to 40 minutes or until drumsticks move easily in the sockets and vegetables are tender, giving dish a half-turn and rearranging vegetables once.
Transfer chicken and vegetables to a platter.
Keep warm.
Skim fat from pan juices.
Remove bay leaves.
Measure 1 cup pan juices into a 4-cup glass measure. Combine the buttermilk and flour.
Stir into measure.
Cook on High, uncovered, for 3 to 4 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Sprinkle chicken with paprika.
Spoon some of the gravy over meat and vegetables.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix
frozen
vegetables, soup and sour cream.
Place in casserole
dish.
Add cubed Velveeta cheese and top with onion rings.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken noodle casserole(kid pleaser)
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl.
Put in 13 x 12 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: beefy cheese ball
directions: Shred beef in blender.
Save 1/2 cup of shredded beef.
With large spoon, blend cream cheese, onion and remaining beef.
Shape into 2 large balls.
Roll in 1/2 cup beef.
Chill.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients until moist.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on top of bubbling stew, etc.
Cover tightly. Cook for 12 to 15 minutes. Do not lift cover while cooking.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons of butter; transfer to greased 9-inch square baking dish. Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water. In a saucepan, melt remaining 4 tablespoons butter; blend in flour. Slowly add half and half, salt, pepper and bouillon, cooking until smooth. Pour over mushrooms. Mix cheese and crumbs; spread over mushrooms. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: yummy s'mores
directions: Place cracker square on paper towel.
Top with chocolate and marshmallow.
Microwave 15 to 20 seconds on High.
Top with other graham cracker and allow to stand for 1 minute for chocolate to melt.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter until soft and gradually cream in the sugar.
Add the beaten yolks of eggs and vanilla.
Beat well; sift the flour. Measure and sift with the baking powder.
Add the milk and dry ingredients separately.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in stiffly beaten whites.
Bake in greased tube pan at 375° for 50 minutes, then turn to 325° for 15 more minutes.

title: kolacky
directions: Soften the yeast in sour cream, add flour and egg yolk.
Add butter and mix.
Divide dough in half and roll out each portion on a slightly floured board to 1/8 inch thick.
Cut into rounds or squares and put on a greased cookie sheet.
Make a dent in the center of each one with thumb.
Place 1 teaspoon of filling in center (apricot or cherry can be used).
Bake in 350° oven for about 15 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: deviled stuffed celery
directions: Combine all ingredients, except celery.
Chill ingredients several hours or overnight to blend flavors.
When ready to serve, wash stalks of celery and cut into 2 to 3-inch lengths. Crisp in ice water.
Drain celery and dry.
Stuff with filling. Makes 20 to 25 pieces.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Boil 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn bake
directions: Put the ingredients in a 9 X 13 X 2 casserole dish at 350 temp. for 40 minutes.

title: orange-coconut balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except coconut.
Shape into balls and roll into coconut.
(Better if sit overnight in refrigerator.)

title: green beans supreme
directions: Cook bacon until crisp in a saucepan.
Remove bacon and crumble.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons bacon drippings until tender.
Blend in soup, milk and green beans.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Top with bacon and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: erma davis' fig preserves
directions: Cook figs and sugar for 2 or 3 minutes.
Add Jell-O and boil for a few minutes longer.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake for 30 minutes at 450°.
Yield enough dressing for a 3 1/2 to 4 pound chicken.

title: coconut crisps
directions: Spread coconut in shallow pan and toast in 325° oven for 2 to 3 minutes.
Cream butter; add sugar and mix.
Add egg and beat, then vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add to butter mixture.
Stir in oats and toasted coconut and pecans. Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until brown on edges.

title: grandmother's pound cake
directions: Preheat oven
to
Grease
and
flour a tube pan. Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Beat in eggs one at
a time.
Add flour in small quantities at a time. Pour batter into
tube
pan.
Bake
45 minutes at 275°, then 1 hour at 300°.

title: mile high biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, cream of tartar and salt. Cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Combine eggs and milk.
Add to flour mixture all at once, stirring just enough to make a soft dough that sticks together.
Turn onto lightly floured surface and knead lightly 15 times.
Roll to 1-inch thickness.
Cut with floured 2-inch cutter and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: no frypan chicken fingers
directions: Place noodles in electric blender or food processor until crumbs form.
Place in a shallow dish. Set aside. Combine buttermilk and next 4 ingredients. Dip chicken strips into buttermilk mixture. Coat with crumbs.
Place on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Turn and bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mom's boston corn chowder
directions: Melt butter; add onion and green pepper.
Saute until onion is slightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Put in a large pot.
Add potatoes, water, salt and pepper.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Switch to a low heat and cook until potatoes are tender.
Add corn, milk and evaporated milk.
Heat, stirring frequently, until chowder bubbles slightly.
Serve immediately.
Garnish each serving with chopped parsley or paprika if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cornflake cookies
directions: Bring sugar and Karo to a boil in large saucepan.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix in cereal.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas.
Sift flour and soda together and add.
Add nuts.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes in 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour in 2 deep pie shells or 3 small shells. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: skid row beef stroganoff
directions: Brown the onion, meat, salt and pepper.
Stir in flour, paprika and soup.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Before serving, add sour cream.
Serve over macaroni or toast.

title: bubble bread
directions: Add 1 cup flour and beat well.
Add 3 cups flour.
Knead and let double in bulk.
Break into small pieces.
Roll in melted oleo, then in 1 cup sugar and the teaspoons cinnamon.
Place in well-greased tube pan.
Add maraschino cherries and nuts amongst the layers.
Dissolve Karo and 1/3 cup sugar.
Pour over before baking.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: white fruitcake(makes 3 loaves)
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and eggs in a bowl.
In another bowl, mix flour, salt and fruit.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Put in three loaf pans or use
7 mini pans. Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.
Less if using mini pans.
Test with a toothpick.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In large kettle combine all ingredients except the last 3. Bring to a boil, cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add macaroni.
Cook 45 minutes more.
Before serving, stir in parsley and cheese.

title: buttermilk puffs
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add oil, buttermilk and egg.

Beat until smooth. Heat enough oil for deep frying and drop dough by spoonfuls into hot oil. Cook until brown. Drain puffs on brown paper bag or paper towels. Ice with thin glaze; shake in powdered sugar or eat plain.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, peanut butter chips and butter in microwave on "HIGH" for 2 minutes.
Stir until smooth, then add vanilla and stir.
Add cereal and stir to coat.
Put powdered sugar into a large paper grocery sack; pour coated cereal into the same sack.
Fold sack down and shake to coat with powdered sugar.

title: sloppy tunas
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Spread the filling on split buns and place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Broil until golden brown and bubbly or bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: gourmet chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix other ingredients well and pour over chicken.
Bake in 275° oven for 3 hours, uncovered.

title: chicken breasts parmesan
directions: Mix tomato sauce, Italian seasoning and garlic salt in a 2 cup measure.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Reduce power to Medium and cook for 5 minutes, stirring once.
Set aside.
Mix corn flake crumbs, 1/4 cup Parmesan and parsley flakes.
Dip chicken in beaten egg, then in crumbs. Place in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover with waxed paper. Microwave at Medium-high until chicken is tender, 9 to 14 minutes, rearranging after half the cooking time.
(Do not turn over.)
Pour sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle Mozzarella and Parmesan over chicken. Microwave at Medium-high until cheese melts and sauce is hot, 2 to 5 1/2 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sourdough doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs and add 1 cup sugar together.
Add starter, buttermilk, lard and dry sifted ingredients.
Mix well.
Turn out dough and knead on a floured board until smooth.
Roll to 1/2 inch thick and cut with 2 3/4-inch doughnut cutter.
Put on a greased cookie sheet and let rise for 30 minutes.
Fry in hot deep fat until golden brown and done.
Roll in sugar.

title: london broil
directions: Salt both sides of flank steak well.
Spread both sides generously with French dressing.
Let steak marinate in refrigerator several hours.
Broil 2-inches under high heat for 5 to 7 minutes each side.
Carve on board having a gravy well, or on a tray or deep platter.
Slice very thin, on a slant across the grain.
Thicken steak juices for gravy; blend in mushrooms, if desired.

title: american chop suey
directions: Mix all together in large pot. Simmer 20 min.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrot mix together. Put in a large bowl.

title: orange cream fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, combine fruit; set aside.
In small bowl, combine dry pudding mix, milk and orange juice.
Beat until blended, 1 or 2 minutes.
Beat in sour cream and fold in fruit. Cover and chill.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat the ingredients well except last 2 (nuts and strawberries) and 2 eggs.
Add eggs, then beat.
Fold in chopped strawberries and chopped nuts.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 375° for 55 minutes.

title: carrot salad(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup juice.
Combine pineapple, carrots, coconut, raisins and sugar.
Mix well.
Combine mayonnaise and reserved pineapple juice.
Beat with wire whisk until smooth.
Pour over carrot mixture and mix well.
Chill.

title: baked vidalia onions
directions: Wash and peel onions.
Cut out approximately half dollar size area at top of onions and 1/4 inch deep into onions.
Place bouillon cube, 1 pat of butter and any preferred seasoning in top. Cover in tent of aluminum foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla together.
Mix well.
Sift flour and baking powder together; stir slowly into mixture.
Chill.

title: low cholesterol ranch style dressing
directions: Mix ingredients in small bowl.
Do not use blender.
Chill 1 hour to allow thickening and flavor development.
Can be used for salads, potato topping, dip or meat sauce.
Has 10 calories and 5 mg cholesterol per tablespoon.

title: pigs in blanket
directions: Cut slit in hot dogs.
Put in a slice of cheese.
Wrap each in 1 crescent roll.
Bake in 350° oven until rolls are golden brown.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Cook noodles. Cut chicken into small pieces.
Drain noodles.
Combine soup and milk.

title: garlic sauce
directions: In a blender or food processor, mince finely the onion and garlic and seasoning.
When minced, add oil and lemon juice. Blend well.
Sauce will turn white in color. Place in bowl and let sit to marinate.
Great with lamb or chicken.

title: jiffy peanut haystacks
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch bits together in a double boiler or microwave.
Add noodles and peanuts to mixture until well combined.
Form little clusters on wax paper and allow to harden in refrigerator.

title: seasoned flour for shake and bake
directions: Mix together and keep in plastic bag or other container.

title: libby's linguine with shrimp
directions: In skillet over medium high heat, saute shallots in oil 4 minutes until soft.
Add tomatoes and 1 tablespoon basil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add cream.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes to thicken.
When hot, toss with pasta and julienned basil.
Makes 2 servings.

title: shrimp soup
directions: Chop or grind shrimp; add to milk.
Place in top of double boiler and cook over hot water for 1/2 hour.
Remove from fire. Add cream, butter, flour, salt and pepper, which have been rubbed to a smooth paste.

title: microwave peanut crispy bars
directions: In 3-quart microproof casserole, melt butter on High for 1 minute.
Add marshmallows and cook, covered, on High for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until soft, stirring once.
Stir in peanut butter until smooth.
Mix in cereal and peanuts.
Press warm mixture into lightly buttered 12 x 7 x 2-inch dish.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: quick chicken breasts
directions: Cut chicken breasts into strips or pieces.
Dredge in flour, then egg and then in bread crumbs.
Brown these in oil.
Slice some mushrooms and onions (to taste).
Simmer chicken, mushrooms, onion, bouillon cubes, water and margarine until done.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Delicious!

title: breakfast danish
directions: Toast bread on one side only.
Mix cheese, 1/2 of the sweetener and vanilla together.
Spread on untoasted side of bread.
Peel and thin slice apple. Arrange in one layer on top of cheese.
Sprinkle with the remainder of sweetener and cinnamon. Cook under broiler until cheese is bubbly and apple is tender. Tastes like apple pie.

title: justin's favorite gingersnap cookies
directions: Combine shortening, 1 cup sugar, 1 beaten egg and molasses. Add flour, cinnamon, ginger, salt and baking soda.
Roll in a ball and dip in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: brian's recipe for hamburgers
directions: Get out the bread.
Take the meat out of the freezer.
Cook the meat for 20 minutes in the microwave.
Put the meat on the bread.
I like the grown-up kind.
Put the salad on the bread. Put the catsup on the bread.
Put the cheese on top.
That's all. Eat it with your mouth.

title: meat loaf wellington
directions: In a bowl, combine 1/4 cup gravy, bread cubes, onion, egg and salt. Crumble beef over mixture and mix well. Press into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour or until meat is no longer pink. Remove loaf from pan. Drain on paper towels. Place on a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Unroll crescent roll dough. Seal perforations. Cover the top and sides of meat loaf with dough. Trim excess. Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until pastry is golden brown. Heat remaining gravy. Serve with meat loaf. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked alaska
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Mix coconut and melted butter.
Press into bottom and up sides of a 9-inch or 10-inch pie plate.
Bake until lightly browned, about 20 to 25 minutes.
If edges get too dark, cover with foil crimped around edges.
Cool shell completely.

title: shrimp victoria
directions: Saute shrimp and onions in margarine for 5 minutes or until shrimp are tender.
Add mushrooms and cook 3 minutes more. Sprinkle in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in sour cream and cook gently for 10 minutes, being careful not to boil.
Serve over rice.

title: strawberry angel cake(may use raspberries instead)
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add defrosted berries.
Chill until partially set.
Whip until fluffy, then fold in whipped cream.
Tear angel food cakes into 1 1/2 to 2-inch pieces.
Put a layer of the torn cake in the bottom of a regular tube pan.
Pour on some of the strawberry mixture; then repeat with cake and with mixture until the pan is filled.
Use a rubber spatula to push into the cake so that the sauce gets around all the cake pieces.
Refrigerate for at least 6 hours.
Unmold and frost with 1 1/2 cups heavy cream, whipped and sweetened to taste with sifted powdered sugar.

title: mexican hot pot
directions: Brown beef and onion until done.
Remove from heat and cut up tamales and add to browned beef and onion.
Mix rest of ingredients holding out 1/4 of the cheese.
Place into a 9 x 13-inch tall sided baking dish and sprinkle the rest of the cheese on top.
Place into a preheated 350° oven and bake for 40 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in 1-quart saucepan over medium-low heat.
Whisk in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring 1 minute.
Gradually whisk in milk.
Cook and stir until sauce is smooth and thickened, 3 to 4 minutes.

title: banana-nut chip bread
directions: In mixing bowl, beat bananas, sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla. Combine dry ingredients; stir into bananas. Fold in chocolate chips and nuts. Pour into 2 greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes, then remove and cool on wire racks.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Empty soup into 13 x 9 casserole dish; add water slowly, stirring until soup is dissolved.
Sprinkle rice and vegetables over soup/water mixture.
Arrange chicken on top of rice and vegetables (it will look odd-laying the chicken in water!)
Bake at 325 degrees until chicken is brown, 1 - 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 - 6.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Place cucumbers in casserole dish. Sprinkle salt over all cucumbers and let stand for 2 hours. Drain. Add sugar and vinegar (chopped onion is optional).
Freeze and serve partially frozen.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, butter and flavoring; add to mixture until a stiff dough is formed.
Roll out very thin and cut to desired size; place on greased baking sheet.
Bake quickly in a moderate oven.

title: 1-2-3-4 basic yellow layer cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk and flavorings, beating after each addition until smooth.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Blend flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; add cornmeal. Blend 2 eggs, milk and oil.
Add corn, cheese and pepper.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt, spices and sugar together. Add the rest to it. Bake 1 hour in 3 (1-pound) coffee cans at 350°. Cans or pans need to be greased and floured.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a bowl, combine mayonnaise, relish, sugar, salt and pepper. Add celery and onions; mix well.
Add broccoli; toss to coat. Chill until serving time.

title: chicken bundles
directions: Pound chicken breasts to flatten.
Place one slice cheese on each breast.
Place 1 slice (halves) bacon on cheese slice. Sprinkle each with 1 tablespoon bread crumbs.
Bring 2 sides of chicken together and secure with wooden pick.
Place, seam side down, in buttered pan and brush each with melted butter.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, until tender.

title: chili sauce
directions: Wash and drain vegetables. Scald, core, peel and chop the tomatoes.
Peel onions. Remove seeds from peppers, chop and measure.
Mix all ingredients except spices and vinegar.
Boil 45 minutes. Add spices (tied in bag). Boil until very thick, then add vinegar and boil until thick as wanted.
Pour boiling hot into jars and seal at once.

title: cherry cake
directions: Do not grease pan.
Put cherry filling in bottom of pan. Spread dry cake mix evenly over top of cherries.
Slice butter over top of cake mix, then spread nuts over top of the whole mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until brown.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli following package directions.
Drain well and reserve liquid.
Melt butter; saute onion until tender.
Add flour to onion; stir until smooth.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until mixture boils.
Add broccoli and 1 cup broccoli liquid.
Season with salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Stir.
If soup is too thick, add more broccoli liquid or milk.

title: kosher dill sweet pickles
directions: Drain pickles and save juice.
Boil sugar, vinegar and water for 5 minutes.
Add pickles and boil 1 minute.
Return to jar.
If not full, add some drained juice.
Refrigerate about 1 week before using.
May add onions, sliced thin, one on bottom and one on top.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add dried onion to taste and coat with a mixture of mayonnaise and Ranch style dressing to taste.
Top the salad with the shredded cheese.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
If necessary, add a little milk for good cornbread consistency.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Slice and place in baking dish. Salt and pepper to taste; pour Ranch dressing on potatoes.	Put cheese and onions on top.
Place bacon bits on top of this.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: 125-year-old walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Mix 1/4 cup flour with nuts.
Sift remaining flour with baking powder.
Add flour and milk to butter mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°. Cool and frost.

title: how to boil water
directions: Fill pan with water; place on burner and leave until water bubbles; turn burner off.

title: broccoli-stuffed cornish hens
directions: Cook broccoli according to the package directions; drain well. Combine with rice, Swiss cheese, butter, salt and pepper.
Rinse birds; pat dry with paper towels.
Lightly salt cavities.
Stuff birds with broccoli stuffing.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 250° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Let cool and remove.

title: cinnamon pudding cake
directions: Combine in saucepan, brown sugar, water and
2 tablespoons margarine.
Bring to a boil and cool.
Cream together 2 tablespoons margarine and 1 cup sugar.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients with 1 cup milk alternately to the creamed mixture.
Spread in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with a few nuts.
Pour brown sugar mix over batter.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Make sure that the pan is high enough as brown sugar mix bubbles up.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: german potage
directions: Slice cabbage.
Chop onion; brown in oleo until wilted.
Add soup (undiluted), caraway seed and sausage.
Cover and simmer for about 10 minutes.

title: eight layer salad
directions: In an oblong glass dish, layer lettuce, celery, green peppers, onions, peas and lettuce again.
"Frost" with dressing; sprinkle with cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add bacon bits before serving.
Serves 10.

title: mammaw's stuffing
directions: Remove crusts from bread and toast in toaster.
Melt butter in large pan and saute onion and celery.
Dip toast into milk and squeeze out excess.
Crumple bread into butter mixture.
Add remaining seasonings and mix well.
Makes enough stuffing for a 4 pound chicken or a turkey.

title: snow cream
directions: Mix together eggs, milk, vanilla and sugar.
Add snow until thick.
Eat very quickly because it does melt.

title: chicken chili
directions: Saute chicken in lightly oiled skillet.
Cook until lightly browned or done.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer about 30 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: In large skillet, melt butter and cook onions over moderate heat, stirring frequently, for 30 minutes. In large saucepan, combine balance of ingredients except the bread and cheese. Bring to the boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour. Toast the bread; place in bowls. Add soup and sprinkle with cheese. Serve with additional cheese, if desired. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cora's brownies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into a greased baking pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy bread ring
directions: Creating your own Ice Cream Shop Pie recipe is fun and easy. Just substitute your favorite add-ins and any flavor Jell-O pudding to the basic recipe and invent a fun flavor of your own.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large frying pan, brown ground beef, onion and green pepper; drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, beans, cumin seed and garlic salt and simmer while preparing pie crust. Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place triangles in ungreased 9-inch pie pan; press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Combine egg and 1 cup cheese; spread over crust.
Spoon hot mixture into crust.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and paprika.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: low-fat strawberry pie
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed.
Set in refrigerator 15 minutes to cool.
Once cool, add fresh strawberries and return to refrigerator for an additional 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Keep refrigerated 4 to 5 hours or until firm.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip.
Add lemonade.
This mixture will thicken.
Pour into baked pie shells.
Let cool.
For a different taste, you may use chocolate flavored graham cracker crust pie shells.

title: black bean and macaroni soup
directions: Wash and pick over beans.
Cover with an inch of water and bring to a rapid boil.
Boil for 2 minutes and turn off heat. Allow to sit, covered, for 1 hour.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add flavorings and stir well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with milk; beat well.
Pour in large greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: champagne punch
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients in blender, then add into punch bowl with remaining ingredients.
Punch has a tendency to creep up on you!

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar.
Boil over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk and cook until it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat, cool, add sugar until spreading consistency.
Spread on cake.

title: cheesy mexican casserole
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, cook ground beef until lightly browned.
Drain off any fat.

Add green onions, salt, flour, chili powder, tomato sauce, beans, evaporated milk and cream cheese cubes. Heat mixture until cheese begins to melt. Cover bottom of buttered 2-quart casserole dish with crushed tortilla chips (reserve some for garnish).
Pour in meat mixture and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes (until meat and cheese bubbles).
Garnish with whole tortilla chips.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Mix jello in 1/2 cup hot boiling water.
Add this to hot rhubarb and mix well.
Add pineapple, pineapple juice and raw apples.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: biscuit-topped italian casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray with cooking spray a 12 x 8-inch (2-quart) baking dish.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion. Drain. Stir in water, pepper, tomato sauce and tomato paste. Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat. Stir in vegetables and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Spoon mixture into baking dish.

title: taco pie
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, layer the whole can of Hormel chili.
Then add the chilies on top.
Slice the cream cheese and lay on top of the chilies.
Add shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly and lightly browned.
Serve with tortilla chips.
(Also may be microwaved in a pinch.)

title: lazy lady's chili rellenos
directions: In a 7 x 11-inch greased casserole, alternate layers of chilies and cheeses, beginning with chilies and ending with cheese.
Beat sour cream with the beaten eggs until smooth.
Pour over chili-cheese mixture and sprinkle generously with paprika. Bake, uncovered, in 350° preheated oven one hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Top should be puffy and golden brown.
Excellent served with ham and spinach.

title: cavatelli
directions: *Add more or less cheese, depending on how "cheesy" you like it!

title: tofu salad delight
directions: Put tofu and ingredients in covered bowl or plastic bag and shake well to coat tofu thoroughly.
Deep fry in olive oil.
Drain and put aside.

title: real egg noodles
directions: Beat egg slightly; add cold water.
Add flour to make a stiff dough.
Divide into 3 parts.
Roll paper thin.
Dry 1 hour or longer.
Roll up like a jelly roll and cut 1/8-inch strip; let dry.

title: spicy cocktail wieners
directions: Heat the mustard and jelly in a saucepan.
Stir or use a wire whisk to mix well.
Add franks and heat through.
Serve hot from a chafing dish, electric skillet, etc.
Spear with toothpicks. (There will be enough mustard/jelly mixture for 2 pounds of franks, if you wish.)

title: rummage pickle
directions: Sprinkle salt over mixture of tomatoes, celery, onions, peppers, cabbage and cucumbers.
Let stand overnight, then drain well.
Cook vinegar, brown sugar, mustard and black pepper until clear, about 1 hour.
Pour over mixture.
Put in jars and seal.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add shortening, buttermilk and mashed bananas.
Beat well and then add buttermilk and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Pour into 2 round 9 x 1 1/2-inch pans or 1 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt Velveeta cheese in microwave.
Put broccoli in pan and boil until tender.
Do not overcook.
Crumble crackers in bottom of pan.
Pour in broccoli.
Pour cheese over broccoli.
Then crumble more crackers on top.
Then pour butter over crackers.
Put in oven.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes or until crackers look brown.

title: whipped frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick.
Cool overnight in a covered bowl in the refrigerator.
Beat margarine.
Add sugar and beat until white.
Add vanilla.
Add flour mixture last.

title: honey walnut spread
directions: In medium bowl, combine cream cheese and honey; mix well. Stir in walnuts.
Cover and refrigerate.
Yields 1 cup.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; season with salt and garlic powder to taste.
Drain tomatoes well, reserving the juice.
Add tomato juice, taco sauce and beans to meat mix.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Layer tomatoes, onion and olives in a large bowl.
Top with meat mixture and cheese.
If you are planning to have leftovers, it is best to serve the lettuce and chips on the side, otherwise layer lettuce, cheese and chips on top.
Serve hot.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, sugar and brown sugar. Add the vanilla. Stir in the remaining ingredients. Form into small balls. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pork chops cherokee style
directions: Dredge chops in flour.
In skillet, melt lard and brown chops on both sides.
Transfer to warm dish.
Drain fat from skillet. Add green pepper, Worcestershire sauce, water, salt, pepper, corn and tomato sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Add chops.
Cover and simmer until chops are tender.

title: french fried franks
directions: Combine.
Beat well.
Dip franks and fry in deep fat, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: shrimp ala marinara
directions: Shell and devein shrimp.
Put in a pan of rice and set aside. Chop scallions.
Cover bottom of skillet with olive oil, heat and add scallions.
Cook until lightly browned.
Mince tomatoes finely and add to skillet.
Add salt and pepper and remaining spices. Add wine.
Cook on low heat until sauce is slightly thickened.
Add shrimp.
Cook shrimp until start to curl.
Add cheese and cook few minutes.
Serve over rice.
Very good with crusty Italian or French bread.
Serves 4.

title: fiesta dip
directions: In skillet, prepare seasoning mix with ground beef and water according to package directions.
Add refried beans and heat 5 minutes.

title: old fashion bread pudding
directions: Measure
into
double
saucepan
brown
sugar.
Butter bread, then
dice
and
sprinkle brown sugar over cubes.
Add raisins. Beat eggs, milk, salt and vanilla.
Pour over bread. Do
not stir. Place over simmering water and cook for 1 hour. The brown sugar will make the sauce.

title: red kool-aid punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in large container and chill.
Add 7-Up at serving time.
(You can pick the flavor that matches the color scheme that you want to follow.)

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and press into a 9-inch pie plate (bottom and sides). Bake in a 425° oven for 15 minutes. Pour off fat. Pour English peas into pie shell. Sprinkle with grated cheese. Boil 1 cup water and add remainder of ingredients (except paprika). Mix thoroughly and cover pie with this potato mixture. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake again for 10 to 15 minutes until potatoes are golden brown.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and cook 10 minutes.

title: potluck smoked sausage
directions: Wrap corn in foil.
Put in bottom of large pan.
Cut potatoes in half.
Add cut-up onion and green pepper.
Add sliced sausage and sliced cabbage.
Cover with water and boil on high until potatoes are done.

title: white chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler over barely simmering water. Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup milk.
Bring remaining milk to boil. In a bowl, gradually combine the melted chocolate and milk.
Add the dissolved gelatin and stir until mixture is smooth and well blended.
Cool the mixture over a bowl of ice water, stirring occasionally, until partially set.
Beat the whipping cream until stiff and refrigerate.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks.
Add the lemon juice.
Beat until stiff.
Carefully fold together whipped cream and egg whites.
Gently add chocolate mixture.
Refrigerate mousse overnight or up to 3 days.

title: christmas ornaments
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll out and use cookie cutters to make shapes or design your own ornament.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Let cool, then paint.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar
until light and fluffy.
Add eggs to butter mixture and mix well.
Combine soda and buttermilk. Peel
bananas
and
pour
buttermilk mixture over them. Mash bananas in buttermilk.
Stir banana mixture into creamed mixture. Combine
baking
powder, salt and flour.
Stir flour mixture and vanilla into creamed mixture.
Pour into a greased 9 x
x 3-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until
done. Cool
slightly;
remove
from
pan
and complete cooling on a wire rack.

title: lobina en papel(bass baked in foil)
directions: Have fish split open to remove center bone.
Brush inside with half the olive oil; sprinkle fish with salt from shaker and ground pepper.
Combine remaining olive oil with remaining ingredients, blending well.
Spread out dressing in center of very large pieces of heavy-duty aluminum foil; place fish in center.
Cover top and bottom with the dressing and seal foil.
Fold over foil; crimp edges to seal securely.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Open foil; fish should be firm to touch when baked.
Will serve 3 or 4 persons.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; bone and set aside.
Saute onion and pepper in 1 tablespoon butter.
Using 1 cup chicken broth, mix with soups and chicken.
In bottom of baking dish, place layer of chips, then chicken and soup mixture on top.
Put crumbled chips and 1 pound grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: chicken 'n dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until tender with salt.
Remove chicken to a pan or platter.
Take one cup broth out for dumplings.
Now add cream of chicken soup and 1 can chicken broth.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut into halves.
Place in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Combine butter, honey, orange juice, salt and flour in saucepan.
Cook until slightly thickened, stirring constantly. Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until done.

title: asian-style grilled beef
directions: Combine soy sauce, sesame oil and brown sugar in a medium baking dish; mix well. Add steak, stirring to coat. Preheat grill or broiler. Cut carrot and green onions into 1 1/2-inch slices. Remove steak from sauce. Reserve sauce.
Thread carrot, green onions and steak onto 6 skewers. Brush kabobs with sauce. Grill or broil, turning once, until steak is browned, about 3 minutes on each side.

title: pear crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Half and core pears; slice about 1/2 inch thick.
Toss with lemon juice.
Combine pears and dried fruit in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish or shallow casserole of similar size. In a medium bowl, mix butter and flour with a fork or your fingers until crumbly.
Mix in rolled oats, brown sugar, nuts and spices.
Sprinkle mixture evenly over fruit and press down lightly.
Bake 20 - 25 minutes until pears are tender.
(Check with the tip of a sharp knife or a pick.)
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream, creme fraiche or whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: marinated stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean the mushrooms and remove stems carefully.
Place in pan and pour entire bottle of Italian dressing on mushrooms.
Marinate in refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix pineapple, water, vanilla, sugar and jello.
Bring to a boil and cool until thick.
Add cheese, nuts and Cool Whip. Refrigerate until set.
Makes a nice molded salad.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Cool and refrigerate overnight. The next day, peel and grate.
Saute onions in butter.
Add sour cream and stir until well mixed.
In a 2 to 3 quart casserole, combine butter-sour cream mixture, potatoes, cheese, salt and pepper.
Toss together lightly.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Allow ice cream to soften.
Spoon over the Ready-Crust.
Cover and freeze until firm, about 3 hours.
Serve pie wedges with topping, whipped cream, cherries and nuts (decorate as desired). Oreo cookie "shells" crushed may be substituted for Ready-Crust.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Mix the crumbs and sugar together and add melted margarine. Press into the bottom of either a 8 or 9-inch spring pan with removable sides.

title: butter brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together. Add eggs and flour and cocoa (mixed together), vanilla and nuts. Mix well. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Good, moist and chewy.

title: terrific taco biscuit
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Arrange 7 biscuits around sides and 3 on bottom of ungreased 9-inch pie pan.
Press biscuits to form crust (biscuits will form scalloped edge around rim of pan).
In large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in beans and seasoning mix.
Reduce heat; simmer for 5 minutes.
Spoon hot mixture into biscuit lined pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 16 minutes or until crust is golden.
Immediately top with cheese, chips, lettuce and tomato.
Allow to cool 5 minutes before cutting into wedges.
Serves 6.

title: potato cake or lumpe
directions: Mix all ingredients together, mixing well.
Take a small portion and roll thin using more white flour as necessary.
Cut in about 8-inch circles and bake on a lefse grill or ungreased frypan.

title: shrimp fajitas
directions: Cut the onion and bell pepper into 1/4-inch strips, the longer the better.
Combine this with half the oil and vinegar with 1 package marinade.
Put into a large Ziploc bag.
Combine shrimp with the other package of marinade and the remaining oil and vinegar.
Put into another large Ziploc bag.
Refrigerate both bags for 24 hours.
Can be frozen for up to 15 days.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Melt shortening in the boiling water.
Add salt and flour. Mix and roll thin; cut into 1/2-inch squares.
Freeze on cookie sheet, using wax paper between layers.
Put into plastic bag; use as needed.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread cake mix in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with butter, cut into 1/4 pats.
Dump cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 250°. Place pretzels in a large shallow baking pan. In a small bowl, combine butter, dip mix, Worcestershire sauce and salt. Pour butter mixture over pretzels; stir well. Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Pour onto waxed paper to cool. Store in airtight container. Yields 6 cups of snack mix.

title: turkey soup
directions: In medium saucepan, combine broth, celery, carrot and potatoes.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add onion, turkey and thyme.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes more or until potatoes are fork-tender.
Adjust seasoning to taste.
Makes 4 cups.

title: garlic shrimp
directions: A crusty Parmesan-breadcrumb topping is dusted over these big garlicky shrimp before serving.
Grill or toast some French bread for sopping up the aromatic juices.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix together until smooth.
Form into 24 small balls and chill.
Press dough into greased and floured small muffin tins.

title: christmas morning rolls
directions: Arrange rolls in greased fluted pan.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over rolls.
Cook remaining ingredients over low heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture bubbles.
Pour over rolls.
Cover tightly with foil.
Let stand overnight on counter top.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except the last three.
Serve on greens with a sprinkling of nuts and paprika.

title: apple cheese crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples (Granny Smith apples are best). Place apples in a shallow baking pan. Pour water and lemon juice over the apples. Mix sugar, cinnamon, flour, shortening, salt and cheese. Sprinkle over apples. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Beat, adding oil and vinegar alternately.
Shake well before using.

title: spread easy casserole
directions: Mix hamburger and onions; spread in baking dish.
Layer soup over this.
Spread the vegetables evenly.
Top with cheese slices. Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: russian tea(great winter drink)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls to 1 cup boiling water.
Store in tightly sealed moistureproof container. (Great for colds, sore throat and flu.)

title: green bean-pea salad
directions: Mix juice from peas, oil, salt, sugar and vinegar.
Heat mixture, then allow to cool.
Mix green beans, peas, pimentos, celery, onion and pepper in a bowl.
Pour cooled liquid mixture over vegetables and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Drain off liquid before serving.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown meat, garlic, onion, parsley and celery in skillet.
Add stewed tomatoes and sauce.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: twinkie filling
directions: Beat butter, Crisco, granulated sugar, evaporated milk and vanilla.
Beat on high for 10 minutes until light and fluffy.
Use between cake layers.
Especially good if used with chocolate or fudge cake.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Butter 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Combine cut potatoes, 1 teaspoon salt and water to cover in large Dutch oven. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer until tender.
Drain. Return potatoes to pot with broth, butter, sour cream, poultry seasoning and 2 teaspoons salt.
Beat with mixer until smooth. Spread potatoes in baking dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until puffed and heated through.
May add French fried onions before baking.
Makes 16 cups.

title: martian muffins
directions: Split each muffin in half and cover the 6 halves with the spaghetti sauce.
Crumble the cheese and scatter pieces evenly on the halves.
Place 3 pepperoni slices on each muffin half. Preheat oven/toaster oven to 325°.
Place the muffins on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 5 minutes.

title: strawberry cheese trifle
directions: In large bowl, cream together cream cheese and sugar; add sour cream, vanilla and almond extract.
Fold whipped cream into cream cheese mixture.
Add cake pieces; set aside.
Combine strawberries, sugar and almond extract.
Layer together in large bowl, starting with strawberries, then adding cake mixture. Continue layering; finish with strawberries.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Chill well.
Yields 24 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add beaten eggs, flour, salt, vanilla and syrup.
Stir well.
Add pecans, pour into 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Double recipe makes 3 pies.

title: cheese cake
directions: Make sure cream cheese is soft (leave at room temperature for about 1 hour before preparation).
Blend cream cheese and sugar first, then add other ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes and 250° for 1 hour.
Serve chilled with fruit topping.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda; set aside.
Mash bananas; add lemon juice to top of mixture, then add sugar, shortening and eggs.
Mix, then add sifted flour mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel onion.
Chop onion and celery. Cut cheese into cubes.
Mix onion, celery, tuna and cheese in a bowl.
Add mayonnaise.
Mix all ingredients with a spoon.
Put 1/2 hamburger rolls on cookie sheet.
Put tuna mixture on rolls. Cover with foil and bake for 15 minutes.

title: shrimp salad supreme
directions: Slice head of lettuce into bite size pieces.
Place in a large salad bowl.
Add other ingredients, including cheese, mushrooms, celery, broccoli, cauliflower, cherry tomatoes and pepperoni.
Mix well.

title: vegetable bisque soup
directions: In large deep saucepan, cook carrots, celery, onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Add chicken broth.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Blend 1/2 cup milk with flour.
Add remaining 2 2/3 cups milk to broth and bring to boil.
Add flour mixture.
Heat, stirring until thickened.
Reduce heat; add cheese.
Blend in egg yolk and vegetables.
Heat; do not boil.
Sprinkle with parsley. Serves 8.
Good with toasted Jarlsberg Loaf.

title: christmas cheese
directions: Grind first five ingredients.
Cream Velveeta, cream cheese, powdered onion and salt into ground ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into logs and roll in 1/2 paprika and 1/2 chili powder mixture. Wrap logs in plastic wrap.
Keep refrigerated.
Slice and serve on Ritz crackers.

title: amish sugar cookies(over 50 years old)
directions: Combine sugars, oil and Crisco; beat well.
Add eggs and beat again.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: caviar pie
directions: Blend in mixer the cream cheese, onion, Worcestershire, Tabasco, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Place mixture in 9-inch pie plate.
Top cheese with grated eggs, parsley and caviar.
Serve with Melba rounds.

title: stuffed goose neck yellow squash
directions: Wash squash and cook until tender. Cut off top portion of squash so insides of squash can be scooped out. Put insides of squash in a bowl. Saute onion in butter in a frying pan; then add onion to the squash. Add cheese and crushed croutons to taste; mix. Add salt and pepper to taste. Put mixture back into each individual squash. Top with additional crushed croutons and a slab of butter. Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Unroll 1 package of crescent rolls and spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Add 1/2 cup chopped walnuts (if desired). Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
Cool and frost with chocolate frosting.

title: party punch
directions: Chill ingredients overnight.
Combine all except champagne in large punch bowl.
Add 1 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon almond extract. Stir to melt sugar, then slowly add champagne.
Serve.

title: beer rolls
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients until blended.
Spray muffin tins with nonstick spray.
Drop dough by spoonfuls into muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for about 15 or 20 minutes or until browned.

title: exquisite pie
directions: Mix ingredients and put into graham cracker crusts.
Keep chilled.

title: southwest stew
directions: In a Dutch oven with cover, heat oil and saute onions and garlic until light brown.
Put flour in bag; add meat a few pieces at a time and shake to coat.
Add meat to Dutch oven and brown with onions and garlic.
Stir in broth, rosemary, pepper and potatoes. Cover and cook slowly 1 hour.
Mix in peaches, bell pepper, squash, corn, celery tops, mint and cilantro leaves.
Cook an additional 25 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water until done; drain and peel and mash.
Stir in all of remaining ingredients except 2 tablespoons of sugar; turn mixture into prepared 1 1/2-quart size greased casserole dish and sprinkle with remaining sugar.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: st. louis bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together with mixer and pour on top of cake mixture.
Will be thick, so spread with spoon. Sprinkle 1 cup pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set in center.
Cool, cut and sprinkle powdered on top. Serve.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients together for one minute.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and drip by spoonfuls onto waxed paper!

title: peach pizza
directions: Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar with electric mixer until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread over cooled crust.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and water in a saucepan; smooth out lumps in cornstarch.
Heat over medium heat until thickened and jelly-like. Remove from heat.
Stir gelatin into jelly-like mixture.
Cool approximately 3 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In skillet season and brown cut up chicken in 1 tablespoon oil.
Make onion soup as directed on package and add chicken.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let simmer for 1/2 hour or until desired thickness.
Can add onions, green peppers, red peppers, sliced carrots and/or pea pods along with other ingredients.

title: pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl.
Stir in sugar, salt, 3 tablespoons oil and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth. Stir in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up. Cover and let rise in warm place 45 minutes.

title: sun ball(cheese ball)
directions: Beat cream cheese with mustard, garlic pwd.
And wine until smooth.
Beat in olives, cheddar cheese and parsley.
Form into a ball, wrap in wax paper.
Chill.
When chilled roll in sunflower seeds.
Serve with crackers, veggie, or chips and salsa.

title: jam cake
directions: Sift baking powder in flour.
Beat eggs and sugar together until light.
Add butter (well creamed), then the flour, spices, jam and, lastly, the juice. Bake in layer pans.
Put together with icing.
This makes a fine substitute for fruit cake.

title: double chocolate chunk cupcakes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 18 muffin cups.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup.
Level off.
In a large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Blend well.
Add buttermilk, margarine, almond extract and egg; blend just until dry ingredients are moistened. Fold in vanilla, milk chocolate chips and almonds. Fill greased muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 3 minutes.
Remove.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Cook and stir beef in 12-inch skillet until lightly brown; drain.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of cheese, green onion, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Cover and set aside.
Heat remaining ingredients to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered 5 minutes.
Spoon about 1/2 cup beef mixture onto each tortilla; roll tortilla around filling.
Arrange in 2 ungreased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch oblong baking dishes.
Pour sauce over enchiladas. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cook uncovered in 350° oven until bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: jane's blueberry oatmeal muffins(servings:  24)
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Combine eggs, milk and corn syrup.
Mix well.
Add to the dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour batter into greased muffin tins.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen muffins, depending upon size of tin.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until muffins are golden brown.

title: short cut rocky road candy
directions: In a 2 quart saucepan combine butterscotch and chocolate chips with condensed milk.
Heat over medium heat, stirring until chips are melted.
(Be careful; Do not let chocolate burn).
Remove from heat.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Mix sour cream and sugar.
Mix all ingredients together; cover and chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O as indicated on box.
Grind cranberries and oranges (with peels) together.
Add to Jell-O mix.
Mix in applesauce and walnuts.
Refrigerate for several hours until set.

title: sea foam salad
directions: Drain pears and add water to juice to make 1 cup.
Heat.
Cut up cream cheese.
Add hot juice to jello and stir until dissolved. Add cream cheese and stir.
Add pears.
Cool in refrigerator until beginning to set and add container of Cool Whip.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels and butter; put in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°; let cool.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip; pour over cooled crust.
Dissolve Jell-O and add strawberries.
Let chill and pour over Cool Whip mixture; chill again until ready to serve.

title: aeblekage(danish apple cake)
directions: Heat butter and sugar in frying pan; add crumbs.
Brown well, stirring occasionally.
Put crumbs in a casserole in layers, alternating with the applesauce.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream and a dab of red jelly.

title: discovered valley ranch
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients. Store in an airtight container.
To make 1 pint of dressing, combine mayonnaise and buttermilk with 3 1/8 teaspoons dry mix.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Mix all together and shape into egg forms.
Dip in melted chocolate.

title: ole green beans
directions: Saute garlic, green pepper and onion rings in hot oil.
Add tomatoes and seasoning; simmer 15 minutes.
Cook green beans and drain.
Place beans in center or round, flat vegetable serving bowl.
Spoon tomato mixture around beans.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Simmer first 5 ingredients for 45 minutes.
Add oregano. Simmer 15 minutes more.
Slice eggplant in 1/4 to 1/2-inch slices; dip in egg and roll in crumbs.
Place in single layer on nonstick sheet 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Then remove; layer eggplant, sauce and cheese and repeat in casserole dish.
Bake, covered, for 20 minutes; uncovered for 10 minutes more.

title: walnut cheesies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the cheese and margarine with mixer at medium speed.
Add flour and salt, mixing well.
Stir in walnuts.
Roll into marble sized balls; flatten with a fork and bake 12 to 14 minutes until nicely browned on the bottom.
Serve warm.
Makes 30.
Store airtight.

title: cornish hens
directions: Salt hens and place in a large cooking bag.
Put onion and bell pepper over your hens.
Quarter potatoes and lay bacon over this.
Pour cooking sherry over all.
Tie bag and punch holes in bag.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Add sugar gradually, beating constantly.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon about 2-inches apart on well greased or sprayed cookie sheet (vegetable spray).
Bake at 300° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 3 to 4 dozen.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: salmon log
directions: Flake drained salmon with cream cheese.
Add onions, lemon juice, liquid smoke and salt.
Let stand several hours after mixing or refrigerate overnight.
Make into log or ball.
Roll in nuts and parsley mixture.

title: battered fried apple rings
directions: Beat Bisquick, eggs and milk together.
Slice apples.
Coat with mixture.
Cook on griddle until golden brown, turning once. Serve with syrup, jelly or powdered sugar.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix ingredients, batter will be thin.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: dinner in a dish(casserole)
directions: Layer in order given.
Pour over 1 can of beef broth.
Bake in oven 1 hour at 350°.

title: cod stew
directions: Partially thaw fish fillets.
Cut into large chunks.
Saute carrots and potatoes in margarine approximately 5 minutes in heavy pot.
Add remaining vegetables and seasonings. Simmer 3 minutes longer.
Add wine, water and fish.
Ladle into 6 ovenproof bowls and bake in preheated 400° oven for 5 to 8 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions.
Put 1 head of dill and 2 thin slices of onion in each pint jar.
Fill with cucumber slices and shake jar to pack.
To make the syrup, combine vinegar, sugar, salt, celery seed and mustard seed.
Heat to boiling.
Pour over cucumbers and add another head of dill and 1 slice of onion to each jar.
Then adjust screw-on lids at once.
Put in canner (like cold packer).
Boil 5 minutes.

title: hot tomato starter(serves 8)
directions: In a saucepan, combine juice, consomme, onion, horseradish, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat, stirring constantly.
Serve with lemon slices studded with cloves, floating in each cup.

title: tuna bake
directions: Mix in large bowl, tuna, mushroom soup, celery, green pepper, milk and onion.
Boil noodles until done.
Combine ingredients and pour into a greased 10 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: easy cherry tarts
directions: Spoon the cherry pie filling into the pie shell or individual tart shells.
Top with the thawed whipped topping.
Sprinkle with chocolate sprinkles, if desired.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix soda and sugar together.
Mix butter, sugar and egg together.
Add vanilla and flour.
Roll in balls, the size of a big marble.
Mash down with potato masher.
Bake at 375° about 5 to 7 minutes.
Do not grease cookie sheet.

title: no knead rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Place 1 cup boiling water, shortening, salt and sugar in mixing bowl.
When water, add beaten egg and dissolved yeast.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour gradually and beat vigorously after each addition.
When all flour is added, it will have a glossy look.
Add 1 more cup of flour and beat. Cover with lid; keep warm and let stand until light.
Work down and let rise.

title: easy noodle casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown beef with onion and garlic.
Drain well.
Mix in tomatoes, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Mix in zucchini, cook for another 10 minutes.
Blend in noodles.
In 12 x 7-inch baking dish, layer half of meat mixture and half of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water; set aside to cool.
Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks and soda; beat.
Add chocolate and vanilla; beat.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately; fold in stiffly beaten egg whites, coconut and pecans.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: homemade chicken pot pie
directions: Arrange bottom layer pie crust in pie pan.
In saucepan, add cooked chicken, soup, vegetables and onion.
Heat until soup is creamy and pour mixture into pie crust.
Arrange top pie crust. Fork the top of the pie crust for air holes.
Bake 45 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Whip sugar and egg white until fluffy.
Add pecans and stir to coat.
Drop onto greased pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 225°.
May bake individual nuts or in mounds.

title: bread pudding
directions: Grease medium casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients in another mixing bowl except bread cubes and raisins.
Mix until sugar is dissolved.
Add bread cubes and raisins.
Stir until well mixed. Pour into greased baking dish.
Place this dish in a large roasting dish.
Water should be added to the other dish to 1-inch deep.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Serve warm with a basic white glaze.

title: firehouse chili
directions: Brown turkey; drain well.
Put turkey in 5-quart pot.
Add remaining ingredients in order given.
Bring chili to a gentle boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer until done.
Yields 4 quarts of chili, 288 calories per 2-cup serving.

title: easy chicken bake
directions: If using fresh chicken, soak in salt water 1/2 hour to deblood it.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken breasts which have been placed in a greased baking dish.
Bake covered for 1 1/4 hour at 350°.
Remove cover.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: cherry strawberry jello salad
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over jello to dissolve.
Thaw strawberries, mash bananas, drain pineapple (saving juice).
Add half pineapple and other ingredients to jello.
Place in refrigerator to set.
Allow cream cheese to soften at room temperature.
Mix remaining pineapple with cream cheese, adding some juice.
Spread mixture on top of jello.
Refrigerate to set cheese.
Serves 12.

title: chicken and rice(from the files of louella scott williams)
directions: Melt margarine in water in saucepan.
Add rice and soup and mix well.
Add mixture to a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Season chicken with salt, pepper and paprika to taste and lay in dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
(I skin chicken, place meaty side down and turn after 45 minutes.)

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups boiling water; gel until thick, but not firm.
Beat with egg mixer until foamy.
Add cream cheese, pineapple, nuts and Cool Whip.
(Save enough Cool Whip and nuts to put on top.)
Gel until firm, then top with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: chicken-vegetable noodle soup
directions: Heat all ingredients (except noodles) to boiling in 4-quart Dutch oven.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until chicken is done. Skim fat.
Cook noodles.
Remove chicken from broth and cool slightly.
Remove chicken from bones and skin.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Add chicken and noodles to broth and heat until hot. Makes 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Combine cauliflower, potatoes, onion, carrots, bouillon and water.
Bring to a boil and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Add grated cheese and stir until melted.
Add salt and milk.
Heat to serving temperature.
May be thickened with 1 to 2 tablespoons flour, if heavier consistency is preferred.
Serves 8.

title: apricot-cheese salad
directions: Drain and chill fruit, save juice (add orange juice if not enough).
Dissolve jello in hot water, add 1 cup fruit juice. Chill jello until slightly thickened. Add fruit and marshmallows. Place jello in 11 x 7-inch glass pan.
Chill until firm.

title: sweet and sour sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage, eggs and bread crumbs. Shape into teaspoon size balls. Saute in oil until brown. Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients;
pour
over sausage balls and simmer for 30 minutes. Serve hot.
Sausage balls may be refrigerated or frozen in sauce. To serve, heat at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields about 6 dozen.

title: seafood risotto
directions: Slowly add the ingredients and cook until absorbed.
Add 2 tablespoons brandy or cognac.
Add seafood to rice mixture.
Stir in remaining 1/4 cup olive oil.
Serves 4.

title: foil stew
directions: 1. Place patties on heavy duty broiling foil. Add raw potato (sliced), carrot and onion slices, salt and
pepper. Fold foil around edges together to lock on ends
and lengthwise.
2. On a grill cook the foil, meat side down for about
15-20 minutes. Using hotgloves flip foil package over seam side down. Cook 10-15 minutes. Serve by opening
foil pack and using pack as a plate.

title: low calorie vegetable soup
directions: Cut up broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, zucchini and yellow squash.
Place all vegetables in large stock pot.
Fill pot with water, covering vegetables completely and seasonings and broth for desired taste.
Let simmer for at least 3 hours over low heat. Freezes well.

title: homemade noodles
directions: The amount of flour depends on the size of the egg.
Mix together until mixed but not stiff.
Place on floured surface and roll out thin.
When you think you can't roll it any longer, roll it some more.
Let dry for 10 to 15 minutes.
Roll up into a thin roll and slice.
Spread out on a flat surface to dry several hours.

title: corn quiche
directions: Bake pie crust at 450° for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Reduce oven to 425°.
Combine eggs, heavy cream, salt, pepper, onion and corn. Blend well, then stir in cheese.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tootie bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Partially slice bread into 16 pieces. Cut each slice of cheese diagonally and place 1 triangle of cheese in between each piece of bread.
Place the bread on foil-covered cookie sheet.
Combine margarine, onion, mustard and poppy seed. Mix well and "ice" the bread on tops and sides.
Place small pieces of bacon on top.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Serve hot!

title: chocolate chip jumbles
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together.
Cream the margarine.
Add sugar gradually. Add vanilla and eggs.
Add sour cream, stirring until smooth.
Add flour mixture.
Stir in chips and nutmeats.
Drop from teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in a hot oven at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: judy's apples
directions: Mix apples, pudding mix and sugar.
Put into greased casserole dish.
Dot with butter, and cover with cinnamon bits or sprinkle on cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into loaf pans and bake at 350° until done.

title: herbed chicken souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Cook chicken and dice.
Prepare stuffing according to directions on package; spread in bottom of dish.
Add layer of diced chicken.
Melt butter in saucepan; blend in flour and seasoning.
Stir in broth; cook until thick.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into slightly beaten eggs.
Blend together gradually. Pour over chicken.
Cook at 325° for 45 minutes, or until knife inserted in souffle comes out clean.
Serve with Pimiento-Mushroom Sauce.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in shortening.
Add onion, tomato sauce, catsup, steak sauce, pepper and parsley.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Cook macaroni.
Combine in a baking dish.
Gently spoon mushroom soup into mixture, lightly lifting from bottom.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.

title: make-ahead butterhorns
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add 4 cups flour, milk, shortening, sugar, eggs and salt; beat for 2 minutes or until smooth.
Add enough remaining flour to form a soft dough. Turn onto a floured board; knead lightly.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 2 to 3 hours.
Punch dough down; divide into four equal parts.
Roll each into a 9-inch circle; brush with butter.
Cut each circle into eight pie-shaped wedges; roll up each wedge from wide edge to tip of dough and pinch to seal. Place rolls, tip down, on baking sheets; freeze.
When frozen, place in freezer bags and keep frozen until needed.
To bake, place on greased baking sheets; thaw 5 hours or until doubled in size.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove from baking sheets and serve immediately or cool on wire racks.
Yield:
32 rolls.

title: apple cake
directions: Peel apples and pour 1/2 cup sugar over apples; set aside. Sift flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon; set aside.
Cream oil and 2 cups sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, cream well.
Add vanilla, mix.
Add flour mixture.
Fold in nuts and apples, mix well.
Pour in well-greased and floured large tube pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Turn out, then ice.

title: raisin pound cake
directions: Rinse raisins under hot water; drain well on paper towels, then cut raisins fine with scissors.
Add raisins to about 2 tablespoons of flour (extra); set aside.
Cream the sugar, eggs and butter until very light and fluffy.
Sift flour again with salt and mace, then add to egg mixture, alternating flour and milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Beat on medium speed until well blended.
Add baking powder and lemon; beat well 2 minutes, then mix in raisins by hand until well blended only.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until well browned and tests done.

title: dixie biscuits
directions: Mix potatoes, potato water, cold water, lard, yeast and sugar. Let stand for 2 hours.
Beat egg and salt together and add to mixture.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Grease well on top and put in a cool place.
Make out 2 or 3 hours before baking. The dough will keep several days if kept in a cool place, but don't let freeze.
