Keep well greased on top.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: In a large bowl, mix the cream cheese and milk until smooth. Stir in onion and chicken.
Mix well.
Place 1/4 cup chicken mixture in each roll. Fold edges of roll around filling.
Brush tops of rolls with melted margarine.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: slaw for 50 people
directions: In a small tub (or large bowl) combine cabbage and onion.
In a mixing bowl blend together remaining ingredients.
Drizzle sauce over cabbage mixture and toss to cover.
Store refrigerated until served.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger and marinate tenderloin in it for at least 1 hour.
Dry tenderloin and cover with honey. Roll in sesame seed.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Serves 3.

title: lentil soup
directions: Soak beans overnight; cook according to package directions in large, heavy pot.
Add lemon juice and chili seasoning (included in bean package).
Add canned chili to cooked beans.
Saute onion in vegetable oil; add to pot of beans.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, macaroni and cheese and optionals as desired.
Cook until done, simmering to keep hot until ready to serve.
Blend in mushroom soup.
Adjust seasoning, adding chili powder if desired.
Stir often and add water as necessary while cooking.
One cup of sour cream may be stirred in, or serve topped with a dollop of sour cream.
Freezes well.
Makes up to 20 servings.

title: ice cream crunch
directions: Mix the ingredients (except ice cream) and pour half the mixture into a buttered 9 x 9-inch dish.
Fill with 1/2 gallon ice cream.
Cover with remaining mixture and freeze.

title: polenta(corn meal)
directions: Cook on medium-high.
In a 3-quart pot, put water and salt to taste.
Slowly pour corn meal while stirring.
Keep stirring to prevent lumps to form until very thick.
Lower heat to medium. Let corn meal cook for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour in a 9 x 9-inch glass pan.
Cover with wax paper and let it stand for 15 minutes before serving.

title: mix for a happy day
directions: A little leaven of prayer,

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt, shortening, eggs, potatoes and 4 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn onto floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover tightly. Refrigerate at least 8 hours (can be kept up to 5 days in fridge). Punch down and make rolls.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: meat loaf casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except gravy and vegetables.
Form into a loaf and place into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Pour gravy over the top of the loaf, add vegetables around the sides and bake for an additional 15 minutes.

title: pot roast in foil
directions: Place meat on a large piece of foil.
Spread undiluted cream of mushroom soup over meat and sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Wrap foil sealing with double fold.
Place in a large roaster.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 or 2 hours or until tender.
The soup may be used as gravy.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all together; sprinkle with paprika.

title: italian beef
directions: Place roast in metal baking dish.
Pour French onion soup over roast and sprinkle with Good Seasons dressing.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 45 minutes to an hour per pound.
Remove roast from broth and shred meat.
Put broth in a bowl and place in freezer to allow the grease to gel.
Remove grease from broth and pour over shredded meat.
Makes 6 to 8 sandwiches.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Put chopped onion in melted butter. Blend in flour and 1 teaspoon salt. Add broth.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pastry shell (large).
Bake for 30 minutes at 450°. Freezes well too.

title: microwave potatoes romanoff
directions: Place potatoes and water in 3-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, on full power 20 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Drain and stir in sour cream, cottage cheese, green pepper, garlic, salt and pepper.
Heat on full power 3 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika, if desired.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Put
in crust and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until center is set.

title: green rice
directions: Melt butter and saute onion; mix drained broccoli and 2 cups cooked rice.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz; add onion.
Grease large casserole pan.
Pour mixture in pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin rum raisin sauce
directions: Microwave directions:
In 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine sugar, cornstarch, allspice and cinnamon.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Add pumpkin, water and raisins.
Microwave on High (100%), stirring at 2 minute intervals until thickened.
Stir in rum, butter and vanilla.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Blend flour and shortening together.
Add buttermilk; stir well.
Put dough mixture on a floured surface; knead 2 or 3 times. Cut biscuits with biscuit cutter or a cup.
Place biscuits on a greased pan; put a little melted shortening on top of biscuit. Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Remember, all ovens cook differently.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Saute onion, snow peas and celery in butter.
Combine all ingredients but noodles.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Before baking, sprinkle noodles over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have Cheddar cheese and cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix together well.
Add other ingredients.
Refrigerate mixture overnight or several hours.
Form into 1 large or 2 small balls. Roll in pecans.
Should be stored in covered containers and refrigerated.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: pastelon
directions: Saute ground beef and pork; shake some Adobo as you saute to taste.
Add tomato sauce; simmer.
Add green beans; let simmer. Slice plantains into long strands (5 to 6 each).
In frying pan, brown plantains and set aside.
Beat eggs with a pinch of salt. In a large (lasagna type) pan, pour 1/3 of egg mixture.
Put in microwave for 3 minutes or until a little hard.
Place 1/2 of plantains on top of egg base; cover whole pan.
Add meat mixture on top of plantains.
Add the rest of the plantains, rest of the eggs (make sure to cover the whole pan) and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Spread chicken in baking dish with jelly.
Mix the dry soup mix with dressing.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° until chicken is tender, approximately 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine the above ingredients and bake for one hour in a 300° oven.

title: black walnut chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and shortening with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, rum and vanilla. Remove 2 tablespoons flour from the measured amount before sifting and toss the black walnuts with it.
Sift flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt together.
Add to the egg mixture alternately with the milk, beginning and ending with the dry ingredients.
Fold in floured, chopped nuts.
Line bottom of 9-inch tube pan with waxed paper.
Grease and flour the paper. Pour batter in pan and bake at 325° for
1 1/4 hours or until a toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Let cool in pan before removing.
Makes 20 portions.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt.
Add buttermilk and yeast.
Blend thoroughly and knead. Shape into balls and let rise 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400°for 20 to 30 minutes until brown.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Blend in oil, eggs and pumpkin. Beat well.
Add nuts.
Bake on large greased cookie sheet at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: fried squash fritters
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spoon mixture into deep fat; cook until golden brown.

title: fruit tea
directions: After brewing the tea bags, press all tea out, add sugar to hot tea and mix.
Now, add juices and enough water to make 1 gallon.
Keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Cut each biscuit in quarters.
Wrap each quarter biscuit around a small cube of cheese.
Melt the butter in a baking pan. Roll biscuit bite in butter and leave in pan.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes.

title: bean and beef burritos
directions: Boil roast until tender.
Cool.
Shred meat into large skillet.
Add chilies, beans, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Heat over medium heat until mixture bubbles, stirring frequently.
Warm tortillas in large flat skillet.
Fill with 1 to 2 tablespoons meat filling.
Sprinkle with cheese, onion and hot sauce.
Fold one end of tortilla up towards middle, then fold alternating sides over this.
Serve with Spanish rice and nachos.

title: pork and rice casserole
directions: Spray a casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Put in the rice and layer with green pepper and onion.
Top with pork tenderloin.
Mix the 2 cans of soup with a little water and pour over top of the casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chili rice bake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Brown hamburger meat with chopped celery in skillet. Add cooked rice. Spoon into buttered, shallow casserole dish. Beat eggs together with milk and Chili-O seasoning mix. Pour over rice mixture. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: apple dot slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, apple and celery seeds.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients, blend well.
Pour over slaw; toss well.
Refrigerate before serving, if desired.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: old-fashion egg custard
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Beat egg yolks and egg whites and add to dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Add milk gradually, then add melted butter.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; reduce to 325° and bake 25 to 30 minutes longer.

title: pimento fluff salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mix with 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Add pimento spread and blend well.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine long grain rice, beef consomme, French onion soup and butter in a casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: garden patch primavera
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Drain. Combine cheese and macaroni with melted margarine.
Add vegetables.
Microwave on medium 2 minutes or until cheese melts. Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain all cans and slice water chestnuts.
Alternate in layers, sprinkling with garlic salt, soup and cheese.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and top with onion rings. Return to oven for 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: date zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add next 4 ingredients; mix well.
Add next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Then add last 3 ingredients and stir well.
Pour into two large greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or use four 7 1/2 x 3 3/4 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans for 45 minutes or until done.

title: apple cobbler squares
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together by hand.
Save 1/4 cup of it for the topping.
Add the eggs, milk and vanilla extract. After dough is formed, cut in half.
Roll out like a pie crust. Roll half on bottom and half on top.
Use wax paper, dusted with flour, to roll crust.
Turn wax paper over and put crust into a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Place 2 cans of apple pie filling over bottom crust.
Roll top crust and then sprinkle the reserved 1/4 cup of ingredients for the topping.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until browned.
The last 10 minutes, sprinkle with 1/8 cup of coconut on top.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown meat in fat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover tightly. Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: baked bananas(honey and rum)
directions: Melt the butter in a baking dish.
Peel the bananas and cut them in half lengthwise. Place the bananas in the butter.
Mix the honey and lemon and pour over the bananas.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Add rum and ignite.
Leave "as is" or over ice cream.

title: sausage treats
directions: Heat sausage in fondue pot.
Add relish and barbecue sauce. Heat to serving temperature.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Brown onion and celery. Add meat. Add rest of ingredients. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Crumble noodles on top.

title: borscht
directions: In 3-quarts of water, part of which is one can of beef bouillon, boil bones and soup meat 30 to 40 minutes, skimming occasionally.
Meanwhile, in another pot, soften onion in butter (don't brown); add crushed garlic and shredded cabbage.
Cover and wilt cabbage over low heat (takes about 15 to 20 minutes), stirring occasionally to avoid sticking.
While this is happening, grate together beets and carrots.
After meat is cooked, put the meat, broth, cabbage mixture, beet mixture, bay leaves, chopped celery, tomatoes, tomato paste and wine vinegar in large pot.
Mixture will be thick but don't worry; it will get thinner.
Simmer about 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, heat slowly and serve with fresh dill and sour cream and bread and all good things.
Before serving, cut the meat into bite size pieces and serve with the soup.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix together the cream or half and half, mushroom soup and sherry.
Add the rice, crab meat or lobster, water chestnuts, garlic salt, shrimp, clams and parsley flakes.
Stir together; pour into a 2-quart greased casserole.
Sprinkle paprika and butter or oleo (in bits) on top.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°. Serves 6.

title: orange julius
directions: Fill blender with ice and crush well.
Add ingredients.

title: pat's bread
directions: Combine
flours.
In a large bowl, combine 4 cups flour mixture,
sugar
and
salt;
mix well.
Add 2 more cups flour. Mix thoroughly.
Gradually
add rest of flour.
Dough will be soft and sticky.
Don't knead.
Place in oiled bowl.
Oil top. Cover and
let rise 2 hours, undivided.
Punch down but don't work out yet.
Let rise another hour.
Take out, work a little bit
and shape
into
6 loaves.
Place loaves in greased loaf pans and
let rise
for
1 hour.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake 25 minutes.
Bread will be crusty and firm and sound hollow when tapped.
Butter top, cover and let cool.

title: konbu maki
directions: Soak konbu; cut
into 5-inch pieces.
Cut meat into 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch strips.
Place meat across one end of konbu; roll tightly.
Tie middle with kanpyo which has been washed and cut into 3-inch pieces.
Place in saucepan with other ingredients. Cover and simmer for 2 hours, or until tender.

title: pumpkin dump cake
directions: In
a large mixing bowl combine the pumpkin, eggs, spice, milk and sugar.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix over pumpkin mixture.
Dribble melted margarine over cake mix;
sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: delean's homemade banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Set aside.
Mix milk, egg yolks, salt and vanilla together well.
Then add sugar and flour mixture.
Cook on medium heat, until mixture thickens, stirring continually.
Remove from heat; layer wafers, bananas and pudding mix in a large bowl, beginning with wafers on bottom of bowl.

title: pork pearls
directions: Soak sweet rice in water for 30 minutes.
Season ground lean pork for at least 30 minutes with the soy sauce, rice wine, cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Stir the green onions into the ground lean pork.
Set up a steamer.
Rinse the sweet rice and put it on a plate.
Using a tablespoon, scoop some seasoned pork and roll it in the plate of sweet rice.
Repeat this until all the seasoned pork is used up.
Place the sweet rice coated pork balls into the steamer.
Steam for at least 15 minutes.
Serve with hot rice and other vegetable dishes.
Makes 20 to 30 balls, depending on size. Cooking time 30 minutes.

title: zesty french dressing
directions: Mix with wire whisk in a large bowl and store in the refrigerator in a covered jar.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Cream margarine with sugar. Add yolks of eggs. Beat until mixture is light and airy. Add flour with rest of dry ingredients. Add to first part with
milk. Mix well. Add nuts, vanilla and lemon juice. Whip egg whites. Mix with the batter carefully. Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: caesar salad
directions: Allow egg to come to room temperature.
To coddle egg, place whole egg in small saucepan of boiling water.
Remove from heat and let stand 1 minute.
Cool slightly.

title: broccoli bricks
directions: Peel eggplant and cut the same as French fried potatoes.
Soak in salt water for 1 hour.
Drain.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Dip in beaten egg and then in cracker crumbs.
Place on platter and refrigerate while oil heats up.
Drop into oil, cook until golden brown and drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: sausage stuffing
directions: Combine sausage, celery and onion in skillet.
Saute until sausage is browned and veggies are tender.
Drain well.
Mix with cornbread and remaining ingredients.
Blend well.

title: cheese spread (ball)
directions: Chop beef in blender.
Mix all ingredients.
May form into ball and roll in nuts or serve as a spread.

title: cherry-peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine cherry and peach pie fillings in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in small bowl. Separate each biscuit into 2 sections; dip each section in butter, then in sugar-cinnamon.
Arrange on top of filling.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: grilled potatoes
directions: Place potatoes and water in casserole dish; cover.
Microwave on High 12 to 15 minutes, stirring after 8 minutes.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Stir in potatoes.
Cover.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Drain, reserving mixture.
Arrange potatoes on skewers. Place on grill on medium heat.
Grill 4 minutes.
Rotate and brush mixture.
Grill 4 more minutes.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix; chill in refrigerator until firm.
Shape into a ball. Roll in finely chopped pecans and parsley flakes.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 2-quart mold.
Chill.

title: fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and bring to full boil for 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, chopped nuts and vanilla until well blended.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan and refrigerate until set.
Cut and serve.

title: tacos in pasta shells(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Cook beef in a large skillet over medium-high heat until brown, stirring to separate meat.
Drain fat. Reduce heat to medium-low. Add cream cheese, salt and chili powder.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: play dough 2
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Tear bread into small pieces. Place pieces in a bowl.
Add glue and mix together with fingers. Knead until mixture no longer sticks to fingers and has a smooth texture.

Dough may be mixed ahead of time and stored in the refrigerator in a plastic bag; it will remain usable for weeks. For ease in handling dough, put a small amount of glycerine or hand lotion on fingertips.
Once the project is shaped, allow it to air-dry for two days.
Dried projects may be painted with water based paints, acrylics or oils.
Spray with clear acrylic all over.
Fingernail polish can also be used to paint and seal.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add water, oil, eggs, strawberries and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with Strawberry Frosting.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
with enough buttermilk to make a batter.
Let set for about 1 hour, do not stir again.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil.

title: double corn bread
directions: Mix all
together
and	pour in 8 x 8-inch greased pan. Bake in hot oven (400°) until brown.
We like this better than hush puppies with fish.

title: minute man macaroons
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until tops are golden brown.

title: quick dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and pack in jars with dill.
Mix water, vinegar and salt.
Bring to boiling point and pour over cucumbers.
Seal at once.
A clove of garlic and hot pepper add additional flavor.

title: old fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions and drain.
Add eggs, milk, margarine, salt and pepper.
Pour into a baking dish with cheese mixed into macaroni and layered on top.
Cook in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes until cheese browns and is bubbly.

title: chinese vegetables
directions: Combine vegetable oil, sesame oil and red pepper. Microwave on high 1-2 minutes, or until hot. Add pea pods and bok choy. Toss to coat. Place vegetables on microwave safe plate. Pour over chicken broth evenly. Microwave vegetables for 5-7 minutes or until tender. Let stand for 2 minutes, add mushrooms, sprinkle with soy sauce.

title: microwave dip for vegetables
directions: Put all ingredients in a microwave safe bowl.
Microwave on High 5 minutes; stir well.
Cool.
Serve with vegetables; cucumber, broccoli, carrots, peppers, celery and cauliflower.

title: tiffany erwin's soft tacos
directions: Brown ground beef with seasoning; drain.
Fill all ingredients in shells.
Eat!

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: Bring sugar, water, syrup and salt to a boil.
Add peanuts; cook until cracked.
Take off heat; add soda, vanilla and margarine.
Mix well and pour into buttered pan.

title: fresh tomato barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered for 1 1/2 hours or until thickened.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add cold water to juice to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into Jell-O in a large bowl until dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid.
Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened.
Stir in whipped topping with a wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound.
Stir in pineapple, oranges and marshmallows.
Spoon into 6-cup mold.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.
Makes 10 servings.

title: lemon lemon cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in large bowl and bake in 350° oven for 40-45 minutes. While still hot, prick with fork and add frosting made of the powdered sugar and lemon juice.

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger, chopped celery and onion together in frypan. Mix together rice, soups, soy sauce, water chestnuts, bean sprouts, mushrooms and water.
Add meat mixture.
Place in 2 large casserole dishes. Bake 2 hours in a 300° oven.
The last 10 minutes, add chow mein noodles on top.

title: hotel lafitte muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Bake at 350° in mini muffin pans for 15 minutes or regular muffin pans for 20 minutes.
Dip tops in melted butter and then in cinnamon and sugar mixture (1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon).
Add chopped pecans before baking, if desired. This makes 1 gallon and can be stored in a tight container in the refrigerator for up to 6 weeks, bake as needed.
Don't forget to grease and flour pans.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except chips and cheese.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chips and cheese.
Bake
for
25 minutes at 400°.
Yields 12 servings.

title: radish dip
directions: Mix everything, except radishes and onions.
Then add radishes and onions and chill.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: cocktail sausage
directions: Form sausage into 1 1/2-inch balls and fry.
Drain and marinate overnight in sauce made from the five remaining ingredients.

title: texas delight cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, oleo and pecans; press into a large casserole dish or pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool.

title: fruit salad
directions: Measure the juices and add enough water to make 3 cups.
Cook tapioca in the drained juices.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Let cool, then fold in the fruit.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Tastes like baby fruit dessert!

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine Mexican mix, corn, oil, eggs and salt and pepper to taste.
Bake until done.
Top with cheese and bake until cheese has melted.
Bake at 350°.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken until tender; debone.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 400° until firm.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Add candies to the boiling water and dissolve, then add Jell-O.
Stir.
Add applesauce.
Chill until set.

title: sour cream dumplings
directions: Beat eggs and sour cream, then add flour.
Mix well.
Add cubed bread.
Drop in boiling water by teaspoonfuls and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain and serve with butter.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix cinnamon, sugar and apples and put aside.
Mix remaining ingredients well in large bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Pour 1/2 batter into well-greased tube pan.
Arrange 1/2 apple mixture, then pour rest of batter on top.
Arrange remaining apple mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk for 5 minutes on medium heat; remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, cream and vanilla.
Pour into container and let set.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients until thoroughly moistened, yet still retaining small lumps.
Cook on griddle.

title: old fashioned lemon pie(makes 2)
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Separate eggs; put yolk in dry mixture.
Work in until smooth.
Add milk, butter and extract; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it thickens. Remove from heat; add grated lemons.
Pour in baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Beat egg whites and gradually add sugar, 2 tablespoons for every egg white.
Pile on pie.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly tinged with brown.

title: holiday cheese spread
directions: Cream the cream cheese; add milk and Worcestershire sauce and mix well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix on high speed for 3 minutes.
If too thick for spreading, add milk 1 teaspoon at a time until desired consistency is achieved.

title: pineapple torte
directions: Mix lemon jello, 1 cup sugar and 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Chill jello until set.
Chill can of Pet milk.
Whip milk.
Whip jello. Add pineapple and milk to whipped jello.
Crush the graham crackers.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and 1 stick melted oleo.
Put 1/2 of crumb mixture in a 9
x 13-inch pan.
Pour in filling.
Place remainder of crumbs on top.
Chill.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Separate 1 can crescent dough into 4 rectangles.
Press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup of meat mixture (all of the other ingredients, except 1 tablespoon butter and crushed croutons), into center of each rectangle.
Pull all 4 corners of dough to top center.
Seal all edges.
Brush with 1 tablespoon melted butter; sprinkle with crushed croutons.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with cranberry relish or cran-fruit on top or to the side.

title: turkey-chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken or turkey.
Debone as much as you want for soup. In the broth, which has been salted, cook the carrots and onion until tender.
Combine the milk and the cream of chicken soup; add to vegetables.
Add the cooked noodles to it.
May need to add bouillon cubes for flavor you desire.

title: raspberry angel cake
directions: Mix water and jello.
Add frozen raspberries and whip with beaters.
Fold in whipped cream.
Break angel food cake into small pieces and fold all together.
Pour in square 8-inch pan. Refrigerate until set (about 4 hours).

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Heat 1 inch water in medium pan.
Place 1 inch square (1/2-inch thick) paraffin in custard cup.
Place custard cup in saucepan and continue heating until paraffin is melted.
Place 1 1/2 inches water in bottom of double boiler; heat on high.
In top of double boiler, place chocolate chips, milk chocolate and peanut butter. Stir with metal cooking spoon until smooth.
Avoid getting it up the sides of the pan.
Remove melted paraffin in custard cup with tongs and quickly pour into chocolate mixture; stir.

title: chicken that you cook or something
directions: *Enough to cover dish.

title: plum cake(maybelle edwards')
directions: Mix
oil,
sugar,
eggs, plums, vanilla and food color. Sift the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves and beat into mixture. Stir
in
1 cup of nuts and bake 1 hour at 350° in a tube
pan.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drain off liquid.
Combine grapes, pineapple, nuts and whipping cream. Fold in cranberries.
Spread marshmallows last and fold in evenly. Refrigerate pineapple and grapes before folding in whipped cream.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream
Crisco
and
sugar
until fluffy.
Add egg; beat well. Add applesauce, then sifted dry ingredients; beat until smooth. Fold in raisins and nuts.
Bake in three 9-inch layer pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pat's veggie salad
directions: Garnish with Feta cheese (crumbled) and oil-cured black olives. Combine bulghur wheat, water and salt in bowl; cover and let sit for about 20 minutes until wheat is chewable.
Add lemon juice, garlic and mint; mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours. Add chopped veggies; garnish with Feta and black olives.
Test seasonings.
May need more lemon juice.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Put drippings in a skillet with onions.
Slice okra 1/4 inch thick on top of onions.
Cover and simmer until onion is soft. Slide onions and okra to one side of skillet (to preserve color of okra) and place tomatoes in other half of skillet.
Continue to simmer, covered, until okra is tender.
Fold tomatoes and okra together gently and season to taste.

title: chicken catalina
directions: Combine the first three ingredients in a saucepan; heat and stir until mixed well. Place chicken in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish. Cover with sauce. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yield: 8 servings.

title: chicken barbecue
directions: Cook chicken and save broth.
Break or cut chicken into small pieces.
Fry out onion and pepper in salad oil and stir in chicken broth, tomato sauce, lemon juice, sugar, salt and pepper, horseradish and mustard.
Thicken with flour to desired thickness. Mix in chicken and let simmer at least 1/2 hour.

title: german red cabbage
directions: Place all ingredients except apple cider vinegar and bacon in large saucepan and simmer 15 minutes to tender.
Add vinegar and apple.
Cook another 5 minutes.
Drain, remove bay leaf.
Transfer to serving dish and add bacon crumbs.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Whip egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar gradually.
Fold in crackers, nuts, salt and vanilla.
Spread in greased floured pie tin.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Top with whipped cream. Refrigerate for several hours.

title: potato-onion casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Mushroom soup can be substituted for cream of chicken or celery.

title: apricot glazed chicken
directions: Blend all ingredients except chicken until smooth.
Cook chicken about 45 minutes to an hour before you sauce it.
Then cook another 45 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix together in blender and refrigerate.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Combine pie filling, sour cream, milk, lemon rind and 2 cups of Cool Whip.
Spoon half of filling in pie crust.
Arrange berries on top.
Add remaining filling.
Chill 3 hours in refrigerator.
Add remaining 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip, and, if desired, decorate with more strawberries on top.

title: never fail divinity
directions: Cook first 2 ingredients to soft ball stage, then cook next 3 ingredients to hard ball stage.
Beat egg whites.
Pour first mixture over egg whites.
Beat until smooth and satinlike.
Then slowly add second mixture and beat until creamy and stiff.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Cut in squares when slightly cool.

title: skinny purple cow
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients.
Blend for 1 minute or until smooth.
Makes 2 servings.

title: apple squares
directions: Beat eggs for one minute.
Add sugar gradually.
Then add oil and dry ingredients.
Fold in apples and nuts.

title: green peas salad
directions: Place 4 leaves of lettuce in bottom of dish.
Pour 1 can drained peas over this.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of onion, chopped. Spread with thin layer of mayonnaise.
Repeat with another layer of lettuce, peas, onion and mayonnaise.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Add milk to pineapple juice to make 3 cups.
Blend liquid with vanilla pudding.
Pour over pineapple chunks.
Mix and chill.

title: bean beef casserole
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces and fry.
Stir all ingredients, except cheese, and place in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When baked, add grated cheese over top and bake until melted.

title: egg noodle tuna casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles according to package directions.
Separate tuna into flakes.
Mix with cream of mushroom soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Combine cooked noodles and tuna mixture in baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onions and drain.	Add salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add celery soup.	Mix macaroni and hamburger mixture in a baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Put slices of Velveeta cheese on top and continue baking a few minutes longer or until cheese is melted.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook bone, pot herb, water, onion and salt slowly for 2 hours. Add vegetables and continue cooking
1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pistachio nut cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan or 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 50 minutes in Bundt pan or 35 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: turkey enchiladas with sour cream
directions: Rinse seeds from chiles.
Saute with garlic in 2 tablespoons oil.
Peel and chop tomatoes.
Add onions, 1 teaspoon salt, oregano and 1/2 cup water to chile mixture.
Simmer slowly, uncovered, until thick, about 30 minutes.
Set aside.
Combine turkey with sour cream, cheese and remaining salt.
Heat remaining oil.
Dip tortillas, one at a time, in the hot oil.
Blot with towels.
Fill with turkey
mixture.
Roll up.
Arrange side by side in baking pan.
Pour chili sauce over top.
Bake at 350° until heated through, about 20 minutes.
Can be made ahead of time and put in fridge.
Allow 35 minutes to heat.

title: raspberry patch iced tea
directions: In 2-quart heatproof pitcher, pour boiling water over tea bags. Let set for 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags; add sugar and raspberry drink.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Serve over ice.
Garnish with raspberries and lemon slices.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: grilled portabella melts with basil and tomato
directions: In medium nonmetal bowl, combine first 4 ingredients. Add mushrooms; toss to coat well. Cover; marinate 1 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat evaporated milk, water, eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla. Place the cooked rice and coconut in a 2-quart casserole and pour the mixture over them.
Place the dish in a pan of water.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes. Stir lightly. Continue baking another 30 minutes. Top with another 1/4 cup shredded coconut during the last 7 minutes of baking. Cool before serving.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and 1 cup sugar.
Add molasses and egg.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Mix.
Cover and chill.
Form 1-inch balls and roll in sugar and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: potato bread
directions: Arrange ingredients in bread machine in order given. Start cycle on bread machine.

title: quickie coffee cake
directions: Combine pancake mix, sugar, milk, egg and butter; mix well. Pour into greased 8-inch round pan.
Mix brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake 20 minutes at 375° or until tests done.

title: sauce for cobblers
directions: Mix flour and sugar. Add enough milk to make consistency of pancake batter. Add to water. Cook until thickens (not very thick) and add butter. Especially good with blackberry cobbler.

title: pineapple cheesecake casserole
directions: Mix sugar, flour and juice from pineapple.
Add cheese and pineapple to mixture.
In separate bowl, mix butter and crushed crackers.
Sprinkle on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water (105° to 115°) with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Proof yeast, then add oil, salt and 2 1/2 cups flour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in dish with potatoes and onions all chopped together.
Pour cream of chicken soup, milk and gravy over chicken, potatoes and onions.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Eat and enjoy!

title: best baked fish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onions and celery in oil for 2 minutes until tender.
Mix garlic and parsley.
Spread over flounder fillets in a baking dish.
Cover with chopped tomatoes and lemon or lime slices.
Pour tomato juice over that until it covers bottom of the dish.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dilly bread
directions: Mix and cover.
Let rise in a warm place until double in size (about 1 hour).
Knead and let rise 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until golden brown. Brush with butter and sprinkle with salt. Serve warm.

title: chick 'n bean soup
directions: Heat oil in large Dutch oven over medium heat. Add onion and garlic and saut for 3 minutes. Add broth, tomatoes and picante sauce. Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Sprinkle chicken with cumin and coriander. Add chicken, beans and corn to soup. Cover and simmer at least 15 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: molasses cookies(gingersnaps)
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Add molasses.
Sift flour and spices together and add to egg mixture.
Make balls the size of walnuts and roll in sugar.
Place on greased tin.
Bake at 350° for 16 minutes.

title: easy garden vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 10 1/2-inch pie plate.
Heat 1 inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling. Add broccoli; cover and heat to boiling.
Cook until almost tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, onion, green pepper and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high speed or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown.

title: caramels
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In 4-quart saucepan with candy thermometer in place over medium heat, heat cream, sugar and syrup to boiling.
Stir frequently.
Continue cooking until 234° or soft ball stage.
Gradually add milk; stir constantly until 246°. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour into pan; cool.
Invert pan, cut and wrap.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pork cutlets with mozzarella
directions: Coat cutlets with flour and dip in egg mixture, then in bread crumbs mixed with Parmesan cheese.
Heat butter in skillet and brown cutlets on both sides.
Remove to a casserole dish.
Saute onion, garlic and green pepper in a skillet for about 5 minutes. Add tomato sauce and oregano.
Pour sauce over cutlets, cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove cover, top with cheese and bake until cheese is melted.

title: texas beef squares
directions: Lightly brown onion, green peppers and beef.
Add canned tomatoes, uncooked rice, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour into square baking dish. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry banana loaf
directions: Beat cranberry sauce and apples; fold in bananas, sugar, vanilla, 1/2 nuts and whipped cream.
Freeze until firm and then serve.
Sprinkle remaining nuts on top.

title: no egg chocolate pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch, cocoa and milk.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat and add margarine and flavorings.
Stir well and pour into 9-inch baked pie shell.
Let cool and top with whipped cream.

title: ham-cheese tarts
directions: Blend cream cheese, milk and dry mustard.
Fold in dip and ham.
Halve biscuits.
Mold each half to fit a 1 3/4-inch muffin cup.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon filling into each.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 20.

title: pork and beans
directions: Pour pork and beans in casserole dish.
Place fried sausage on top.
Place in oven for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix to soft dough.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Pat down peaks.
Cook 10 minutes.
Watch carefully.
Remove from oven and brush with melted butter and garlic powder.
Makes 12.

title: jambalaya
directions: Heat oil in large skillet. Add ham and kielbasa.
Heat 7 to 8 minutes.
With slotted spoon, remove from pan.
In same skillet, saute onion, peppers, celery and garlic 5 to 6 minutes until soft. Stir in rest of ingredients and heat to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Add ham and kielbasa. Cover and simmer 4 more minutes, stirring once. Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: crispy sugar nuts
directions: In electric skillet at 325° stir water and sugar till dissolved; add nuts, and cook, stirring, till moisture is gone. Pour onto cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally so that nuts do not burn.

title: mocha macadamia cookies
directions: In
a large bowl, beat together butter and sugars until fluffy.
Dissolve coffee in eggs; beat into butter mixture.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Beat just until well combined.
Heat oven to 350°.
Coarsely chop chocolate.
Place Macadamia nuts in a strainer.
Shake off excess salt.
Stir into dough along with chocolate.
Drop slightly rounded measuring tablespoonfuls of dough 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden and firm in centers.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: broccoli and pasta
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss lightly.
Serve warm.
To make a light version of this, I substitute 1 can of light evaporated milk for the whipping cream.

title: golden corn loaf
directions: Combine corn, milk, egg, onion, salt, pepper and 3/4 cup of the cheese.
Turn into loaf dish (5 x 9-inch).
Toss bread crumbs with the melted butter and remaining 1/4 cup of cheese.
Sprinkle over corn mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Garnish with green pepper rings and pimentos, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked spinach
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package.
Drain well.
Add sour cream and dry onion soup mix, blending well.
Bake in buttered baking dish at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix and roll in chopped nuts and chili powder; chill.

title: cloud dessert
directions: Mix well and put in parfait glasses or pretty small clear bowls.
At serving time, top each with chilled cherry pie filling. Serves 4.

title: flavored oyster crackers
directions: Warm oil and pour over crackers; toss with hands.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Toss altogether until well coated.
Store in covered container.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Slice the zucchini into 1/4-inch or slightly thicker rounds. Beat the egg and milk. Crush corn flakes. Add dash of salt and pepper. Dip zucchini rounds into egg and milk mixture, then into corn flakes. Place on a cookie sheet (spray cookie sheet with cooking spray). Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour. "Delicious."

title: hot pockets
directions: Brown hamburger; add onions and mushrooms and saute.
Add salt, pepper, Hot Pete and liquid smoke to taste.
Drain any fat from mixture in a colander.
Allow to cool.
Flatten out prepared biscuits or cut apart crescent rolls.
Spoon some meat mixture onto the center of biscuit; place a slice of cheese on top; place second biscuit on top and carefully pinch edges together.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until biscuits are light golden brown.
These can be frozen for snacks and lunches.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar, add pudding and milk.
Fold in cool whip and vanilla.
Layer cream mixture and oreos in a large bowl, beginning and ending with oreos.

title: butter crunch candy
directions: Combine sugar, water, corn syrup, butter and 1 3/4 cups nuts. Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until a teaspoon of syrup dropped in cold water forms a brittle mass (285°).
At the end of cooking time, syrup will be thick and amber colored.
Be careful not to let it scorch.
Keep heat low.

title: exquisite crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve cold or bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with cocktail rye bread or crackers.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and 1/4 cup sugar in bowl; mix well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 5 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese and 1 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon over pretzel layer.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in strawberries.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Chill until jello is set.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Beat eggs.
Add salt, milk, sugar, flour and melted shortening.
Put all in blender or electric mixer.
Put margarine in a heavy skillet.
Be sure the pan is real hot.
Add about a 1/3 cup of batter in the skillet.
As soon as it looks cooked, turn and cook on the other side.
It doesn't take long.
Serve with jam or syrup or butter.
Roll up.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain well. In a 2-quart casserole dish, stir together noodles, chicken and green onions.
In a medium bowl, stir together soup, milk, cheese, basil and pepper.
Stir in noodle mixture.

title: chicken spaghetti(servings:  1)
directions: Cook chicken in pan of salted water with a piece of onion and celery until cooked.
Take meat from bones and save liquid (strained).
Saute celery and onion in small amount of margarine until clear.
Add pimiento to this.
Cook spaghetti (broken) in chicken broth for 10 minutes.
Add chicken, onion mixture and remaining ingredients, saving a little cheese for sprinkling on top at serving time.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Cut stew beef into bite-sized pieces. Brown in a little oil with salt and pepper. Then add V8 juice, broth, water, onion, salt, thyme, parsley, bay leaf, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce. Cover and simmer 45 minutes to an hour. Then add frozen veggies, cabbage, potatoes, celery, carrots and barley. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: texas caviar
directions: Drain peas and mash with a fork. Add finely chopped chilies, jar of cheese and garlic powder.
Microwave for approximately 2 minutes.
Add green onions and serve with tortilla chips.

title: cajun corn
directions: Cook bacon and crumble; set aside.
Add onion and pepper on medium heat.
Add tomatoes; simmer 15 minutes.
Add corn, salt, pepper and bacon, then heat.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Wash and pick over cranberries.
Place in saucepan.
Cover with water; cover with lid.
Boil berries 3 or 4 minutes or until skin bursts.
Add sugar; bring to rolling boil.
For sauce, remove from heat; cool.
Refrigerate.
For jelly, boil about 5 minutes, skim and pour in a wet mold.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Add bananas, flour, soda, salt and nuts.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into 10-inch pie plate.
Bake 1/2 to 3/4 hour or until golden brown at 325°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter casserole.
Add apples and pour water and cinnamon, mixed, over.
Work sugar, flour and butter until crumbly; spread over apples.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° until browned and bubbly. Serve warm.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter.
Add eggs and pecans.
Fill unbaked crust with mixture and bake in hot oven 400° for ten minutes.
Reduce heat to moderate 350° and continue baking for 40 minutes, or until done.
Some variations on this are for adding 1/2 cream or 1/4 c. whole milk. The recipe doubles well for 2 pies, but cut back on pecans.

title: mushroom marsala soup
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except the parsley, in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and cook on High for 4 to 7 minutes, or until heated through.
Pour the soup into bowls and sprinkle with parsley.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and flour mixture.
Add water, oatmeal, coconut and candy last.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Cool.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Fry chopped onion in a little oil until light brown.
Add tomato sauce and simmer for 30 minutes; set aside.
Peel and slice eggplant.
Soak slices in 2 quarts of cold water with 2 tablespoons salt for 5 minutes.
Drain and squeeze slices to remove water.
Set aside.
Scramble the eggs, with milk, grated cheese, salt and pepper.

title: caramel chip bars
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl.
Add margarine and mix well. Press half the mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Melt caramels with cream in double boiler, blending well.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on baked layer. Pour caramel mixture over chocolate chips.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over top.
Bake for 15 minutes longer.
Cut into squares when cool. Yields 24 servings.

title: broccoli-cheese potato topper
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine soup, cheese, mustard and black pepper.
Over low heat, heat until cheese is melted, stirring often.
Add broccoli.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve over potatoes.

title: pear blossom cake
directions: Dump
all
but
last 2 ingredients in mixer.
Mix well. Add
3 cups
chopped,
peeled pears and 1 cup chopped pecans. This will be
a
heavy
dough.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Excellent for freezer.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: To Prepare Mix:
In a large mixing bowl, stir together the dry milk powder, sifted powdered sugar and cocoa powder.
Store in a tightly covered container.
Stir before using.

title: holiday shrimp dip
directions: With electric mixer, beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually blend in soup.
Beat just until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients; chill.
Serve with chips and crackers.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Cook chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Mix soup and milk together.
Grate cheese.
Toss crumbs with margarine.
Spray oblong casserole dish with nonstick vegetable spray.
Place in layers the broccoli, chicken, soup, cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: parmesan rounds
directions: Preheat broiler.
Using a 1-inch round cutter, cut 3 to 4 circles from each bread slice.
Butter one side of each circle. Arrange in single layer on baking sheet.
Broil until lightly toasted.
Turn and broil unbuttered side until lightly toasted. Transfer to rack and cool.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat very well all ingredients. Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Bake until silver knife inserted into side of filling comes out clean.
Center may look soft, but it will set later.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 425°.
This recipe yields two pies or 1 deep dish pie.

title: russian tea
directions: Add
spices to water.
Heat to boiling.
Add tea; steep for five
minutes.
Strain.
Heat fruit juices and sugar just to boiling,
stir.
Add
to hot tea mix.
Serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Store leftover tea in tight container and refrigerate. Reheat to serve.

title: rice pudding
directions: Boil water.
Add salt and rice.
Cook approximately 20 minutes, or until water is absorbed.
Add margarine.
With mixer, combine sugar, eggs, milk and flavoring.
Add to rice and butter. Pour into baking dish and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Put chocolate and coffee in a double boiler until melted and smooth.
Let cool.
In separate bowl, beat egg yolks.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Fold in egg whites gently but thoroughly and then fold in the whipped cream.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart bowl and chill for 4 hours.
Garnish top with chocolate curls.

title: chocolate snappers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat about half of the cake mix (dry), the shortening and eggs in large bowl on medium speed until smooth. Stir in remaining cake mix.
For each cookie, place 3 pecan halves, with ends touching in the center, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Place 1 teaspoon dough in center of each group of pecans.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until centers are slightly puffed and edges are set. Cool completely; remove from cookie sheet.
Frost with frosting. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: cold avocado soup
directions: Place the avocado, cream, milk, chicken broth, lime juice and salt and pepper in a blender or the bowl of a food processor; process until smooth.
Chill for at least 2 hours.

title: date nut logs
directions: Melt butter; let cool and add egg.
Add sugar, chopped nuts, Karo syrup and vanilla.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Add Rice Krispies.
Shape into logs.
Roll in coconut.

title: miss peacock's applesauce meat loaf
directions: Combine celery, green pepper, onion, water and broth mixture. Cook until celery is tender.
Pour in mixing bowl.
Add remaining stuff and mix well by hand or spoon.
Divide evenly into loaves and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: dill pickles
directions: Combine first three ingredients and bring to boil.
Pack cukes in jars.
Add mustard seed, garlic salt and dill.
Pour boiling solution over cukes.
Put on lids and place in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
The jars should seal.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Cook, peel and cube potatoes.
Add seasonings.
Add onion and green pepper.
Add cheese, bread and melted butter.
Add enough milk just to moisten.
Combine all ingredients and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with a handful of crumbled corn flakes. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: microwave tuna pasta bake
directions: Place lasagna in 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Cover with water and set aside.
In 1-quart measure, combine onion, oil and flour. Cook on High power 1 minute.
Stir to dissolve flour.
Stir in vegetables and milk.
Cook on High 4 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in lemon juice.
Combine 1 cup Mozzarella, cottage cheese, Parmesan, egg and pepper.
Drain lasagna in same dish.
Layer half each lasagna, vegetables, cheese and tuna.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup Mozzarella.
Cover and cook on High 15 minutes or until hot.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 9 servings.

title: fay's chunky sweet pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and leave whole.
Put in a pan and pour boiling water over pickles, enough to cover pickles.
Repeat boiling water for 3 more days.

title: jiffy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Great for pork or chicken.

title: divinity candy
directions: Boil until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Pour slowly over beaten egg whites.
Beat until it is cool.
Add pecans and flavoring while beating.

title: mexican lasagna ole
directions: Brown beef and drain thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and heat.
Line bottom and sides of a 13 x 9-inch pan with corn tortillas.
Cover with beef mixture and place another layer of tortillas on top.
Mix together cottage cheese, Monterey Jack cheese and egg; pour over tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with grated cheese, black olives, green onions, tomatoes and lettuce.

title: pork over rice
directions: Cut the pork into cubes. Roll in flour; brown in small amount of oil. Push meat to corner of pan and add the celery, green pepper and onion. Fry until tender. Add the catsup, pineapple, mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Cook about 30 minutes at low temperature. Serve over cooked rice.

title: banana bread(diabetic)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Put bananas in bowl; beat.
Add shortening, eggs and sweetener.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients. Mix with spoon.
Pour into loaf pan (grease pan well).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out dry.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer 3 hours.
Crock-pot works well. Freeze some too.

title: cabbage bake casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in small amount of water and drain.
Add soup, put on top Velveeta cheese.
Heat soup and cheese until melted, add seasoned salt (a little).
Put on water chestnuts and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Brown about 1/2 hour in 350° oven.

title: wheat bars
directions: In large bowl cream margarine and sugars.
Add to creamed mixture, 1 egg and beat well.
In small bowl combine flour and oatmeal.
Add this to creamed mixture and mix well.
Spread dough in 9 x 12-inch baking pan (do not grease).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool completely.
Spread topping over cooled oat mixture.

title: raspberry ribbon pie
directions: Red Layer:
Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water; add frozen berries and lemon juice.
Stir until berries thaw.
Chill until partially set.

title: homemade ice cream - vanilla
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, milk, whipping cream and dash of salt.
Warm on stove or microwave until lukewarm.
Remove and add dissolved junket tablets to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Place in freezer and let stand about 15 minutes.
Then freeze with ice and salt until frozen.
If you are making any flavor other than vanilla, adjust sugar.
I add fruit after mixture has been heated but before freezing.

title: swiss mocha coffee
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Store in a sealed container to preserve freshness.
Use 1 to 2 teaspoons of mixture to 1 cup of hot water.

title: corn chip salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add chips and dressing just before serving.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all 6 ingredients well.
Serve with cut up vegetables.

title: glazed chinese style spareribs
directions: Cut ribs.
Place in shallow pan.
Sprinkle the garlic and place salt on them.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: deep south ovenly chicken
directions: Combine Bisquick, seasoning and pecans.
Dip chicken in evaporated milk and roll in flour mixture.
Melt butter in shallow pan and place chicken in pan, leaving 1/2-inch between pieces. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 40 minutes; turn pieces and cook 20 minutes longer.

title: spinach pie
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix drained spinach with Ricotta, onion, salt and pepper and egg.
Line pie plate with 1/2 cheese. Pour spinach mixture into pie plate.
Cover with remaining cheese. Place in oven at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Let set 10 to 15 minutes, then slice like pie.

title: frut dip
directions: Put in blender and whip.
Good with grapes, strawberries, pineapple chunks and apple slices.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in flour, soda and salt. Add bananas and nuts last.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° in greased loaf pan.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: bryon's special snack
directions: You will need 2 paper plates.

title: dump-it cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump in applesauce, then dump in pineapple on top of that.
Spread cake mix on top.
Melt oleo and pour over the cake mix.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° or until golden brown.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: fish casserole
directions: Mix butter, flour, salt, pepper and milk.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Stir in cheese, reserving 1/4 cup for topping.
Stir in onion and pimentos.
Alternate layers of potatoes, fish and sauce in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until top is brown.
Serves 6.

title: vodka rigatoni
directions: Cook all ingredients, except the cream and noodles, in a covered pan for 30 minutes.
Add cream and bring just to a boil and toss with the noodles.

title: small meatballs
directions: Combine hamburger, onion soup mix and crackers; make very small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients; beat and then add baked meatballs.

title: kolacky
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in vanilla extract.
Combine flour and salt; add in fourths to butter mixture, blending well after each addition.
Chill dough until easy to handle.
Roll dough to 3/8-inch thick on a floured surface.
Cut out 2-inch circles or other shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make a "thumbprint" about 1/4-inch deep in each.
Fill with jam.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until delicately browned on edges.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Beat together.
Store in freezer.
To use, put 3 tablespoons mixture in mug; add 1 jigger rum.
Fill with boiling water and top with whipped cream.
Enjoy! (Cinnamon stick optional.)

title: christmas pickles
directions: Drain the dill pickles.
Slice if they are whole.
Place back in jar; put in sugar, celery seed, chopped onion, horseradish and vinegar.
Shake.
Put in refrigerator.
Shake everyday for 3 to 5 days.

title: grandma riegel's fudge cake
directions: Cream the butter; add sugar and egg.
Dissolve cocoa in boiling water and cool.
Add to first mixture alternately with milk and flour that has been sifted with baking powder.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Cut marshmallows in half (or use miniatures).
Cover top of hot cake with marshmallows and return to oven for 3 minutes.
Frost with Cocoa Frosting.

title: apple butter bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix in flour, baking powder, sugar, spices and salt.
Make a well in center and add egg, butter, apple butter, milk and cider.
Mix quickly.
Add drained raisins.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan, ring mold or Bundt pan.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: finger licking good finger paint
directions: Make pudding according to package directions; allow time to set.
Add several drops of food coloring.
Use freezer paper, wax side down, so it doesn't soak through.
Make plenty.
It has a way of disappearing.

title: roast pork loin("slow cooker recipe")
directions: Place uncooked meat in a slow cooker.
Layer brown sugar, onions, and sauerkraut which has been washed and drained well over the meat.
Pour tomato juice on top of food.
Cook all day on low in slow cooker.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Put sliced apples in 8 by 12 in. baking dish.
Combine sugar, spices and 1/4 tsp. salt. Sprinkle over apples, mixing lightly. Dot with butter. Sift flour and salt, cut in shortening until pcs. are size of sm. peas.
Add milk and then roll crust to size of pan.
Place on top of apples and brush pastry with cream and cut slits to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 450° for 15 min., then at 350° for 45 min.

title: schlishkas
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Add eggs when potatoes cool, then add flour.
Place dough on a floured board.
Roll it out to 1/2 to 1-inch diameter.
Cut into 1-inch piece.
Put into boiling water for 10 minutes.

title: creole style okra with shrimp
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Add okra and cook until crisp.
Add tomatoes and oregano.
Cook, covered, for 15 minutes over low heat.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Add shrimp and cook for 10 minutes.

title: asparagus divan
directions: In a 9-inch pie plate, arrange asparagus and chicken.
Combine soup and milk; pour over chicken mixture.
Add bread crumbs to top; sprinkle with margarine.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbling.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugars and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel the apples and slice into buttered 9 x 9-inch casserole or baking dish.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar and cinnamon to suit your taste.
Combine butter, flour and brown sugar (crumbly, do not overwork).
Spread on top of apples.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) about 30 minutes or until apples are soft and crumbs are nice and brown.
Serve with cream, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: ten minute texas chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain excess fat.
In large pot mix beef, tomatoes, kidney beans, chili mix, chopped onion and chopped green pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stirring occasionally.
Simmer as long as you like.
Serve and top with cheese.

title: champagne mustard
directions: Blend all ingredients, except butter, in blender for 2 minutes.
Cook in double boiler, stirring constantly, until thick. Add butter and stir well.
Cool mixture and store in refrigerator.

title: half moon cookies
directions: Combine shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool, then frost as desired.

title: ham casserole
directions: Add milk to soup to make a smooth sauce.
Blend in sour cream; add rest of ingredients.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.

title: potato salad
directions: Add potatoes to boiling water and cook about 8 minutes.
Put in strainer and rinse with cold water.
Drain well.

title: creamy zucchini soup
directions: My dad packing the saddle bags for the trip to the mountains. They had to be balanced so we could lift them, judging weight, adjusting and readjusting until the loads were equal.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Save the broth.
Saute onion and shrimp until the shrimp turn pink.
Add all ingredients to chicken broth.
Add 1 package Oak Grove gumbo mix, salt and pepper to taste and okra.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes.

title: hot fudge pie
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate. Mix eggs and next 4 ingredients.
Add cooled chocolate mixture and pour into an uncooked crust. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Don't overcook! Serve with ice cream.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Grate cheese. Slice hot dogs down the middle.
Stuff with grated cheese and roll in a crescent roll.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serves 8 to 16.
Quick and easy dinner.
Kelly Eason just loved Pigs in a Blanket!

title: dolly's vegetable soup
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Bring V-8 juice and water to a boil. Add other ingredients.
Reduce heat and cook for about 30 to 40 minutes to blend flavors.
Do not overcook.
Vegetables should remain firm.

title: plum cake
directions: Use butter that has softened at room temperature or place it in a bowl that was rinsed with very hot water so it will soften. Add 1/2 cup sugar and 1 egg.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Add second egg and beat until light.

title: crazy mixed up cake(contains no milk or eggs.)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix well with fork the salad oil, vinegar, vanilla and water.
Add the dry ingredients and blend well.
Bake in an 8-inch square greased pan at 350° for about 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mama's biscuits
directions: Put liquid into bowl.
Stir in flour until sticky.
Put on dough board.
Add more flour until you can roll out dough for biscuits.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: sauces for cakes or puddings
directions: Mix these ingredients well.

title: elephant stew
directions: Chop elephant into bite size chunks (this will take about 3 weeks).
Generously salt and pepper.
Add water and simmer in large kettle over open fire for four months.
Continue to add water as necessary.
This will feed about 3,000 people.
If more are expected, you may add 2 large rabbits, but do so with caution as most people do not like to find hare in their stew.

title: luscious lumps(3 dozen)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add cornstarch and beat until blended.
Add vanilla.
Add flour and combine until mixed.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown around edges.

title: cool cucumber pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. While pasta is cooking, mix your dressing in a separate bowl.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Add cheese, onion, mayonnaise, cream of mushroom soup and pimentos with juice.
Mix well.
Put into a dish.
Mix Ritz and butter.
Spread over top of dish.
Bake 30 minutes.
You can make overnight.

title: cornbread-mushroom dressing
directions: Melt the butter in a skillet over medium heat.
Add the onion, celery and mushrooms; saute about 7 minutes.
In a large mixing bowl, combine vegetables with stuffing mix, cornbread, chilies, pecans, seasonings and egg substitute.
Mix well with your hands. Add 1 cup or so of chicken stock as needed to moisten the dressing.

title: anginetti cream puffs
directions: Slice cookies in half and hold aside.
Drain pineapple leaving a little juice.
Mix whipped topping and cream cheese together in a bowl for about 1 minute at medium speed.
Add Crushed pineapple and blend all 3 ingredients for about 1 minute at low speed.
Drop filling from tablespoon onto the bottom layers of cookies and then replace the tops.
Refrigerate puffs until ready to serve.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and then mix with cake mix.
Use enough flour to make stiff as dough should be for rolls.
Put in warm place.
Let raise for about an hour.
Roll out and pour melted butter over and then spread cinnamon and sugar mixture. Roll and cut for cinnamon rolls.
Let raise in warm place until doubled 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Drizzle with powdered sugar thin icing.

title: cheese-rice-zucchini
directions: Cook onion in small amount of oil until tender; add zucchini and cook until slightly tender.
In a small casserole dish, layer 1/2 of rice, then 1/2 of soup, 1/2 zucchini mixture and 1/2 of the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Mix cornstarch with cold milk until smooth.
Add salt, pepper and margarine.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat.
Boil 1 minute.
Place ham in bottom of casserole dish.
Top with potatoes and cheese.
Pour white sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: swedish cake
directions: Soften cream cheese and margarine.
Cream.
Add confectioners sugar, vanilla and walnuts.

title: apple chunkies(brownies)
directions: Melt butter; remove from heat and stir in sugar.
Boil.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Spread in greased 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no bake jiffy candy cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal, coconut, pecans and cocoa in large bowl.
Mix sugar, milk, margarine and vanilla in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and let boil slowly for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and pour over dry mixture.
Stir.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: loganberry tapioca
directions: Mix tapioca, sugar, salt, loganberry
juice and water.
Stir well and cook over direct heat, stirring constantly, until it reaches a full, rolling boil.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice.
Cool and chill before serving.
It becomes much thicker when cold.
Serve with top milk or cream.
Makes 5 servings.

title: cocktail rye rounds
directions: Brown pork and beef separately.
Mix together with cheese in pan until cheese melts.
Add oregano and Worcestershire sauce. Spread on rye and freeze immediately.

title: e-z banana bread
directions: Mix all together and bake in 1 loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: marshmallow frosting no cook
directions: Beat the egg whites and salt until foamy.
Gradually beat in the corn syrup a little at a time, continue to beat until it holds firm peaks.
Fold in the vanilla.
Tint with food coloring if desired.
Makes enough to frost 2 x 9-inch layers or 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix instant pudding as directed on box, then add the rest of ingredients and mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: homemade pimiento cheese
directions: Grate the cheese and stir in the cut up pimientos.
Add the onion and enough hot water to mix everything.
Stir in mayonnaise to spreading consistency and add Tabasco to taste.
Delicious as pimiento sandwiches or to fill celery stalks.

title: peachie chicken
directions: Clean chicken, prepare chicken, salt and brush with butter or oleo.
Bake in uncovered baking dish for 30 minutes in 350° oven. Blend mixture and pour over chicken, place chicken back in oven for another 30 minutes.
Put peaches and sweet onions on for 15 minutes more.
Total baking time is 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: turkey lasagna
directions: *Defrosted and squeezed dry.

title: pineapple chiffon pie
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O in boiling water.
Let cool.
Cream cheese, pineapple and sugar; slowly add Jell-O mixture.
Chill in refrigerator until it starts to set.
Put condensed milk in a bowl into freezer.
When it starts to freeze, whip like whipping cream. Add lemon juice.
Fold in cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with crushed graham crackers.
Makes two large pies.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Blend mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into prebaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife blade comes out clean.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 400.
Put butter in dish and melt in oven. In a blender add sugar and eggs, blend.
Add milk, corn and salt. Blend all together for about 20 seconds.
Pour in dish with melted butter.
Cover and bake for 40 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Combine bacon and onion in large saucepan.
Cook until bacon is crisp and onion tender.
Blend in flour; cook 1 minute without browning.
Add 2 cups water, potatoes, sage and bay leaf.
Cover and cook until potato is tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Remove bay leaf.
Add creamer, 1 cup boiling water, cheese, corn and seasonings.
Heat until boiling and cheese melts.

title: heavenly hash cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cocoa; add one egg at a time.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and slowly add flour until blended.
Mix in pecans.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Warm marshmallows in microwave or double boiler and spread on cooled cookies.

title: snickerdoodles(cookies; serves 18 large)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into balls (walnut size). Roll into 2 teaspoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon (mixed together).
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Defrost strawberries.
Mix flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar.
Make a well.
Pour in beaten eggs, strawberries and oil.
Mix until dampened.
Scrape the batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Make small balls and pat around cherries, leaving stems.
Freeze on wax paper for 2 hours.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in a double boiler.
Dip cherries. Let cool.
Makes about 100.

title: rice pudding (with custard top)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bring water to boil.
Stir in rice and salt.
Cover and simmer until all water is absorbed, about 30 minutes.
Add milk and boil gently, stirring occasionally, until mixture thickens slightly, about 5 minutes.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In medium bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese with butter.
Add vanilla until creamy.
Add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Spread on cool cake and sprinkle nuts on top.

title: cheese corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except cornmeal and oil.
Stir well.
Add cornmeal mix until just blended; set aside.

title: popsicles
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid and jello in 2 cups hot water.
Then add sugar, then 2 cups cold water.

title: creamy corn chowder(preparation time:  25 minutes)
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan.
Stir in onion, celery and carrot; saute over medium heat until soft but not brown.
Add flour, stirring to combine.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Place corn (even if still frozen) in food processor or blender.
Process until pureed.
Add to saucepan.
Add milk, salt (if used), pepper and thyme, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat; simmer, covered, for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not boil.
Serve soup steaming hot, topped with grated carrots or chopped parsley, if used.

title: mom's hot dish
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Rinse and drain.
Brown meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
May add cubed cheese in hot dish.
Put all in large casserole.
Add enough tomato juice to moisten.
Bake, covered, at 375° to 400° about 1/2 hour.
Reduce heat to 350° for another 1/2 hour.
Cover with cheese and bake until browned.
Do not overcook noodles.

title: beaver tail soup
directions: Place the beaver tail in the oven and heat at 350° until the skin puffs and peels.
Remove the tail and boil it in lightly salted water until the meat falls away from the bone.
Discard the bone and cut the meat into cubes.
Return the meat to the stock, add the carrots, potatoes, celery and onion.
Add pepper to taste, garlic powder and bay leaf.
Simmer gently until the carrots are tender.

title: pepperoni-pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain. Add vegetables, pepperoni, seasoning and croutons. Pour salad dressing over this and toss to coat well.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt 1/4 pound oleo.
Add thawed potatoes and mix.
Mix sour cream, onions, soup and cheese.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix in pot. Put in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining oleo with corn flakes and spread over pan.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 14 to 16.

title: fabulous fudge
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in double boiler.
Mix rest of ingredients (milk, sugar, egg and vanilla) on medium speed of mixer.
Pour in chocolate mixture and blend again until smooth (medium speed). Pour into buttered dish, put in refrigerator and let cool.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter the potatoes. Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a bag.
Moisten potatoes with water and shake a few pieces at a time in the bag, coating them well.
In flat uncovered pan, place melted margarine and potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Turn potatoes after 30 minutes.

title: barbecued beef brisket
directions: Pierce the brisket with a fork repeatedly; pour about 1/2 to 3/4 of the bottle of liquid smoke over it.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, saving 1 can tomato sauce.
Roll into balls; sear in skillet.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top. Cover.
Cook until done all the way through.

title: 6 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: condensed milk
directions: Put warm water in bowl; stir in milk, the sugar last.

title: mandarin orange salad
