directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add sherbet and blend.
Add oranges.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.
Cut mayonnaise with reserved liquid and use as dressing.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: play dough
directions: Add any color food coloring before cooking over medium heat for 3 minutes or until hardens.
Knead a ball on wax paper.
Store in airtight container.

title: pickle snacks
directions: Dry pickles; spread cream cheese on dried beef.
Roll around a pickle, forming a log.
Allow to chill 2 hours to overnight.
Slice and serve.

title: onion puffs
directions: Soften cheese with just enough milk to spreading consistency. Add mayonnaise, onion and seasoning.
Cut bread in circles, about the size of a silver dollar.
Spread mixture on bread, then spread another round of bread and place on top of first round. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yields 75 puffs.

title: clam dip
directions: Fry bacon.
Saute garlic, onion, celery and green pepper.
Add flour, clams, crackers and hot sauce.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Mix sugar and flour together.
Add yolks and rest of ingredients to flour mixture.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Put in crust and top with meringue.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Cook noodles.
Mix all together and heat until bubbly.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except the green beans.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add green beans and continue simmering 15 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: funny face cookies
directions: Allow both crust pouches to stand at room temperature for 15 to 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 450°.
In small bowl, lightly beat egg white and almond extract; set aside.
Cut dough rounds from crusts with floured 2 1/2-inch round cookie cutter.
(Reserve dough scraps.)
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Brush with egg white mixture; sprinkle with sugar.
Make funny faces with desired candy topping and reserved dough scraps.
Brush dough scraps with egg white mixture and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 450° for 5 to 7 minutes or until light golden brown. Immediately remove from cookie sheets.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: home baked beans
directions: When I
cook pinto beans, I add a can of Ro-Tel tomatoes (canned Mexican tomatoes with chilies).

title: cheddar-bacon potato topping
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve over baked potatoes.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Form into a ball and then roll in crushed pecans.

title: veggie pizza appetizer
directions: Unroll crescent rolls, press into cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix together Miracle Whip, cream cheese, dill and onion powder or chives.
Spread over baked crescent rolls.

title: traditional sugar cookies
directions: Mix
thoroughly, shortening, sugar, eggs and flavoring. Blend in	flour,	baking	powder and salt.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.

title: old fashioned lemonade
directions: Boil sugar and water in small saucepan, 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice.
Cool, then pour into jar and refrigerate.

title: tropical dogs
directions: Chop hot dogs into bite size pieces.
Drain juice off pineapple.
Couple a piece of hot dog and a chunk of pineapple on each toothpick.
Place in baking dish with barbecue sauce.
Bake until warm in 350° oven.

title: chicken fajita pizzas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place tortillas on cookie sheet and sprinkle with Velveeta.
Bake 4 to 5 minutes or until Velveeta is melted.
Toss chicken with salsa and spread on tortillas.
Toss bell pepper with remaining Velveeta and sprinkle with chicken mixture.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated and Velveeta is melted.
Top with remaining ingredients.

title: cream of wheat dumpling soup
directions: Boil water, add bouillon and soup greens.
Melt margarine. Add Cream of Wheat and eggs to margarine and mix thoroughly.
Dip teaspoon in cup of cold water.
Drop teaspoons of Cream of Wheat mixture into boiling water, dipping teaspoon in cold water before forming next dumpling.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and pour half of mixture into slightly greased hot iron skillet.
Add cheese, then remaining batter.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
May serve as spoon bread. The green chilies are the green Mexican type, not the hot ones.

title: puppy chow
directions: Combine first three ingredients; pour over cereal.
Shake in bag with powdered sugar until coated.

title: wild rice party dish
directions: Combine all ingredients, except broth, in frying pan.
Cook until rice is coated.
Place in casserole with chicken broth. Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: praline pie
directions: In mixing bowl, blend all ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.
(Pie may have appearance of being undercooked and not firm.)
Cool at least 1 hour before cutting.
Never refrigerate. Garnish with chocolate chips or pecans.

title: kraft cheese balls
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Form into medium balls and bake 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Really delicious.

title: tex-mex cheese dip
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onions and butter over medium heat until onions become clear. Add both cheeses and stir until melted. Add green chile peppers
and heat through. Serve warm.

title: greek salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, toss together the torn mixed greens, tomato, cucumber, onion, olives, Feta cheese and radishes.
Cover; chill until serving time, up to 2 hours.
Just before serving, shake Greek vinaigrette to mix.
Pour dressing over salad; toss gently to coat.
If desired, sprinkle with fresh oregano and chive blossoms.

title: spinach artichoke dip
directions: Defrost and drain spinach well.
Drain artichoke hearts and chop up.
Drain green chilies.
Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into Pyrex dish and place under broiler until top is golden brown or in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve with Wheat Thins.
Yields 10 servings.

title: potato and cheese casserole
directions: Boil potatoes; chill, then peel and cut into cubes. Mix remaining ingredients. Add to potatoes. Let stand in refrigerator overnight. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend flour and shortening.
Mix egg, water and salt together. Work into flour mixture.
Store in refrigerator or roll into 3 crusts and use or store in freezer.
Yield: 3 crusts.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add egg and extract, mix well. Sift flour, soda and cream of tartar together.
Mix well with the first mixture.
Chill dough thoroughly, then form into small ball and place on slightly greased cookie sheet and press ball flat. Cook 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown at 350°.

title: open-face apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until done.

title: elsie's rice and shrimp salad
directions: Mix in advance so rice gets moist.

title: parslied-wine sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine onion and wine.
Cook until wine is reduced by half.
Remove from heat and stir in 3 tablespoons margarine, 1 tablespoon parsley, a dash of salt and a dash of pepper.
Serve over steak.

title: low calorie cheese dip appetizer
directions: In a small bowl with fork, stir cottage cheese with milk until smooth.
Stir in green onions, pimento and salt.
Cover and refrigerate.
Prepare dippers and refrigerate.

title: chicken-rice skillet casserole
directions: Sprinkle chicken with paprika, salt and pepper and lightly flour.
Brown slightly in oleo and oil.
Add rice and brown 5 minutes more.
Add broth and carrots.
Cover with tight fitting lid.
Simmer gently for 20 minutes or until liquid is mostly absorbed.
Add broccoli, cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in medium-size bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
In another bowl, combine sour cream with mayonnaise and taco seasoning.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Melt oleo and Cheez Whiz.
Fold into drained vegetables.
Put in casserole.
Cover with Ritz cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° until light brown and bubbly.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel eggplant and cut lengthwise into 1/2-inch slices.
Mix bread crumbs, cheeses and black pepper.
Mix yoghurt, Italian herbs, garlic powder and salt.
Dip eggplant slices into yoghurt mixture and then into bread crumb mixture to completely cover eggplant.
Hold aside remaining bread crumbs for later use.
Heat olive oil in frying pan.
Fry eggplant until both sides are brown. Remove onto flat surface and blot with paper towels.
Place eggplant into baking dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Cover with pasta sauce and grated Mozzarella cheese.
If necessary add another layer, ending with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve with pasta.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Mix together in punch bowl.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Cook chicken breasts; cut up.
Cook broccoli and separate and drain.
Put into buttered oblong baking dish.
Add cut up chicken.

title: creamy potato casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet; drain.
While ground beef is browning, microwave potatoes 3 to 5 minutes to soften, then slice in rounds.

title: buttermilk orange shakes
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend on high speed until smooth.
Makes 2 servings.

title: new york cheesecake
directions: In bowl, combine cream cheese and sugar; beat until creamy. Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each.
Add flour, vanilla and sour cream.
Beat; sprinkle in cinnamon or nutmeg.
Butter and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nutmeg or cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Leave in oven with door open 1 hour or until cooled.
Refrigerate.

title: vegetable  casserole
directions: In a casserole dish mix the above and Bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: biscuits
directions: You mix it all together and put it in the oven and let them cook at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: curried pumpkin seeds
directions: In a saucepan, mix curry powder, water, garlic and salt.
When well blended, add 1 cup water and heat until liquid simmers.
Add pumpkin seeds and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Remove stems from fresh spinach, wash well and pat dry.
Break into bite size pieces.
Combine spinach, sprouts and onion. Chill, covered, for 4 hours.
Mix vinegar, oil and catsup well. Toss with spinach.
Arrange on salad plates, add bacon crumbs and egg slices.

title: potato rosettes
directions: With Cream:
Peel and cut into slices (lengthwise) some fine cucumbers.
Boil them until soft; salt to taste.
Serve with delicate cream sauce.

title: easy peach or strawberry cobbler(you can use any fruit)
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar with sliced fruit.
Set oven at 350°.
Put butter or margarine in heavy baking dish and set in oven to melt. Stir together 1/2 cup sugar, flour and milk.
Pour this batter over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Put sugared fruit on top of batter; do not stir.
Bake in moderate oven for 1 hour.
The batter will rise to top and be brown and crisp.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream, if desired.

title: ima's chocolate icing (old fashioned)
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar; add milk.
Stir until dissolved.
Put on stove.
When mixture comes to a boil, cover pot and boil hard for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter.
Beat until cooled.
Spread on cake.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Combine 1 cup of the cereal with all the raisins.
Pour boiling water over them and set aside to cool.
Combine sugar and oil in a very large bowl.
Stir in molasses, eggs, milk and remaining cereal one at a time.
Mix together the flour, baking soda and salt and add this to the batter.
Add cooled raisin and bran mixture.
Batter is now ready for use or can be refrigerated for future use.
Store in quart jars up to 2 months.
Recipe can be doubled.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pans, 2/3 full. Bake in 400° oven exactly 20 minutes.
Allow to cool slightly in pan before removing.

title: slow cooker chicken
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in bottom of slow cooker.
Add chicken pieces.
Mix next 4 ingredients together and pour over chicken and vegetables.
Cover.
Cook medium-high for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serves 4.

title: beef brisket
directions: Line baking pan with foil (enough foil to wrap and seal brisket inside).

title: granny's hot chicken salad
directions: Mix in a casserole dish and top with crushed potato chips. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown meat according to taco seasoning directions.
Put 1/2 meat mixture into bottom of casserole dish or electric skillet. Then add 1/2 onions, 1/2 cheese and 1/2 olives (sliced) and then do layers again.
Heat until cheese melts.
Eat with chips.

title: president nixon's favorite meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine beef and pork in large bowl or have butcher grind them together.
Add onion, salt and pepper and enough tomato sauce to moisten meat.
Form into a loaf.
Place in baking dish.
Decorate with bacon and pour remaining tomato sauce over top.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours until well done.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bacon cheese biscuits
directions: Mix baking soda and buttermilk; stir and set aside.
Cook bacon, then drain and crumble.
Shred the cheese if you did not get the shredded pack.
Combine the flour and sugar.
Cut in the shortening to resemble coarse meal.
Add buttermilk mixture, then add the cheese and bacon.
Knead with hands and roll out.
(I use my hands, unless I want it fancy for a special time.)
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken-a-la-king
directions: Boil chicken and reserve 1 cup chicken stock.
Bone and chop chicken; set aside.
In heavy pan, melt butter; add flour.
Stir until mixed and bubbling.
Add milk and broth.
Stir constantly until thick.
Add rest of ingredients.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over hot rolls or toast.

title: oyster soup
directions: Drain juice from oysters into saucepan.
Add milk, margarine, salt and black and cayenne peppers.
Heat thoroughly.
Add drained oysters and continue to cook on low heat until oysters are heated through.
Serve with buttered crackers.

title: out of this world pie
directions: In saucepan, combine pie filling, pineapple, cornstarch, sugar and food coloring.
Cook until thick.
Remove from the heat and add Jell-O.
Cool.
Add banana slices and pecans if desired.
Top with whipped topping.

title: tony's italian sausage on grill(salsiccia arrosto)
directions: This is my husband's specialty.

title: meat cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until soft but not browned.
Add ground beef, breaking up until it loses its pink color.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions. Drain. In skillet, brown ground beef in 1 tablespoon margarine. Stir in tomato sauce.
Remove from heat.
Combine cream cheese, cottage cheese, sour cream, onions and green pepper.
In a buttered 3-quart casserole, spread half the noodles.
Cover with cheese mixture, then cover with remaining noodles.
Pour 2 tablespoons melted margarine over noodles.
Pour ground beef sauce on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fruited acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise; remove seeds.
Place, cut side down, in a shallow baking pan and add boiling water to a depth of 1/2 inch.
Cover and bake squash at 350° for 35 minutes.
Turn cut side up and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients; spoon into squash cavities.
Cover and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Yields 2 servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix meal, flour and salt together.
Mix milk until the meal mixture is paste consistency.
Then add water until dripping consistency.
Drop by tablespoon in deep fryer of grease and cook until golden brown.

title: snowball surprise
directions: Heat sugar and corn syrup just to boiling in 3 quart saucepan over medium heat.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter until blended.
Stir in cereal, cook 5 minutes.
Lightly butter hands; shape about 1/4 cup cereal mixture into a ball around each chocolate kiss.
Immediately roll in candy sprinkles.
About 20 snacks.

title: egg sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Place bread cubes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheese, then browned sausage.
Blend eggs and 2 1/2 cups of milk; add mustard.
Pour over ingredients in pan.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Just before cooking, blend soup and 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over cold casserole. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Set electric skillet to 250° and allow to heat.
Add milk; stir in sugars and margarine.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in pecans.
Cook while stirring until sugar starts to thicken around the edges of skillet.
Turn heat setting to off.
Continue to stir until mixture cools and thickens.
Using a large spoon, drop mixture one at a time on cookie sheet or waxed paper.
Allow to cool.
Serves 12.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate. Ready to serve.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Refrigerate.
Serve with fresh veggies.

title: juicy burger entree
directions: Season to taste over patties and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tender pot roast
directions: Moisten both sides of the roast with water and sprinkle generously with Microshake.
Pierce meat with fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Place meat in a cooking bag.
Microwave 5 minutes on 100% power.
Microwave 30 minutes on 50% power.
Turn meat over and arrange vegetables around meat.
Microwave 45 minutes on 30% power or until meat and vegetables are fork-tender.
Allow meat and vegetables to stand, covered 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: poor man's stroganoff
directions: Brown onion in margarine until opaque.
Add hamburger and brown.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add soup and mushrooms. Simmer 5 minutes.
Just before serving, mix in sour cream.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: sweet potato casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° until well set.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: In large bowl, blend together cake mix, oil, and butter. Beat in eggs, one at a time; beat well. Fold in sour cream and pecans. Pour half of the batter into greased and floured tube pan. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over batter in pan; cover with rest of batter. Do not stir.

title: buttered green beans
directions: Cook beans as package label directs; drain very well.
Add butter or margarine, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Toss lightly to combine.
Makes 2 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugars, oil and eggs.
Beat until well blended.
Sift together flour, salt and spices and mix well.
Stir in raisins, nuts and flour.
Spoon into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean and center cracks open.
Turn onto rack, cool and slice.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: dillworth tomatoes(pudding)
directions: Add sugar and salt to puree.
Boil 5 minutes.
Place bread squares in casserole.
Pour melted butter over them.
Add hot tomato mixture.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes in medium oven.

title: buttermilk corn bread
directions: Sift together corn meal, flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar.
Combine egg, buttermilk and shortening.
Add liquid ingredients to dry mixture, stirring only enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Pour into hot, well greased muffin pans, corn stick pans or 10-inch skillet or pan.
Bake in 450° oven for 20 minutes for muffins or corn sticks, 25 to 30 minutes for square pan or skillet.
Makes about 12 muffins, corn sticks or pieces.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat eggs, sugar and oil, then add alternating with water until well mixed.
Stir in sweet potatoes.
Grease 4 coffee cans or large loaf pans and flour; fill half full.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for
1 hour or until bread pulls away from sides of the pan.
Use coffee cans to store bread.

title: chocolate cake(thin layer)
directions: Mix as directed on cake mix box.
Grease and line cake pans with wax paper.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour 1/2 cup batter in each pan.
Spread out over pan.
Cook only a few minutes.
Cool.
Repeat until all layers are made.
Use your favorite chocolate icing. Very good!

title: easy strawberry layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 inch round cake pans.
Prepare, bake and cool cake according to directions on box. Place one cake layer on serving plate. Spread with strawberry glaze.
Place second cake layer on top.
Frost top and sides of cake with Cool Whip.
Garnish with strawberry slices.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: pk am's stone soup
directions: Go home, put it in a pot and cook.
You will need a great big pot to cook it in and a little pot to pour it in.
You put it on the stove and turn to seven.
Cook a long time.
You can choose 5 minutes, 20 minutes or 1000 minutes.
Then take it out and turn the hot stove off.
Then eat.
Eat with a spoon or draw a picture of a spoon.
You can serve over 5 lettuces, if you want.

title: lecso
directions: Saute onions until tender.
Add green peppers, continue to cook until tender.
Add stewed tomatoes, meat and seasonings. Cook on low setting for about 45 minutes.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli very little.
Add celery, onion, hot rice and cheese.
Add soup.
Mix carefully.
Bake at 325° until bubbly.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter until smooth.
Pat into bottom of pie shell, reserving 1 tablespoon.
Mix pudding mix and milk according to package directions.
Pour over peanut butter and sugar layer.
Refrigerate until set.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle the tablespoon of peanut butter/sugar mixture over Cool Whip for decoration.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix well and pour over cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain grease.
Add rest of ingredients and cook slowly for 2 or 3 hours.

title: angel food cake pudding
directions: Cut the cake into small pieces in a bowl.
Beat the egg yolks, butter and powdered sugar.
Add whipped cream and candy bars. Fold 1/2 cake pieces into pudding mixture.
Top with remaining cake pieces.
Refrigerate until set.

title: soft gingerbread(50 years or older)
directions: Cream sugar, butter and molasses until fairly smooth.
Stir in boiling water.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to molasses mixture gradually, blending well after each addition.
Stir in eggs.

title: cinnamon cucumber rings
directions: Bring syrup to a boil and pour over sliced, drained cucumbers. Let stand all night; then reheat and stand overnight again.
Then pack in jars.
Heat syrup to boiling and pour over filled jars and put 1 stick of cinnamon in jar before sealing.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix together.
Put together in casserole dish.
Bake about 1 hour until golden brown at 350°.

title: bananas barrington
directions: Dust banana halves heavily in the brown sugar and cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Melt butter in a sturdy frying pan over medium-low heat (add a few drops of olive oil to prevent burning). Add coated banana halves and brown.
Cook until evenly browned on each side.
Raise heat to medium for 60 seconds; add brandy extract.
Turn heat down immediately; cover and cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Place 2 halves of banana on four of your favorite dessert dishes.
Add 2 scoops of vanilla ice cream to the center of the banana halves; drizzle with brandy sauce if desired.
Serve immediately.

title: happiness cake
directions: First mix thoroughly and add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy.
Fold in 4 cups prayer and faith to lighten all other ingredients and raise texture to great heights of character. After flouring this into daily living, bake with the heat of human kindness.
Serve with a smile anytime and it will satisfy the hunger of starving souls.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stand.
Line 9-inch deep dish pie pan with crust.
Pour berry mixture in crust.
Cover and seal top with the other crust.
Make slits to let steam out.
Dot with butter and bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until light brown.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Stir these ingredients together with loving care.
Add humor to suit.
Sprinkle with good luck to ensure best results.

title: queso
directions: In a double boiler melt Velveeta.
Fry sausage, breaking it up like crumbs.
Drain well!
Use paper towels to squeeze out all grease.
Once Velveeta is melted, add sausage and Ro-Tel.
Let simmer about 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with restaurant style tortilla chips.

title: golden harvest muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease or place paper liners in 36 muffin cups.
Measure dry ingredients into very large mixing bowl; stir until well blended.
Mix oil, milk, eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Add to dry ingredients, along with apples, carrots, raisins, nuts and coconut.
Stir just until thoroughly blended. Portion into muffin tins, using 1/4 cup (number 16 scoop) each. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until center of muffin springs back. Makes 36 muffins.
These muffins freeze well and reheat beautifully in the microwave.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Pour in buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° until done, then put grated cheese on top and melt.

title: banana coconut creme pie
directions: Cook first four ingredients until thick.
Add egg yolks slowly to thickened mixture and cook mixture again.
Add vanilla and butter.
Cool completely.
Add coconut as desired.
Line pan with bananas.

title: bean and sausage soup
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Crumble bacon and set aside. Saute onion.
Add carrots, potato, parsley, marjoram, pepper and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add sausage and beans (including juice).
Add bacon. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: chip and veggie dip
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and vinegar.
Cook until thick.
Add cream cheese.
Mix until smooth.
Add green pepper and onion.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: slovakian casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Season with salt, pepper and onion.
Add rest of ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. (Or serve right from the pan.)

title: fruit crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8-inch baking dish.
Drain all fruit and coarsely chop.
Combine in baking dish with lemon juice. In bowl, mix oats, butter, sugar, flour and cinnamon until crumbly. Sprinkle over fruit.
Top with walnuts.
Bake 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: sheet cake
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: franks in orange mustard
directions: Cut franks vertically into about 8 pieces per frank.
Heat mustard and marmalade over low heat in a large saucepan.
When this mixture begins to bubble, add franks and cook about 5 minutes.
Franks will puff into small balls.
These are speared with toothpicks and should be served immediately in sauce in a chafing dish.

title: chicken special
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients in a 3-quart dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Onion rings may be put on top.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat together and pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 425° for first 5 minutes, then at 350° until done.

title: easy casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Slice onions and potatoes.
Alternate layers of beef, onions and potatoes.
Pour soup over top.
Bake for 1 hour at 300° or 350°.

title: vegetable stuffed chicken(delicious)
directions: Season body cavity of chicken with seasoned salt. Tie wings flat to body and tie legs together.
Secure neck skin over opening to back with toothpicks.
Sprinkle chicken all over with seasoned salt and paprika.
Place breast side down on baking and roasting pan. Baste with 2 tablespoons of butter.
Loosely cover with 2 pieces of wax paper.
Microwave about 6 minutes per pound, turning 3 times.
After the first 6 minutes of cooking, rotate 1/2 turn and baste from the juices collected in the cooking well.
Cook the second 6 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn and turning chicken breast side up.
Baste chicken with juices collected in cooking well and sprinkle with paprika.
Microwave for another 6 minutes with chicken covered.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and flavorings.
Mix well; add flour sifted with dry ingredients.
Add oatmeal, Krispies and coconut.
Make into small balls.
Press with fork. Bake at 375°.

title: onion meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix ground beef, onion soup mix, milk and egg.
Press mixture firmly in ungreased loaf pan (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch).
Loosen edges with spatula; unmold loaf in ungreased rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix remaining ingredients; spoon onto loaf.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: slender french toast(96 calories per slice)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a shallow bowl; beat well. Coat a large skillet with vegetable cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Dip bread, one slice at a time, into the mix, coating well.
Cook on medium heat 4 minutes on each side or until browned.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: linguine salad
directions: Mix all then refrigerate.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix
flour, salt, sugar and cocoa.
Beat egg yolks well and add the milk, beating until well mixed.
Then add gradually
to the dry ingredients, mixing well.
Cook until thickened (easier if	double	boiler is used).
Be sure to cook several minutes after
the	mixture
thickens,
stirring
constantly. Remove
from fire,
add vanilla and butter.
Beat well.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue or whipped cream.

title: pork tenderloin medallions
directions: Slice tenderloin in 1/2-inch medallions.
Salt and pepper to taste and dust with flour, pressing each medallion with fingertips to flatten slightly; let rest.

title: krispy kritters for kids
directions: Melt margarine; stir occasionally.
Add marshmallows and stir until all are melted.
Stir in Rice Krispies cereal; until well coated.
Wet hands with cold water and shape the mixture into all sorts of imaginary animals.
Use raisins, nuts and chips for faces, spots and details.

title: meatballs pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Let chunks dry; soak bread in juice and squeeze out.
Mix bread, meat, eggs and onion salt. Shape in balls that enclose the pineapple chunks.
Brown slowly in butter and oil, shaking pan to keep balls round.
Drain fat and blend juice with remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture over meatballs and cook for 10 minutes or until sauce boils or thickens.
Serve in chafing dish.

title: peppered beef tenderloin
directions: Combine seasonings and rub over entire tenderloin. Wrap tightly and refrigerate overnight for more intense flavor. Place on a rack in a roasting pan. Bake, uncovered, at 425° until meat is cooked as desired. Allow approximately 45 - 50 minutes for rare or until a meat thermometer reads 140°, 55 - 60 minutes for medium-rare (150°), 62 - 65 minutes for medium (160°), and 67 - 70 minutes for well-done (170°). Let stand 10 minutes before carving.

title: shake-n-bake mix
directions: Stir all ingredients together and store in Tupperware or other plastic ware with seal in refrigerator.
This is equal to 20 packets of Shake 'n Bake coating mix.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes; drain well.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, egg, cheese and onions. Add broccoli and mix well. Place in lightly greased dish.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with crackers. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix and add 1 cup boiling water.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into a pan.
Cover with foil. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Check every 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend all together.
Roll in chopped pecans or walnuts and chill.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Roll out dough.
Brush on oil; add cheese and pepperoni.
Roll up and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: clam cakes
directions: Lightly brown onions and celery in butter.
Add clams to egg, stuffing and water or clam juice.
Add onion and celery mixture and pepper.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoons on a greased cookie sheet and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Makes a little more than 1 gallon.

title: vegetable stew or sort-of ratatouille
directions: Chunk all veggies.
Cook in large frypan until al dente.
Add some water so they don't stick or fat if you prefer.
Add seasonings generously (to taste).
Add 1 can of tomato paste or sauce plus a can of water.
Simmer until all flavors are blended. (Better the second day.)
May serve with cheese on top or add ground meat (just cooked) or use over pasta as the sauce or use your imagination!

title: breakfast casserole
directions: The Night Before:
Pour croutons in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook and drain sausage.
Sprinkle over croutons. Beat eggs and 1 cup of the milk together.
Pour over croutons and sausage.
Sprinkle with cheese to cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: pork roast and sauerkraut
directions: Rub salt and pepper into pork.
Combine remaining ingredients in bottom of Dutch oven or casserole.
Place roast on top of mixture.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat thermometer registers desired doneness.
Slice pork to serve with kraut.

title: peach beauty salad
directions: Drain peach halves; reserve juice.
Arrange peach halves, open side up, in a glass cake pan.
Fill each opening with cream cheese.
Dissolve black cherry Jell-O with 1 cup of boiling water; add 1 cup of ice water.
Pour over peach halves.
Refrigerate until set.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Saute boiled shrimp in skillet sprayed with Pam.
Add remaining ingredients and stir-fry until lightly browned.

title: nacho dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed. Top with shredded cheese. Heat through. Serve with nacho chips.

title: country supper
directions: In large skillet, fry potatoes, carrots, celery and onion in bacon drippings over low heat.
Season with salt and pepper.
When carrots and potatoes are tender, place smoked sausage on top; cover and heat for about 12 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Spread guacamole in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in the following order: sour cream, picante sauce, olives, tomatoes and cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips or large corn chips.

title: pineapple crush cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) pans.
Prepare cake as directed on package.
Divide evenly in pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes; follow package directions for doneness test and cooling.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook Karo syrup, water and sugar until creamy, light amber in color.
Add raw shelled peanuts and continue cooking constantly until peanuts are parched and candy is a little more brown.
Add butter, salt and soda.
Beat 1 minute; pour thinly on buttered tray.
Do not spread with a spoon.
As it cools, stretch out into thin wafer-like pieces.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: nacho sauce dip
directions: In crockpot, on high, brown sausage and onion.
Turn heat to low and add remaining ingredients.
Stir mix as it melts.
Dip with nachos or other munchies.
Yield: 5 pounds sauce.

title: ziploc bag ice cream
directions: Put ingredients in Ziploc bags.
Zip and shake to mix.
Fill 1 gallon Ziploc bag with ice and put salt on top of ice.
Lock and shake bag until milk is thickened up.

title: garbage recipe snack
directions: Mix in tall kitchen garbage bag first three ingredients.
Melt chocolate chips, butter and peanut butter.
Pour over Chex mix in bag.
Mix and then add 1 pound powdered sugar and mix.
Store in containers in refrigerator.

title: delicious apple cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Blend eggs, oil and sugar until creamy.
Add flour, a little at a time. Blend well.
Batter will be stiff.
Fold in apples, coconut and nuts.
Pour into tube pan and bake for 1 hour.
Remove from pan after about 30 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat until light.
Knead with hands.
Roll into small balls. In buttered skillet, brown well. Place in covered dish and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti
directions: Cook and stir hamburger and onions until hamburger is light and brown.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, water, salt, sugar, chili powder and spaghetti.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until spaghetti is tender.

title: caramel sauce(for dipping green apples and pears)
directions: Melt all ingredients in double boiler.
Cut up apples (green) and pears (green) into lengthwise wedges for dipping.

title: doris hanson's dilly cukes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Pour over sliced cucumbers.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: ham and bean soup
directions: Combine.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce to a simmer until vegetables are done.
Serve with French bread.
